Location: West of Coonana on Transline, Western Australia.
Description: Small mallee to 3m tall. Smooth white to pale grey bark. Glossy green to dark green leaves. No mature buds present. Growing on red sand with E. platycorys.

Location: South of Transline near Zanthus on Balladonia track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6-8m tall. Bark hard, rough, dark grey for 1-2m then smooth, light grey. Glossy, dark green leaves. Growing in a pure stand with a Triodia understory.

Location: 100m south of junction of Frances to Bordertown and Naracoorte to Bordertown Road, SA
Description: Tree 10m tall with smooth, flaky grey over yellow cream bark and glaucous buds and fruit.  Leaves dull, grey green.

Location: 100m south of junction of Frances to Bordertown and Naracoorte to Bordertown Road, SA
Description: Juveniles glaucous grey-white leaves.

Location: 200m south east of top of Mount William, Vic.
Description: Robust mallee to 4m tall with glossy light green leaves and smooth tan over white bark throughout.  Growing with E. alpina.

Location: Mount William summit, Vic.
Description: Dense low mallee, 3m tall with glossy green leaves, rough stringy bark and warty buds.  Growing with E. pauciflora ssp. gariwerdensis.

Location: Mount William Road, about 1km below car park, Vic.
Description: Small tree, 7m tall with some rough flaky bark for <1m then smooth or matte creamy white bark.  Leaves slightly glossy, green. On west facing rocky slope with E. baxteri.

Location: Mount William Road, Vic.
Description: Robust tree mallee, 8m tall with glossy green leaves, smooth bark becoming flaky and rough near the base. On west facing rocky slope with E. baxteri.

Location: Just north of summit of Mount Abrupt.
Description: Dense, coarse mallee to 4m tall with thick dark green glossy leaves and thick rough bark.  Similar to E. alpina proper (growing within 100m), but with larger buds and fruits in ones and threes and thicker, broader adults leaves.

Location: Mount Thackeray summit, Vic.
Description: Small tree 10m tall with glossy green leaves and rough bark to 10cm diameter.  Growing on rock nearby E. baxteri and E. obliqua.

Location: Syphion Road, Grampions, Vic.
Description: Small tree 6m tall with dull green leaves and rough grey bark to 10cm diameter then smooth creamy grey. Growing on sandy valley bed with E. obliqua.

Location: Syphion Road, Grampions, Vic.
Description: Juveniles from stump on roadside, leaves dull blue green.

Location: Rose Creek Road, Grampions, Vic.
Description: Scraggly mallee 5m tall, leaves dull bluish green, bark rough to 1m then smooth.  Growing in low forest with E. obliqua.

Location: 1.8km from main Roseworthy to Wirra Road on Mitchell Road, SA
Description: Large mallee, 6m tall. Bark rough, brownish grey to 10cm diameter. Adult leaves dull at first, maturing glossy green. In full flower, leaves pendulous. Growing on red clay/loam with E. dumosa and E. socialis.

Location: 0.7km east from Fairlie and Semmler Roads intersection, SA
Description: Tree mallee, 5m tall. Bark rough, grey brown to 10cm diameter. Leaves pendulous, dull at first, maturing glossy green. Growing on red loam with E. dumosa.

Location: Half way up west side of Mount Moon, SA
Description: Stout mallee, 2-3m tall with glossy green leaves and smooth, grey bark.  No fruits present. Growing in low mallee heath with E. cosmophylla, E. baxteri  and E. leucoxylon ssp. leucoxylon mallee form.

Location: Half way up west side of Mount Moon, SA
Description: Mallee to 3m tall, leaves glossy green, narrower than typical E. leucoxylon. Bark smooth in ribbons, grey over white. Growing in low mallee heath with E. cosmophylls and E. fasciculosa.

Location: Top of hill in Myer Scrub, Fleurieu Peninsula, SA
Description: Small mallee, 3-4m tall. Bark smooth, grey. Leaves thick, glossy, dark green. Many oil glands in leaves just finished flowering. Growing on grey loam with E. aff. odorata.

Location: Top of hill in Myer Scrub, Fleurieu Peninsula, SA
Description: Small mallee, to 4m tall. Bark smooth, grey over tan. Leaves dull, blue/green at first, maturing glossy green. In full flower (white). Growing in grey loam with E. cosmophylla, E. ancipita and E. leptophylla sens. lat.

Location: 50m east of top of hill in Myer Scrub, Fleurieu Peninsula, SA
Description: Small mallee, 1-2m tall. Fruit very rare on plants. Bark smooth, grey over tan. Leaves glossy, yellowish/green. Buds reddish. Many oil glands in leaves, none in stem. Growing with E. aff. odorata (DN 380)

Location: North east boundary of Myer Scrub, Fleurieu Peninsula, SA
Description: Large tree mallee, 8m tall. Bark rough, flaky for 2-4m then smooth. Leaves glossy, green. Some oil glands in leaves. Growing with E. fasciculosa and E. leucoxylon.

Location: Road between Canoe tree and Tonkin's Currency Creek Winery, Fleurieu Peninsula, SA
Description: Mallee 5m tall, erect habit. Bark smooth, light grey. Leaves slightly glossy, green. Growing with E. aff. odorata, E. fasciculosa and E. ancipita.

Location: Road between Canoe tree and Tonkin's Currency Creek Winery, Fleurieu Peninsula, SA
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark rough for 1-2m then smooth, grey over cream. Leaves dull, light blue/green. Buds glaucous. Fruits rare on all plants. Associated with E. fasciculosa.

Location: Road between Canoe tree and Tonkin's Currency Creek Winery, Fleurieu Peninsula, SA
Description: Mallee 3m tall. Leaves thick, dull bluish/green. Flowers white at first, maturing dark pink. Four plants seen. Associated with E. incrasata.

Location: Road between Canoe tree and Tonkin's Currency Creek Winery, Fleurieu Peninsula, SA
Description: Tree mallee 7m tall. Bark rough, dark grey to 15cm diameter. Leaves glossy green (new growth dull bluish/green). In full flower. Associated with E. fasciculosa and Melaleuca decussata.

Location: Base of Mount Barnett, Everard Ranges, SA
Description: Mallee 2m tall. Bark smooth throughout, various shades of white and grey. Leaves dull, grey. Branchlets and fruit glaucous. Growing on granite with E. oxymitra.

Location: Base of Mount Barnett, Everard Ranges, SA
Description: Mallee 2-3m tall. Bark smooth. Leaves dull, green to glaucous. Fruits and twigs glaucous. No buds present. Growing with E.  aff. intertexta on granite.

Location: South base of Mount Barnett, Everard Ranges, SA
Description: Tree 6m tall. Bark tessellated, light brown on trunk and branches. Twigs pendulous. Leaves dull, light green. No buds or mature fruit present. Growing on plain at base of mountain with Eucalyptus oxymitra.

Location: South base of Mount Barnett, Everard Ranges, SA
Description: Mallee 1-3m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream. Leaves dull, grey/green. On granite with E. oxymitra.

Location: 200 m west of Ronalds Well, Everard Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Large mallee 5 m tall. Rough bark for 2 m, then smooth above. Leaves very glossy, green. Growing on sandplain.

Location: 200m west of Ronalds Well, Everard Ranges, SA
Description: Intermediate leaves from previously burnt mallees 2-3m tall. Dark green, glossy, intermediate leaves.

Location: 6.68km due south west of Maynard Bore, Everard Ranges, SA
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Rough, grey bark for 2m then smooth, light pink/grey.  Leaves glossy, green. On red sand dune with no other eucalypts present.

Location: 15km due south west from Maynard Bore, Everard Ranges, SA
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Dull grey/green leaves. Rough, ribbony, grey to tan bark for about 1m, then smooth cream and pink bark. Growing on top of red sand dune with no other eucalypts present.

Location: 8.0 km east from Newton road along Gorge road, then 30m above Torrens River, SA
Description: Mallee to 4m , only 1 clump seen (10 plants). Leaves glossy, green. Bark smooth, greenish yellow over cream. Starting to flower. Associated with Melaleuca lanceolata on a steep rocky slope.

Location: Soldiers memorial above Melrose, south Flinders Ranges SA.
Description: Mallee to 9 m tall with dark grey, rough, fibrous bark throughout. Leaves dull blue-green, old mature leaves (few) glossy green. Growing in Rocky loam in pure stand. E. microcarpa and E. cladocalyx nearby.

Location: Near top of Point Bonney, Wilpena Pound Ranges, SA. 1100m alt.
Description: Mallee to 6m. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, grey and white. Leaves (adult) dull or rarely glossy, blue green. Growing in rock crevice, dominant plant, no other eucalypts in immediate vicinity. Stems always glaucous, buds and fruits variably glaucous

Location: Top of Mount Illuka Hill, Wilpena Pound Ranges, SA. 1050m alt.
Description: Mallee to 3m tall. Bark smooth, ribbony throughout, leaves dull blue green. Buds and stems glaucous, no fruits present. Co-dominant with E. flindersii.

Location: East base Illuka Hill.
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark shortly fibrous, grey. Leaves dull grey. Twigs and immature fruit glaucous.

Location: East base Illuka Hill.
Description: Mallee to 2m tall. Bark smooth, leaves dull blue grey. Buds  glaucous, starting to flower.

Location: Coonalpyn (Adelaide side of township), SA.
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Bark mostly smooth, olive green or tan over cream. Leaves glossy, green. In full flower (white) staminodes present.  Growing with E. oleosa and E. brachycalyx-rugosa intergrades. AD, CANB, NSW

Location: 15.2 km west of Vic/SA border towards Bordertown, SA
Description: Tree 10m tall. Bark rough, fibrous, dark grey over all trunk. Leaves broad variable among individuals, this tree being near the broadest limit, glossy, green. No buds present. Growing as dominant tree. E. wimmerensis (narrower leaves) and E. leucoxylon subsp. pruinosa nearby. AD, CANB, NSW

Location: 22.8km south from HW8 (Kaniva to Nhill) towards Lemon Springs, Little Desert, Vic.
Description: Large mallee 5m tall. Leaves glossy dark green. Bark stringy, rough throughout. Growing in sand with E. incrassata and E. leptophylla.

Location: 22.8km south from Highway 8 (Kaniva to Nhill) towards Lemon Springs, Little Desert, Vic.
Description: Mallee 3m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Occurring in small clumps with Eucalyptus arenacea and E. incrassata on sand.

Location: 19.2km west of Goroke then 100m south of road, Vic.
Description: Tree to 12m. Bark brownish grey to 15cm diameter then smooth, leaves pendulous, green and glossy. Growing in low area with E. camaldulensis, E. arenacea and E. leucoxylon pruinosa.

Location: 500m below Mount Aripiles summit car park, Vic.
Description: Scraggy tree or mallee to 6m tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. Juveniles glossy green. Bark rough, thin, fibrous over trunk. Growing with E. leucoxylon stephaniae. Dominant eucalypt.

Location: 500m below Mount Aripiles summit car park, Vic.
Description: Juveniles of DN 449 from stem coppice near road. Glossy green. Stems red, strongly quadrangular.

Location: 500m below Mount Aripales summit car park, Vic.
Description: Small tree 8m tall. Canopy sparse. Bark rough, thin, grey for 2m then smooth grey over cream. Leaves glossy light green. Growing with E. sp. nov. aff. goniocalyx.

Location: About 600m from Main Wimmera Highway towards summit of Mount Aripiles.
Description: Erect mallee to 8m tall. Bark rough grey. Leaves variable in width, slightly glossy green to slightly blue-green. No other eucalypts present. No buds present. AD, CANB, NSW

Location: 3.8km south of Lower Norton towards Nurrabiel, Vic.
Description: Large mallee 7m tall. Bark rough, tessellated, dark grey for about 1m then smooth grey over copper. Leaves glossy olive green. Growing on top of rise with E. wimmerensis and E. leptophylla.

Location: 400m east of Mirrawana Gap, Grampians, Vic.
Description: Mallee 1m tall, some up to 2.5m. Bark rough and stringy or smooth dark grey. Leaves glossy green. Growing as dominant Eucalypt on steep north facing slope with E. alaticaulis. No integration with E. baxteri seen.

Location: 47km from Avoca towards Ararat, Vic.
Description: Scraggly tree 8m tall. Bark rough, scaly throughout. Leaves dull grey green. Growing on rise with E. melliodora and E. camaldulensis.

Location: 16.5km from Avoca towards Maryborough, Vic
Description: Small tree 8m tall. Bark rough throughout, grey. Leaves dull, grey at first, becoming blue green. Branchlets slightly pruinose. Growing on rise in open forest with E. tricarpa and E. microcarpa.

Location: 4.0 km south of Chewton, Victoria.
Description: Scraggly tree 8m tall. Bark rough, brown throughout. Leaves dull grey green, maturing glossy green. Branchlets and buds glaucous. Growing on rise with E. polyanthermos subsp. vestita and E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha. AD, CANB, NSW

Location: NA
Description: Tree 7m tall. Bark rough throughout, dark grey. Leaves dull, grey green, becoming glossy inside crown. Growing on ridge with E. obliqua and E. aff. aromophloia.

Location: Opposite "Southern Rose" Rose Gardens, Torquay, Vic.
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark rough, thin and flaky for 1.5m then smooth. Leaves dull green, beginning to flower, no other Eucalypts present. Fresh specimens not glaucous.

Location: Ironbark basin car park on Point Addis Road, Vic.
Description: Tree to 10m tall. Bark rough, deeply furrowed, almost black. Leaves slightly glossy green. Flower white.  Growing in orange clay with E. obliqua.

Location: C 500m from Point Addis Road on Forrest Road, near Anglesea, Vic.
Description: Small bushy tree 6m tall. Bark rough, tan to brown throughout. Adult leaves slight discolourous when new then dull green. Growing with E. obliqua.

Location: 500m east of Forrest Road, near Anglesea, Vic.
Description: Tree 7m tall. Bark rough, thin, brown for 2m then smooth and ribbony. Leaves glossy green. Growing with E. obliqua.

Location: Irirurquarts Bluff, 7.5km west of Anglesea in gully on NE side of road.
Description: Tree 12 to 15m tall. Dense canopy. Bark variable, rough and flaky or smooth, grey and cream. Leaves glossy green. Growing on orange clay and ironstone with E. obliqua.

Location: Irirurquarts Bluff, 7.5km west of Anglesea in gully on north east side of road.
Description: Juveniles from coppice near road. Glossy green, slightly discolourous leaves.

Location: Allenvale Road, Lorne, Victoria.
Description: Tree 30 metres tall. Bark smooth, light grey over cream. Leaves glossy green. Pure stand, with Eucalyptus obliqua nearby.

Location: About 1km past Irskine Falls, north of Lorne, Vic.
Description: Tree 10m tall, others to 40m. Bark rough, thin, grey for 2m then smooth grey over cream. Leaves glossy light green. Growing in tall forest with E. viminalis and stringybark sp. AD, CANB, NSW

Location: Otway Ranges, east or Deanes Marsh, Vic.
Description: Tree 18m tall, others to 30m. Bark smooth olive or grey over white. Leaves glossy, dark green, buds glaucous.

Location: Mount Richmond township (east side), Vic.
Description: Small bushy tree 5m tall. Bark rough dark brown. Leaves glossy green. Growing with E. willisii and E. obliqua.

Location: North boundary Canunda National Park on N-S track.
Description: Tree 5m tall, bark rough dark grey to 10-20cm diameter then smooth grey over tan and cream. Leaves slightly glossy green. In flower (cream). No other eucalypts present. On low ground behind sandhills.

Location: (17.2km east of Nora Craena turn off). 7.9km east of Lake George Resort turn off towards Beachport.
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark smooth grey. First seen coming from the east since Nelson. Growing with Acacia sophorae.

Location: (11.2km east of Nora Craena turn off). 1.9km east of Lake George Report turn off towards Beachport.
Description: Tree 6m tall. Leaves glossy green. Bark flaky grey and cream. Flowers cream. Growing on slight rise on limestone and E. diversifolia.

Location: Abound12km east of Robe towards Nora Craena, SA
Description: Tree 7m tall. Leaves narrow glossy green. Flowers pale pink-cream. Bark smooth grey over white. Two trees only, no other eucalypts present. Grey loam. Branclets pendulous.

Location: 5.1km from Princes Highway towards Penola, SA
Description: Tree to 10m. Leaves glossy green. Bark smooth flaky, grey and cream. Branchlets variably glaucous. Growing as only eucalypt present.

Location: 22.3km from Princes Highway, east towards Penola, SA
Description: Robust tree-mallee 6m tall. Bark rough, finely furrowed, grey. Leaves glossy green. Venation acute. Growing in pure stand in bracken. E. camaldulensis and E. cygetensis elsewhere.

Location: Snow Gum Reserve - central track, SA
Description: Tree 12m tall. Bark mostly smooth, grey over white. Some ribbony bark at base. Leaves glossy green. Venation parallel, glands numerous. Growing in forest with E. cygnetensis and A. melanoxylon. Seed of another tree.

Location: 12.7 south of Narracourte then about 800m east to scrub, then about 800m north to top of hill.
Description: Tree 7m tall, other to 12m. Bark rough and flaky for about 2m then smooth, light grey. Leaves glossy green. Buds yellow, flower white, no fruit. Growing on sandy hill top with E. baxteri and E. cygnetensis

Location: 12.7 south of Narracourte then about 800m east to scrub, then about 800m north to top of hill. .
Description: Juvenile leaves dull olive green not glaucous.

Location: 3.0km from Hynum towards Frances, SA
Description: Tree 15m tall. Bark dark grey, rough, tightly held. Leaves glossy ollive green. No buds. Small stand in E. camaldulensis forest. Most southerly stand seen.

Location: Mary Seymore Conservation Reserve about 500m west of north boundary, SA
Description: Tree 18m tall. Bark rough, thick, dark grey for about 2m then smooth grey/orange and cream. leaves glossy green. Oil

Location: 47.4km from Salt Creek towards Kingston, SA
Description: Mallee 4m tall, bark smooth grey and olive green over cream. Leaves glossy green, juveniles on stem glossy light green. Flowers pink. Growing on limestone plain with E. diversifolia.

Location: West side of base of Mt. Wudinna, South Australia
Description: Large mallee 6 metres tall. Bark rough, thick dark grey over grey. Leaves glossy green, intramarginal vein well in from leaf edge. Glands moderately dense. Growing in pure stand with Dodonaea  understory. Flowers white.

Location: 3.2km north of Eyre Hill on Cook Track, South Australia
Description: Mallee 2m tall. Bark rough grey throughout. Leaves dull blue green. Growing on plain in small stands with M. lanceolata - compare with DN 484 & 485.

Location: 3.2km north of Eyre Hill on Cook Track, South Australia
Description: Mallee 3m tall. Bark rough grey throughout. Leaves slightly glossy blue green. Bud variation. Growing on plain in small stands with M. lanceolata - compare with DN 483 & 485. Intergrade with E. oleosa ?

Location: 3.2km north of Eyre Hill on Cook Track, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 3m tall. Bark rough grey throughout. Leaves dull blue green. Bud variation within population. Growing on plain in small stands with M. lanceolata - compare with DN 483 & 484. Intergrade with E. oleosa ?

Location: Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 8m tall. Bark thick, rough to 2m then smooth grey over cream. Leaves dull blue green. Flowers pale yellow. Growing on sand dune with Acacia anura (in red sand).

Location: Cook - Vokes Hill track, Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Effuse mallee 6 metres tall. Bark rough, thick red-brown to 3cm diameter. Leaves glaucous grey green. Buds and fruits glaucous. Old fruits not glaucous. Growing on red sand dune with Eucalyptus eucentrica.  Photos 1.

Location: Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark rough for about 2m then smooth. Leaves very glaucous, grey. No flowers present. Buds may be slightly disformed as last ones on trees. Growing in red sand with E. concinna, E. yumbarrana and E. striaticalyx "GVD form".

Location: Junction of Cook to Vokes Hill Rd and Oak Valley to Tjuntjunjara Rd, Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 2m tall. Bark rough for about 1m then smooth. Leaves slightly glossy to dull, green. No parts glaucous. Common on red sand plain with E. yumbarrana, E. concinna and E. pimpiniana. AD, CANB

Location: Cross Road, Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4m. Bark rough, thick and grey to 1m them smooth cream. Leaves glossy green. Flowers pale yellow. Growing as dominant mallee with E. aff. striaticalyx (DN 489) and E. pimpiniana on red sand plain.

Location: 34km from Cross Road,  Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Leaves glaucous grey. Flowers lemon yellow. Bark rough for about 2m, brown & ribbony above. Growing as dominant Eucalypt on red sand plain with E. concinna. Photos 2.

Location: 74km from Cross Road,  Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Spreading mallee 3m tall. Bark rough and ribbony for 1m then smooth pure white. Leaves dull grey-green. Growing on sand plain with E. eucentrica. Oil glands numerous.

Location: 157km from Cross Road,  Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark rough, dark grey to about 3m (most of trunk). Leaves dull, blue green. Flowers pale yellow, fruits rare. Growing as a small pure stand on red sand plain.

Location: 157 km west from cross roads,  Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Bark smooth white throughout. Leaves glossy, dark green. Pure stand on red sand plain. No mature buds present. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: 158km from Cross Road,  Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Large mallee 8m tall. Bark rough & ribbony on lower trunk. Leaves dull, green. Flowers yellow. One pure stand on low red sand dune.

Location: 178 km west from cross roads,  Great Victoria Desert, WA.
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark rough at butt, then smooth pure white. Leaves glossy, dark green. New growth red. Growing on red sand with E. concinna, E. eucentrica and E. oleosa. AD, CANB

Location: 178 km west from cross roads,  Great Victoria Desert, WA.
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark smooth grey over cream throughout. Leaves glossy green. Flowers white. Growing on red sand with E. gracilis and E. eucentrica. AD, CANB

Location: 178km from Cross Road,  Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Bark smooth, white & slightly powdery throughout. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing on red sand with E. gracilis and E. eucentrica.

Location: 179km from Cross Road,  Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark rough and hard for about 1.5m. Leaves not glaucous, dull blue green. Buds & fruits & stems glaucous. Growing on red sand with E. eucentrica.

Location: 311km from Cross Road,  Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream. Leaves very glossy, dark green. Growing on orange sand with A. anuara.

Location: NA
Description: Mallee to 7m tall. Bark rough, thick, dark grey to about 2m. Leaves dull grey green. Flowers pale yellow. Growing on south side of dry lake with E. concinna.

Location: South-west of Jubilee Lake on edge of Great Victoria Desert, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4m. Bark smooth, grey throughout. Leaves very glossy, dark green. No buds present. Growing with E. aff. salicola and E. eucentrica on south side of dry lake.

Location: South-west of Jubilee Lakes, WA
Description: Mallee to 4m tall. Bark smooth, ribbony, cream in colour. All mallees burnt in fire, no live adult leaves, buds or fruits. Juvenile leaves glaucous, very glandular and grey. Growing on south side of dry lake with E. concinna on red sand.  AD, CANB, PERTH Photo.

Location: NA
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark smooth, light tan over cream on north side, curled & ribbony on south side of stems. Leaves glossy green with many oil glands. Dominant mallee on south side of dry lake with E. eucentrica and E. concinna on red sand.  Photos.

Location: NA
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark smooth, light tan over cream on north side, curled & ribbony on south side of stems. Leaves glossy green with many oil glands. With fruit.  Dominant mallee on south side of dry lake with Eucalyptus eucentrica and E. concinna on red sand.

Location: NA
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark smooth grey/white throughout. Leaves glossy green. Growing on red sand plain with E. oleosa.

Location: Near Kitchener on Transline, WA
Description: Large mallee 8m tall. Bark rough and thick, dark grey to 10-15cm diameter then smooth grey over cream. Leaves glossy dark green with numerous oil glands. First eucalypts after Rawlinna. AD, CANB

Location: NA
Description: Mallee 3m tall. Bark smooth grey over cream. Leaves very glossy, dark green with numerous island oil glands. Growing on red sand with E. gracilis, E. oleosa and E. hypolaena.

Location: Between Zanthus and Kitchener on Transline, WA
Description: Large mallee 8m tall. Bark rough, thick and dark grey to brown to 15cm diameter. Leaves very glossy green. Glands numerous in stem. Dominant with E. cylindrocarpa on red sand. AD, CANB

Location: Between Zanthus and Kitchener on Transline, WA
Description: Mallee 3m tall. Bark smooth grey over light grey. Leaves glossy yellowish green. Many oil glands in leaves. No green fruits present. Dry fruits cup-shaped. Growing on red sand with E. melanoxylon and E. platycorys. AD, CANB

Location: Between Zanthus and Kitchener on Transline, WA
Description: Mallee 2.5m tall. Bark smooth grey. Leaves glossy green. Oil glands absent. Only 1 mallee with E. platycorys and E. gracilis on edge of Ponton Creek. AD, CANB

Location: Between Zanthus and Kitchener on Transline, WA
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream. Leaves dull grey green, maturing finally to slightly glossy. Flowers white. Growing on gravelly red sand with E. hypolaena, E. gracilis and E. comitaevallis. AD, CANB

Location: Near Coonana on Transline, WA
Description: Tree 15m tall. Bark rough, almost black to 1.5m then smooth orange and tan over white. Leaves dull grey green. Twigs glaucous. Flowers yellow. On red sand plain with E. salubris.  AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: NA
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Bark smooth grey over olive green. Leaves glossy green. Reticulation sparse. Growing on red sand with E. ravida.

Location: North of Transline between Karonie and Coonana, WA
Description: Mallee 7m tall. Bark rough, fibrous and grey for 0.5m then smooth grey over light green. Buds and fruit not glaucous. Twigs to 5cm diameter very glaucous. Growing on slight rise with E. hypolaena, E. trichopoda and E. loxophleba lissophloia. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: NA
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Bark rough, thick, dark grey to brown over most of stems. Leaves glossy green. Growing on red sand with E. optima hypoleana and E. undulans?

Location: NA
Description: Juveniles from roadside. Glaucous, decurrent grey juveniles.

Location: WA
Description: Mallee 2.5m tall. Bark smooth dark over light grey. Leaves erect, dull, grey green. No buds present. Growing on red sand on slight rise with E. youngiana and E. rigidula.

Location: Near Ponton Creek, Great Victoria Desert, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 8m tall. Bark smooth white with many tan and grey scales on trunk. Leaves dull, grey green. Buds and twigs glaucous. Growing on sand rise with E. rigidula.

Location: Great Victoria Desert, WA
Description: Small mallee 3m tall. Bark smooth, coppery. Leaves glossy green. Operculum bright red. In full flower and bud. Style articulate. Growing on gravelly red sand on rise with E. concinna.

Location: 7.1 km north of Mulga Rockhole, WA.
Description: Mallee 2x3m. Bark smooth ribbony, light grey. Leaves dull blue green. Flowers yellow. Growing on red sand with E. undulans and E. platycorys.

Location: 7.1 km north of Mulga Rockhole, WA.
Description: Erect mallee 5m tall. Bark smooth grey over cream. Leaves glossy green. Buds red on north side. Growing with Eucalyptus platycorys, E. gongylocarpa, E. youngiana and E. pimpiniana on red sand.

Location: 7.1 km north of Mulga Rockhole, Great Victoria Desert, Western Australia.

Location: Summit of Iron Duchess, Middleback Ranges, Eyre Peninsula, SA
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark rough for about 2m, dark grey-brown. Leaves glossy, light green, with many island oil glands. On rocky summit in mallee scrub with E. oleosa. AD, CANB

Location: Iron Duchess, about 500m E of summit, Middleback Ranges, Eyre Peninsula, SA
Description: Mallee 4-5m tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2m, grey-brown then smooth. Leaves blue-green at first maturing glossy, green. On steep SE facing slope with E. oleosa and E. gracilis. AD, CANB, NSW Photos

Location: 300m S of Ronald Well, Everard Ranges, SA
Description: Multistemmed tree 5m tall. Bark persistant, flakey, red-brown and grey. Leaves concolorous, dull, pale green, no intramarginal vein. Growing below granite outcrops, Eucalyptus sparsa and E. camaldulensis var. obtusa nearby. AD Photos

Location: Near Currie Creek, south of Musgrave Rngs, SA
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Bark rough for 2 to 3m, thick, dark grey. Leaves dull, grey-green. Buds, fruits and twigs variably glaucous. On slight rise of red sand over limestone. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Near Currie Creek, SA
Description: Rounded Mallee 4m tall. Bark smooth, tan over cream. Leaves dull, grey-green. Twigs glaucous. On red sand between dunes. AD Photos

Location: North east of Moolapinna Hill Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Large mallee 7m tall. Bark rough, loose for 2m then smooth. Flowers cream. Twigs very slightly glaucous. Top of red sand dune, only one clump. May be an intergrade with E. oxymitra. AD, CANB Photos

Location: North east of Moolapinna Hill Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark rough, dark grey for 1m then smooth, cream. Leaves very glossy, dark green with many large, island oil glands. On red sand dune with E. glomerosa. (First seen from N.) AD, CANB Photos

Location: North east of Moolapinna Hill Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark rough, coarse, dark grey-brown for 2m then smooth. Leaves very glossy, green. Pith glands absent. In red sandy swale between dunes with E. oxymitra. AD, CANB Photos

Location: SW base of Moolapinna Hill, SA
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark rough, almost black on lower half. Leaves very glossy, green. At foot slopes of rocky, steep hill in small pure stand. AD Photo

Location: South east of Mt Lindsay, Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Spreading tree 7m tall. Bark rough, deeply tessellated, grey-brown to small branches. Leaves dull, pale green. Operculum smooth (not scurfy). (Buds only present in AD specimen). On red sand dune below rock dome. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Base of Mt Lindsay, Birksgate Range, SA
Description: Tree 8m tall. Bark rough, yellowish and grey, thin for 2m and then smooth cream. Leaves dull, grey-green. In red sand below granite slope with Corymbia eremaea. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Base of Mt Lindsay, Birksgate Range, SA
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark rough, loose, grey over most of stems. Leaves glossy, green. Pure stand. Nearby is  E. intertexta and C. eremaea. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Base of Mt Wooltarlinna, Birksgate Range, SA
Description: Tree 7m tall. Bark rough, tessellated, brown-grey. Leaves slightly glossy green. On red sand plane below rocky mountain with Eucalyptus intertexta. AD, CANB Photos

Location: north east side of Mt Wooltarlinna, Birksgate Range, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall, some others up to 5 m tall. Bark smooth, grey over cream. Leaves concolourous, dull, blue-green at first, maturing slightly glossy, green. Reticulation moderate with many small, mostly island oil glands. Crevices in granite dome with Corymbia eremaea subsp. eremaea and Eucalyptus intertexta. AD, CANB, PERTH, NSW Photos

Location: South of Mt Poondinna, Great Victoria Desert, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark ribbony rough at base, otherwise smooth tan over cream. Leaves dull, grey-green. Twigs slightly glaucous. On red sand between dunes with Eucalyptus youngiana. AD, CANB Photos

Location: South of Mt Poondinna, Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Tree 8m tall. bark rough, strongly tessellated, light grey brown. Leaves slightly glossy, pale green. On side of red sand dune with Eucalyptus youngiana. AD, CANB Photos

Location: South of Mt Poondinna, Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Spreading mallee 5m tall. Bark rough for about 2m, thick, loose, dark grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. In red sand between dunes with E. youngiana and E. glomerosa. AD, CANB Photos

Location: South of Mt Poondinna, Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Tree to 8m tall. Bark smooth, dull to glossy, white, powdery. Leaves dull blue-grey. Twigs, leaves, buds and fruits glaucous.On red sand with E. youngiana and C. eremaea. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Near Iltur Outstation, Great Victoria Desert, South Australia
Description: Multi-stemmed tree 6 metres tall. Bark rough, tessellated, soft, grey-brown. Leaves slightly discolorous, dull, pale green. Growing in red sand with mulga scrub. AD, CANB Photos

Location: South west of Moolapinna Hill, Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Bark rough, thick, loose, dark grey for 2m then smooth light tan. Leaves very glossy, dark green. On red sand dune with E. youngiana. AD, CANB Photos

Location: South west of Moolapinna Hill, Great Victoria Desert, SA
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark rough for 1m, thick, soft, dark grey then smooth, pale salmon. Leaves dull, grey-green. New growth glaucous. On red sand dune in pure stand. AD, CANB Photos

Location: North west of Oodnadatta, SA
Description: Mallee 5m tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 m, coarse, dark grey then smooth orange-tan. Leaves dull blue-green to green. Buds weakly glaucous. On limestone rise in powdery loam. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Near Lake William, south east of William Creek, SA
Description: Tree-mallee 6m tall. Bark rough, box type, grey for 1 to 2m then smooth, cream. Leaves dull, blue-green. Growing on red sand dune on floodplain, probably originally on floodplain floor. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Near Hermit Hill on south side of Lake Eyre South, SA
Description: Mallee 6m tall, some others developing into small trees. Bark rough for about 2m then smooth pale salmon grey. Leaves dull blue-green. On low powdery limestone rise with little other vegetation. AD, CANB Photos

Location: About 67km N of Innaminka towards Cordillo Downs HS, SA
Description: Tree, some multi-stemmed, 6m tall. Bark rough, tessellated, red brown to grey to small twigs. Leaves slightly glossy, light green. No green fruits or buds. On red sand plane. AD Photo

Location: East of Angepena, Gammon Ranges NP, Flinders Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark rough at base, fibrous, grey, otherwise smooth light grey over orange. Leaves dull blue-grey. Twigs, new leaves, buds and fruits glaucous. On steep south facing slope in rocky, powdery loam. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Near Salt Creek, SA
Description: Tree 5m tall. Bark more or less smooth, grey over cream, decorticating in plates. Leaves slightly glossy, green. Twigs strongly glaucous. Flowers cream, staminoides present. In loam over limestone with E. diversifolia. AD, CANB  Photos

Location: Snow Gum Reserve, near Caroline, north edge of reserve, SA

Location: near Mt Richmond township, Vic
Description: Tree 8m tall. Bark rough for about 2m, grey then smooth tan over cream. Leaves glossy, green, reticulation dense with no oil glands seen. Flowers white. On rise with E. willisii and E. baxteri. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Stevens road, east of Portland, Vic
Description: Erect, robust, mallee, 6 m tall. Bark smooth, tan over light brown. Leaves glossy, light green with many, mostly island oil glands. In low swampy area with E. splendens? AD Photo

Location: Stevens road turnoff to Mt Richmond NP from HW 1, east of Portland, Vic
Description: Tree 10m tall. Bark rough, finely fissured, grey to smaller branches. Leaves glossy, green, reticulation sparse with many mostly island oil glands. Growing with E. splendens. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Stevens road turnoff to Mt Richmond NP from Hwy One, east of Portland, Victoria.

Description: Scraggly mallee 2m tall. Bark rough, more or less stringy. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing on wind-swept cliffs with E. willisii and E. ovata var. graniflora. (and E. baxter?) AD

Location: Between Gellibrand River and Moonlight Head Rd, Otway Ranges, Victoria
Description: Tree 30 metres tall. Bark smooth, pale grey over yellowish cream. Leaves glossy, green, with moderate reticulation and some island oil gland. Growing in more or less pure stand on steep east facing slope. AD

Location: Great Ocean Rd, between Gellibrand River crossing and Moonlight Head Road, Otway Ranges, Victoria.

Location: Aireys Inlet, Victoria.

Location: Dandenong Creek, Glen Waverley, Melbourne, Vic
Description: Tree 6m tall. Bark rough to small branches, thick, fibrous, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, green, reticulation moderate, with no visable oil glands. In swampy creek with E. viminalis on edges. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Near Tynong, Vic
Description: Tree 10m tall. Bark rough throughout, fibrous, brown-grey. Leaves glossy, light green, reticulation dense with some small intersectional oil glands. Dominant, with E. cephalocarpa. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Near Tynong, Vic
Description: Tree 8m tall. Bark rough, fibrous, grey to small branches. Leaves dull, glaucous at first, becoming slightly glossy, green, within crown. Buds glaucous. Growing with E. radiata and Swamp Gum. AD, CANB

Location: Tarago River, near Bunyip, Victoria.
Description: Tree 15 m tall, (others to 20 m tall.) Bark rough for about 2m, thin, brown then smooth, grey over cream. Leaves more or less concolourous, glossy, green, reticulation moderate with many mostly island oil glands. On swampy river flat. AD, CANB Photos

Description: Tree 25m tall. Bark rough, coarsly stringy, grey-brown over red-brown. Leaves more or less concolourous, glossy, green. In more or less pure stand on low, broad rise. AD, CANB

Location: Near Metung, Vic

Location: Near Metung, Vic

Location: Near Metung, Vic
Description: Tree 18m tall. Bark smooth, grey and light grey over yellow-cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing on slopes above creek with E. bosistoana and E. baueriana. AD, CANB

Location: Between Metung and Swan Reach, Vic
Description: Tree 10m tall. Bark smooth (some chunky bark at base), grey and brown over cream. Leaves slightly glossy, green. Beside river with E. baueriana. AD, CANB

Location: Snowy River south of Orbost, Vic
Description: Tree 25m tall. Bark rough to 5cm diameter, thick, flakey, red - brown. Leaves strongly discolourous, glossy, green above. Growing in pure stands on river flat. AD

Location: Between Marlo and Cape Conran, Victoria
Description: Dense crowned scraggly tree 6 metres tall. Bark rough on trunk or to small branches, dark grey. Leaves glossy, light green. Growing in dense coastal scrub with Eucalyptus botyoides. AD

Description: Erect whipstick like mallee (or slender tree) 6 metres tall. Bark rough at base otherwise smooth grey over yellow-white. Leaves thick, non undulate, slightly discolourous, glossy, light green above, reticulation moderate, with many mostly island oil glands. In inpeneratable tall heath in swamp between (old dunes?) AD, CANB, NSW Photos

Location: Errinundra River, north of Club Terrace, Vic
Description: Narrow tree 30m tall. Bark rough, finely fissured, grey for about 4m then smooth, light grey over cream. Leaves glossy, green. Growing above river with E. cypellocarpa and E. yangoura. AD

Location: Errinundra Plateau, Vic
Description: Tree 50m tall. Bark rough at butt, otherwise smooth, grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing on steep slopes with E. fastigata ? AD

Location: West of Cann River, Vic
Description: Tree 8m tall. Bark rough, finely fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue - grey. Growing with E. obliqua, E. cypellocarpa and E. yangoura. AD

Location: Near Genoa, Vic
Description: Tree 15m tall. Bark rough finely fissured, dark grey. Leaves discolourous, glossy, green above. Growing on rise with E. yangoura. AD

Location: near Eden, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 12m tall. Bark rough, to small branches, finely fissured, grey. Leaves dull, green. Flowers cream. On rise with Eucalyptus cypellocarpa and E. globoidea. AD, CANB

Location: Dr. George Mountain just below trig point, east of Bega, NSW
Description: Whipstick mallee 4m tall. Bark smooth, grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green, reticulation sparse, with many island glands. Growing in between granite bedrock.  AD, CANB Photos

Location: Near Narooma, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 18 metres tall. Bark smooth, blotched grey over cream. Leaves glossy, green. Growing on hillside in a nearly pure stand, with a few Eucalyptus botryoides. AD

Location: West of Bodalla, NSW
Description: Tree 20m tall. Bark rough, stringy, brown - grey. Leaves discolourous, glossy, dark green above. Growing with  E. sieberi and E. yangoura. AD

Location: Between Batemans Bay and Braidwood, NSW
Description: Tree 15m tall. Bark rough, stringy, grey over red -brown. Leaves glossy, dark blue - green. On rocky rise with E. seiberi. AD

Location: Berrima, NSW

Location: Between Moss Vale and Berrima, NSW
Description: Tree 12m tall. Bark rough, stringy, brown - grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing on rise with E. dives. AD, CANB

Location: Between Bargo and the Hume Freeway, NSW
Description: Tree 12m tall. Bark rough, deeply furrowed, hard, dark grey - brown. Leaves dull, blue - green. Growing with  E. globoidea. AD

Location: Between Bargo and the Hume Freeway, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 10 tall. Bark rough, stringy, grey-brown. Leaves strongly discolourous, glossy, green above. Growing with  Eucalyptus punctata, E. globoidea and Corymbia gummifera. AD, CANB

Location: Between Braidwood and Araluen, NSW

Location: near Pikes Saddle on western edge of Deua NP, NSW

Location: Approach track to Mother Woila from Dampier trig, about 3/4 way there, Deua NP, NSW

Description: Tree 15m tall. Bark rough, finely fissured, brown-grey, to small twigs. Leaves dull, blue-green. Buds glaucous. On steep slope with E. dives and E. mannifera. AD, CANB

Location: West of Swanpool, Victoria.
Description: Tree 20 m tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy, thick, grey - brown. Leaves dull, blue green. Growing with E. macrorhyncha, E. radiata subsp. radiata and E. rubida subsp. rubida. AD

Location: Near Torbreck Station, south east of Eildon, Vic
Description: Tree 15m tall. Bark rough, thick, stringy, grey - brown. Leaves slightly glossy, slightly blue - green. New growth slightly glaucous. In forest with E. viminalis ssp. viminalis and E. robertsonii. AD

Location: Silver Gums Reserve?, Just south of Buxton, Vic
Description: Scraggly small tree, or mallee, 5m tall. Bark mostly smooth, grey, some rough bark towards base. Leaves discolourous, grey. All parts glaucous. In low swampy area with E. ovata - camphora and E. robertsonii (dull green) AD

Location: About 500 metres along cliffs from eastern edge of Newland Head CP to east.
Description: Mallee 4m tall. Bark smooth, cream. Leaves glossy, green. Growing on coastal cliffs with E. diversifolia and E. leptophylla.

Location: NA

Location: NA

Location: NA
Description: Mallet 9 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 metres, thick, moderately fissured, almost black, smooth above, light grey over cream. Leaves very glossy, green. Growing on broad rise in red powdery earth with Eucalyptus salubris, E. urna and E. yilgarnensis. CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: NA
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey over cream. Leaves, buds and branchlets strongly glaucous, less so in others, but all here with at least some glaucescence. Leaves maturing glossy and green. Growing on + flat in gritty pale loam with Eucalyptus salmonophloia, E. sheathiana, E. salubris, E. neutra, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae and E. tephroclada. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: NA
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey over tan. Leaves glossy, dark green, some others here paler green. Growing near top of rise with Eucalyptus calycogona subsp. calycogona, E. sheathiana, E. capillosa subsp. polyclada, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae and E. tephroclada. PERTH Photos

AD, CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: 4.6 km north from Quairding - York road, Western Australia.

CANB, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus erythronema var. erythronema x E. salubris
Location: Between Walgoolan and Bodallin on Great Eastern Highway, Western Australia.

CANB, PERTH

Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey and tan over cream. Rare here, growing in orange lateritic loam in low forest vegetation with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus marginata . CANB, PERTH

Location: Near Mundijong, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 9 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, powdery white over pink, with some attached brown flakes. Leaves very slightly discolorous, glossy, green. Flowers white. Growing on grey sandy flat with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: North-east of Badgingarra, Western Australia
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Barksmooth throughout, light grey over cream. Leaves + glossy, green to slightly blue-green, reticulation moderate, with scattered intersectional oil glands. Flowers cream. Two plants here, growing on laterite rise with white sand with Eucalyptus todtiana. AD, CANB, PERTH photos

Location: North-east of Badgingarra, Western Australia
Description: Spreading, low mallee 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, light grey and tan. All parts glaucous. Leaves dull, greyish. Common here, growing on slight slope of white sand over laterite in low sand heath with Eucalyptus macrocarpa subsp. macrocarpa. CANB, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus accedens x E. loxophleba subsp. loxophleba
Location: 200 metres E along track from below coordinates (Boothendara Hill), Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 metres, curled-flaky, grey-brown, smooth above, light grey and tan. Leaves dull, slightly grey-green, scattered island oil glands. Growing as single sand 15 metres in diameter in thck Casuarina scrub with Eucalyptus accedens and E. loxophleba subsp. loxophleba. CANB, PERTH photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus accedens x E. loxophleba subsp. loxophleba
Location: 400 metres E along track from below coordinates (Boothendara Hill), Western Australia.
Description: Erect mallees 8 metres tall. Bark rough for 0 to 1.5 metres, flaky-chunky, grey, smooth above, light grey over cream. Leaves slightly glossy, green, scattered small intersectional oil glands. Growing as stand of mallees 25 metres in diameter on laterite with Eucalyptus accedens, E. loxophleba subsp. loxophleba and E. gittinsii subsp. illucida. AD, CANB, PERTH photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus x leprophloia (E. accedens x E. zopherophloia)
Location: 500 metres NE onto laterite ridge from below coordinates (Boothendara Hill), Western Australia.
Description: Large mallee 6 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 to 3 metres, flaky-fibrous, grey-brown, smooth above, light grey-brown over cream. Leaves moderately glossy, green, with numerous island oil glands. Growing as single mallee clump on massive laterite plataue with Eucalyptus accedens and E. gittinsii subsp. illucida. CANB, PERTH photos

Location: North of Badgingarra, off Brand Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Large mallees 4 metres tall. Bark rough up to 2 metres, thin, fibrous, grey-brown over yellow-brown, conspicuously smooth above, white. Leaves glossy, very slightly blue-green, fairly thick, reticulation obscure by numerous island oil glands. Growing on massive laterite breakaway with Eucalyptus lateritica, E. drummondii subsp. drummondii and E. gittinsii subsp. illucida. PERTH; photos

Location: North of Badgingarra off Brand Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Robust mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough + throughout, thick, fibrous, grey-brown over yellow-brown. Leaves glossy, dark green, fairly thick, with prominent oil glands. Growing on massive laterite breakaway with Eucalyptus suberea, E. drummondii subsp. drummondii and E. gittinsii subsp. illucida. PERTH photos

Location: North of Coolimba , Western Australia.
Description: Juvenile regrowth to 50 cm tall. Leaves slightly discolorous, + dull, light green. Burnt out country of white sand over limestone, only a few of these mallees here. CANB, PERTH

Location: 11.6 km west of Northampton on Pt Gregory road, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, greenish yellow and powdery white. Leaves slightly glossy, slightly blue-green. Growing on creek in + pure stand. Buds and fruits large in this population. CANB, PERTH

Location: 37.5 km north from Gregory turnoff on coastal road to Kalbarri, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall. Bark rough to 240 mm circ., grey, smooth above, grey over light grey and cream. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing slightly glossy, green, reticulation moderate, with intersectional and island oil glands. Flowers cream. Co-dominant here, growing in pale brown sand over limestone in dense mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus obtusiflora. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: 37.5 km north from Gregory turnoff on coastal road to Kalbarri, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough to 290 mm circ., grey, smooth above, grey over light grey and cream. Leaves  slightly glossy, slightly blue-green, reticulation moderate, with moderately dense intersectional and island oil glands. Flowers cream. Co-dominant here, growing in pale brown sand over limestone in dense mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus obtusiflora. CANB, PERTH

Location: 2.1 km west along south boundary of Kalbarri National Park from Kalbarri to Gregory road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough throughout (to twigs), fibrous, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, green, numerous intersectional oil glands. large population here, growing on brown sand and limestone with Eucalyptus oraria. AD, CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: 2.1 km west along south boundary of Kalbarri National Park from Kalbarri to Gregory road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough to 1.5 to 2 metres, fibrous, dark grey; smooth above, glossy, brown and olive green-grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. New growth yellowish. Growing on brown sand and limestone with Eucalyptus kalbarriensis. PERTH

Location: 0.1 km west along south boundary of Kalbarri National Park from Kalbarri to Gregory road, Western Australia.
Description: Regrowth mallees 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, slightly blue-green at first, maturing green. No fruit found. Growing as 4 or 5 mallees on broad high rise in grey sand. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: Eagle Gorge turnoff on Kalbarri to Gregory road, Kalbarri Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2.5 metres tall. Bark rough to 200 mm circ., dark grey-brown, smooth above, grey over cream. Leaves slightly glossy, green at first, maturing glossy, dark green, reticulation moderate, with moderately sparse intersectional oil glands. Flowers cream. Co-dominant here, growing in pale red sand over limestone in low mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus obtusiflora and E. eudesmioides. PERTH

Location: South of Kalbarri township, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee 2 metres tall. Bark ribbony-rough over most of stems, pale grey over yellow tan. Leaves glossy, green, scattered oil glands. Growing on sand over limestone overlooking limestone gorge with Eucalyptus eudesmioides, E. obtusiflora and E. dolichocera. CANB, PERTH

Location: Ca. 1 km from Red Bluff towards Kalbarri township, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 1 metres tall, others from 30 cm to 2 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, fibrous. Leaves glossy, green. Large stand growing on broad sand dune of pale red-white sand. Juvenile leaves seen, more like E. hypochlamydea, not like E. rigidula. CANB, PERTH

Location: Ca. 1 km from Red Bluff towards Kalbarri township, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall, others from 30 cm to 2 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, fibrous. Leaves glossy, green.  Large stand growing on broad sand dune of pale red-white sand.  Juvenile leaves seen, more like Eucalyptus horistes, not like E. rigidula. CANB, PERTH

Location: Hawks Head on Murchison River, Kalbarri National, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough for 0.5 metres, ribbony-fibrous, grey, smooth above, cream. Leaves glossy, dark green, reticulation sparse. Growing in pure stand on sandstone escarpment of Murchison River. PERTH Photos

Location: Hawks Head on Murchison River, Kalbarri National, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall. Bark smooth, pink over cream. Leaves dull, becomming slightly glossy, dark green, but whole plant with blue-green look. A few mallees growing in white sand and sandstone boulders with Eucalyptus gittinsii subsp. gittinsii. PERTH

Location: 6.1 km north from Binnu towards Billabong Roadhouse on highway, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4.5 metres tall. Bark rough to 230 mm circ., dark grey-brown, smooth above, light grey-brown over light tan. Leaves glossy, dark green, reticulation moderate, with dense intersectional oil glands. Scattered here, growing in red clay-loam in tall open mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus loxophleba ssp. supralaevis. CANB, PERTH

Location: 9.4 km north of Murchison River bridge on NW Coastal Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough for 30 cm above ground level, box-type, smooth above, glossy, grey and olive green. Leaves glossy, dark green. Flowers white, with staminodes. Several dozen plants growing on rise of red clay-loam in + pure stand. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus dolichocera x E. kochii subsp. borealis
Location: 11.4 km north from Murchison River bridge towards Billabong Roadhouse on highway, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3.5 metres tall. Bark rough to 160 mm circ., dark grey, smooth above, light grey over cream. Leaves glossy, green, reticulation moderate, with dense intersectional and island oil glands. Flowers white. Scattered here, growing in red sand over limestone in tall open mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus obtusiflora, E. dolichocera, E. loxophleba ssp. supralaevis, E. subangusta ssp. subangusta and E. eudesmioides. CANB, PERTH; Photos

Location: 11.4 km north from Murchison River bridge towards Billabong Roadhouse on highway, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall. Bark rough to 250 mm circ., grey-brown, smooth above, pale tan over cream. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green at first, maturing slightly glossy, green, reticulation moderately dense, with dense intersectional and island oil glands. Growing in red sand over limestone in tall open mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus obtusiflora, E. kochii ssp. horistes, E. loxophleba ssp. supralaevis, E. subangusta ssp. subangusta and E. eudesmioides. PERTH

Location: 2.7 km north from Murchison River bridge towards Billabong Roadhouse on highway, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough to 130 mm circ., dark grey, smooth above, light grey over tan. Leaves glossy, dark green, reticulation moderate, with intersectional and island oil glands. Scattered here, growing in red powdery earth in shrubland vegetation with Acacia species. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. supralaevis x E. victrix
Location: Ca. 600 m from NW Coastal Highway on track running west just to north of Murchison River, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 10 metres tall, several-stemmed. Bark rough to 1 metres, box-type, then smooth, somewhat glossy, pale creamy white. Leaves slightly glossy, slightly blue-green or olive-green. Single tree growing in side creek of Murchison River with Eucalyptus victrix. CANB, PERTH

Location: 15.9 km north from Binnu towards Billabong Roadhouse on highway, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4.5 metres tall. Bark rough to 150 mm circ., dark grey, smooth above, light grey over light grey. Leaves glossy, dark green, reticulation moderate, with dense intersectional and island oil glands. Scattered here, growing in red clay-loam in low open mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus hypochlamydea and E. loxophleba ssp. supralaevis. PERTH

Location: 6.3 km south from Andanooka Springs Road on Burma Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey-tan over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green, reticulation moderate, with dense intersectional and island oil glands. Single clump, most northerly known, growing in grey sandy loam in shrubland vegetation with Eucalyptus eudesmioides and Acacia. CANB, PERTH

Location: Tompkins Road, south of Mingenew, Western Australia.
Description: Erect-stemmed mallee 5 metres tall. Bark smooth, ribbony, light grey-tan. Leaves glossy, metalic dark green. Buds smooth, including operculum. Stamens very pale yellow. No fruits found. Clump of ca. 5 mallees growing on white sand high in landscape with Eucalyptus todtiana. CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: Mindaloo Beacon, Western Australia.
Description: Whipstick mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey-brown over cream. Leaves glossy, light green. Flowers cream. Good stand in white sand in broad depression between laterite rises with Eucalyptus todtiana. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus x crispata (E. accedens x E. arachnaea)
Location: Near Mindaloo Beacon, Western Australia.
Description: Erect-stemmed, sparse-crowned mallee 6 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth but imperfectly decorticating and crisped on lower stems. Leaves slightly glossy, pale green. Scattered mallees of this hybrid growing in gully below breakaways with Eucalyptus arachnaea subsp. arachnaea and E. accedens. CANB, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus x crispata (E. accedens x E. arachnaea)
Location: Near Mindaloo Beacon, Western Australia.
Description: Coppice growth 30 cm long from stem at 1 metre above ground level. Leaves dull, greyish, slightly glaucous. PERTH

Location: South of Eneabba on the Brand Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall, others to 3 metres. Bark rough, flaky-fibrous, grey-brown over red-brown. Leaves concolorous, + dull, blue-green, but noticably greener than E. todtiana. Flowers white, with staminodes. Reasonable stand growing on white sand plain with Eucalyptus todtiana. PERTH

Location: 2.4 km south of the Hill River bridge on the Brand Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Whipstick mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey. Leaves glossy, green, reticulation very dense, no oil glands visable. Growing as stand of 5 to 6 mallees on flat above Hill River, nearby is Corymbia calophylla, Eucalyptus todtiana, E. camaldulensis and E. wandoo subsp. pulverea. PERTH Photos

Location: Scarp Road, ca. 5 km north of E. x graniticola site, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark rough over lower half of stems, flaky, red-brown-grey, smooth above, cream. Leaves dull, blue-green. No parts glaucous. About 10 mallees here growing on side edge of steep sheet granite slope with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. CANB, PERTH

Location: 2.1 km south of Sabina Road on track, Whicher Range, Western Australia.
Description: Several-stemmed tree 12 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, thick, finely fissured, dark grey. Leaves distinctly discolorous, glossy above, dark green. A few scraggy trees here growing on gravelly pale sand on slight slope with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. CANB, PERTH

Location: Vasse Highway, south-east of Busselton, Western Australia.
Description: Tree of poor form, 8 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately fissured, grey over brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy above, dark green. Flowers cream. Population here growing on orange laterite hillside with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. AD, CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: 500 metres east up gully from below coordinates at Mt Lindesay carpark , Western Australia.
Description: Tree 12 metres tall, others up to 20 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over powdery white over pink. Leaves discolorous, glossy above, green. Population of at least 200 trees in gully of white gritty sand between granite boulders, growing with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. AD, CANB, PERTH Photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus x kalganensis (E. pachyloma x E. preissiana)
Location: Entrance to Gnowellan Homestead on Chillinup Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, but ribbony rough near base, light grey over cream. Leaves dull, blue-green, maturing somewhat green. Flowers light yellow. Single roadside mallee growing on white sand with Eucalyptus pachyloma, E. pleurocarpa, E. decipiens subsp. adesmophloia and E. phaenophylla subsp. phaenophylla. CANB, PERTH

Location: Chillinup Road, south-east of Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Erect mallee 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very ribbony, grey-tan over pale grey. Leaves thick, glossy, dark green. Common here, growing on flat of pale brown sandy loam with Eucalyptus falcata, E. pleurocarpa, E. uncinata and E. phaenophylla subsp. phaenophylla. CANB, PERTH

Location: Chillinup Road, south-east of Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and orange-tan. Leaves dull, blue-green, some with purplish tinges. Large population growing with Eucalyptus neutra, E. pleurocarpa, E. uncinata, E. conglobata subsp. perata, E. angulosa and E. thamnoides. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: Chillinup Road, south of Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Terminal-crowned tree 10 metres tall. Bark rough on trunk and larger branches, thick, hard, moderately fissured, dark grey-brown, smooth above, cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing in shallow depression in white sand over orange gravelly clay with Eucalyptus decipiens subsp. adesmophloia, E. uncinata and E. pleurocarpa. PERTH

Location: Chillinup Road, south of Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, pale grey-tan and tan. All adult parts glaucous. Leaves dull, greyish, glaucous when new.  Growing on white sand with Eucalyptus decipiens subsp. adesmophloia and E. incrassata robust. PERTH

Location: 1 km from Kambellup towards Mt Barker, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, light grey and cream, but thinly rough for 1 metre, flaky, light grey. Leaves + dull, blue-green, somewhat variable in leaf width, this being towards the broader end. Growing on grey sand over orange clay, low in landscape, with Eucalyptus wandoo subsp. wandoo, E. uncinata, E. thamnoides subsp. thamnoides and a few E. occidentalis. PERTH; Photos

Location: 1 km from Kambellup towards Mt Barker, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, slightly glossy, pale grey and orange-tan. Leaves glossy, dark green. Flowers very pale yellow. Growing on grey sand over orange clay, low in landscape, with Eucalyptus wandoo subsp. wandoo, E. uncinata, E. hebetifolia and a few E. occidentalis. CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: Mt Trio Carpark, Stirling Range Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee, recovering from fire, 2.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, mid-green. Growing on footslopes of Mt Trio in rocky grey loam with Eucalyptus talyuberlup, E. preissiana subsp. preissiana, E. marginata subsp. marginata, E. decurva and E. falcata subsp ecostata. CANB, PERTH

Location: North of Mt Trio, Stirling Range Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey over orange tan. Leaves glossy, metalic olive green. Growing on + level rise of orange gravel with Eucalyptus decurva. CANB, PERTH

Location: Chester Pass Road, Stirling Range Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark rough, but thin and flaky, light grey-brown over cream. Leaves dull, blue-green, some somewhat purplish. Growing on slight slope in gravelly orange loam with Eucalyptus wandoo subsp. wandoo, E. incrassata robust and E. pleurocarpa. PERTH

Location: Ca. 17 km north of Ongerup towards Lake Grace , Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, glossy, grey and tan. Leaves glossy, metalic olive green (but not metallic bluish like E. spathulata). Growing on saline flat with Eucalyptus celastroides subsp. virella. PERTH

Location: Oakdale Road, near Corackerup Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey over paler grey. Leaves glossy, metalic green. Flowers very pale creamy yellow. Growing on slight rise of white gravelly sand with Eucalyptus uncinata, E. phaenophylla subsp. phaenophylla and E. pleurocarpa. CANB, PERTH

Location: Southern boundary of Corackerup Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dark grey over grey and tan. Leaves thick, glossy, dark green. Growing as dense stand in minor depression, but also on low rise, with Eucalyptus annulata, E. perata, E. vegrandis subsp. vegrandis, E. calycogona subsp. calycogona and E. flocktoniae - E. neutra intergrade. CANB, PERTH Photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus eremophila x E. platypus subsp. platypus
Location: Reserve Road, east of Lake Magenta Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Small mallet 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark olive-green. Quite common here, but probable hybrid swarm between Eucalyptus platypus subsp. platypus and E. eremophila mallee, both growing here (on broad rise), also E. pileata, E. scyphocalyx, E. celastroides subsp. virella, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae and E. phaenophylla subsp. phaenophylla. CANB, PERTH

Location: Hammersley Drive, Fitzgerald River Nat. Park , Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey. Leaves glossy, green, with dense island and intersectional oil glands. Growing on white gravelly sand with Eucalyptus incrassata, E. ecostata, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae, E. uncinata, E. phaenophylla subsp. interjacens and E. pleurocarpa. CANB, PERTH

Location: Hammersley Drive, Fitzgerald River Nat. Park , Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing on white gravelly sand with Eucalyptus communalis and E. pleurocarpa. CANB, PERTH

Location: 200 metres NW over estuary from below coordinates at Quoin Head campsite, Fitzgerald River Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Spreading non-sprouter shrub, 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves held erect, glossy, green. Much seedling regeneration from fire, adult plants killed. Growing on steep N facing quartz-granite slope with Eucalyptus redunca, E. pleurocarpa, E. uncinata and E. preissiana subsp. preissiana. AD, CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: 200 metres east down gully from below coordinates, near Quoin Head, Fitzgerald River Nat. Park , Western Australia.
Description: Spreading non-sprouter, 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey-tan over cream. Leaves glossy, mid-green. Flowers slightly greenish yellow. Growing in dense stand in acute gully between boulders with Eucalyptus macquoidii and E. preissiana subsp. preissiana nearby. CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: 36.9 km north of Hopetoun towards Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall (lignotuberous). Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, dark green, dense island oil glands. Flowers red in whole population except 1 or 2 plants possible hybrid plants. Growing on rise of gravelly white loam with Eucalyptus suggrandis subsp. suggrandis, E. phaenophylla subsp. interjacens, E. scyphocalyx, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae and E. incrassata. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus proxima x E. suggrandis subsp. suggrandis
Location: 36.9 km north of Hopetoun towards Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 1.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, mid-green. A few plants of this hybrids, with pale pink to dark pink flowers, growing on rise of gravelly white loam with Eucalyptus suggrandis subsp. suggrandis, E. phaenophylla subsp. interjacens, E. allocernua, E. scyphocalyx, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae and E. incrassata. CANB, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus phaenophylla x E. suggrandis subsp. suggrandis
Location: 37.4 km north of Hopetoun towards Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, light green, moderate reticulation and scattered island and intersectional oil glands. One plant of this, growing on undulating rise with Eucalyptus suggrandis subsp. suggrandis, E. phaenophylla subsp. interjacens, E. cernua mallee red, E. scyphocalyx, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae and E. uncinata. CANB, PERTH

Location: North of Ravensthorpe on road to Lake King, Western Australia.
Description: Large mallets 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Flowers light yellow on all plants here. Growing on rise of grey rocky and red clayey loam with Eucalyptus extensa, E. conglobata subsp. perata and E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: Near Mt Short, north of Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall. Some rough basal bark, otherwise smooth, light grey and tan. Leaves glossy, green, scattered intersectional oil glands. Leaves, buds and fruits coarse. Growing on high broad rise of laterite with Eucalyptus incrassata and E. pleurocarpa. CANB, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus X bennettiae (E. lehmannii x E. sporadica)
Location: 300 metres west down steep slope from below coordinates; Near Mt Desmond, S of Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, light green. Single plant growing in gully in dense Dryandra-Melaleuca scrub with Eucalyptus falcata subsp. falcata, E. sporadica, E. preissiana subsp. preissiana, E. incrassata and E. lehmannii subsp. modifolia. PERTH Photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus lehmannii subsp. parallela x E. megacornuta
Location: 300 metres west down steep slope from below coordinates; Near Mt Desmond, S of Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Small tree 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dark grey-brown. Leaves glossy, green. Single plant growing in gully with Eucalyptus falcata subsp. ecostata, E. sporadica, E. preissiana subsp. preissiana, E. incrassata and E. lehmannii subsp. modifolia. CANB, PERTH

Location: East side of Mt Desmond, south of Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and light grey over orangish. Leaves glossy, green. Growing as dense stand on laterite ridge with Eucalyptus falcata subsp. ecostata, E. clivicola and E. lehmannii subsp. modifolia. PERTH Photos

Location: Near Bandalup Hill, east of Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 4 metres tall, mature mallets to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, light grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark olive-green, reticulation moderately dense with sparse intersectional oil glands. New growth conspicuously red-purple over whole population. Flowers cream. Population covering ca. 10 ha, growing on white powdery magnesium NE facing slope with Eucalyptus indurata and E. brachycalyx. AD, CANB, NSW, PERTH Photos

Location: Near Bandalup Hill, east of Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, light grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark olive-green, reticulation moderately dense with sparse intersectional oil glands. New growth conspicuously red-purple over whole population. Flowers cream. Population covering ca. 10 ha, growing on white powdery magnesium NE facing slope with Eucalyptus indurata and E. brachycalyx, with low Melaleuca-dominated understorey. AD, CANB, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus x stoaptera (E. stoatei x E. tetraptera)
Location: 0.2 km west of Mason Bay Road on Jerdicuttup North Road, Western Australia.
Description: Erect mallee 4 metres tall. Leaves glossy, green, very rigid. Flowers apricot-coloured. About six plants here, growing on sandplain with Eucalyptus stoatei, E. pleurocarpa, E. kessellii subsp. eugnosta and E. tetraptera. CANB, PERTH Photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus x bennettiae (E. lehmannii x E. sporadica or E. astringens)
Location: 6.3 km down track from Hopetoun to Ravensthorpe road opposite Jerdicuttup Road junction, Western Australia.

Location: 7.3 km down track from Hopetoun to Ravensthorpe road opposite Jerdicuttup Road junction, Western Australia.

Growing in dense stand on broad rise with Eucalyptus clivicola, E. cernua mallee (yellow and red flowers) and E. redunca - E. densa subsp. improcera intergrade. CANB, PERTH

Location: East of the Ravensthorpe to Hopetoun road near Kundip, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dark olive-grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing in dense stand on steep banks of deep gully with Eucalyptus clivicola. PERTH

Location: 7.2 km from South Coast Highway on Farrells Road to Quaggi Beach, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey over light grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Flowers very light creamy-yellow. Location: 7.2 km from South Coast Highway on Farrells Road to Quaggi Beach, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey and orange-tan. Leaves glossy, somewhat blue-green at first, maturing dark olive green. Growing on limestone rise with Eucalyptus uncinata  and E. semiglobosa. CANB, PERTH

Location: Cascades Road, east of Cascades, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, glossy, dark grey and light olive green. Leaves glossy, very dark green. Leaf shape somewhat variable here. Growing in broad depession with Eucalyptus forrestiana, E. crassa, E. depauperata and E. flocktoniae. PERTH

Location: Neds Corner Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, orange tan over light grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Flowers dull red, others here yellow. Growing orange-white sand on plain with Eucalyptus forrestiana, E. conglobata and E. flocktoniae. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: Neds Corner Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 4 metres tall, others to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale silvery grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Location: 0.3 km east from Esperance to Norseman road on Circle Valley Road, Western Australia.

Location: Corner of Punkett Road and Carranya Road, Western Australia.

Location: Western slope of Mt Burdett, Western Australia.
Description: Erect-stemmed mallee 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale pinkish grey over pale grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing on foot of Mt Burdett below sheet granite slope with Eucalyptus tetraptera, E. pleurocarpa and E. micranthera. CANB, PERTH

Location: South-west of Mt Ney on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.
Description: Dense, spreading mallee 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale olive-green. Leaves becomming glossy, very dark olive green. Growing in dense stand on edge of saline flat with Eucalyptus halophila and E. leptocalyx. CANB, PERTH

Location: South-west of Mt Ney on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 6 metres tall, many branched near ground level. Bark smooth throughout, + glossy, light olive grey over yellow-orange. Leaves glossy, distinctly blue-green. Location: 6.2 km north of Koa Road on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.

Locally frequent, growing in orange loam with limestone in tall mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus dielsii, E. conglobata, E. leptocalyx, E. quadrans and E. uncinata ssp. dendra. CANB, PERTH

Location: 8.1 km north of Koa Road on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.

PERTH

Location: Western base of Mt Ney, Western Australia.

Location: 13.7 km north of Logans Road on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.

Scattered here, growing in grey sandy loam in mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus dielsii, E. conglobata, E. scyphocalyx, E. kessellii ssp. kessellii, E. extensa, E. platycorys, E. flocktoniae ssp. hebes, E. tumida and E. uncinata. CANB, PERTH

Location: 13.7 km north of Logans Road on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall, regrowth from past fire. Leaves glossy, blue-green. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: 25.4 km north of Mt Ney access track junction with Mt Ney Road on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.

Location: 25.4 km north of Mt Ney access track junction with Mt Ney Road on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.

CANB, PERTH

Location: 25.4 km north of Mt Ney access track junction with Mt Ney Road on Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.

CANB, PERTH

Location: 21.0 km from Parmango Road on Buraminya track to Mt Ney Road, Western Australia.

Location: 6.1 km from Zanthus to Balladonia track near Spy Hill on the Fraser Range Station track, Western Australia.

Location: 21.1 km from Zanthus to Balladonia track near Spy Hill on the Fraser Range Station track, Western Australia.
