Location: Corner Maisey Rd & Quelagetting West Rd, N of Meckering, Western Australia.
Description: Robust mallee to 7 m tall. Bark smooth throughout to loosely rough for up to 2 m, ribbony, pale grey over pinkish tan. Leaves dull, green. Much juvenile/intermediate leaves in canopy. About 100 plants in pure stand on broad ridge of white sand. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Twenty Six Gate Rd, SW of Wyalkatchem, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 m tall. Bark rough for 2 m, hard-fibrous; smooth above. Leaves glossy, green; slightly duller on new growth. On pale brown loam on very slightly undulating topography with Eucalyptus salubris, E. erythronema (erythronema - marginata intergrade), E. subangusta subsp. subangusta, E. moderata and E. celastroides subsp. virella. CANB, PERTH

Location: Borgward Rd, SW of Wyalkatchem, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 m tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout, very ribbony and accumulating. Leaves thick, glossy, green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus subangusta subsp. subangusta on broad rise of white gravely sand. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: Bencubbin - Kununoppin Rd, N of Kununoppin, Western Australia.
Description: mallee to 7m tall. Bark smooth throughout, very ribbony, pale grey over pale orange-tan. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets, buds and immature fruits waxy. Common here on level topography in brown loam in mixed mallee-woodland with Eucalyptus salmonophloia and E. loxophleba subsp. lissophloia. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Sutton Rd, NE of Kununoppin, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 m tall. Bark rough for up to 2 m. Leaves slightly glossy, green. No wax present. Common here where co-dominant with Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. lissophloia on pale sand near granite outcrops. CANB, PERTH

Location: Billyacatting Hill, walk track to summit, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout. Leaves dull, dark green. About eight mallees on granite between high domes. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Billyacatting Hill, 100 m S of car park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 m tall. Bark amorphic and thick at base, minniritchi-type above. Leaves dull, blue-green About 15 plants on lower granite outcrop. Plants very drought stressed. PERTH + seed + photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus kochii subsp. plenissima x E. salmonophloia
Location: Near corner Jolly Rd & Lee Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 13 m tall. Bark rough for 1.8 m, moderately-fissured; smooth above, grey over tan. Leaves slightly glossy, green. Single tree growing with Eucalyptus kochii subsp. plenissima, E. loxophleba subsp. lissophloia and E. sheathiana, with E. salmonophloia growing about 200 m away. CANB, PERTH

Location: Warralakin Rd, just N of Stoneman Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree to 7 m tall. Bark rough for 2 to 3 m, thick, moderately-fissured, hard-fibrous, grey; smooth above, grey over coppery-tan. Leaves glossy, green. On reddish loam with Eucalyptus longicornis, E. salubris and E. yilgarnensis. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Mt Rankine South, track to summit on E side, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 16.8 m Spread av. - 11.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 1.99 m. On stony red clay in open woodland of Eucalyptus longicornis, E. salubris, E. prolixa and E. corrugata. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: Gobetti Rd, SE of Moorine Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 m tall. Bark ribbony rough over stems, pale grey-tan over cream. Leaves very glossy, green, reticulation moderate with scattered oil glands. Common here on pale yellow sand with Eucalyptus leptopoda, E. platycorys, E. burracoppinensis and E. capillosa nearby. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Gobetti Rd, SE of Moorine Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Regrowth to 1 m tall, from lignotuber, cleared fence line. Leaves discolorous, slightly glossy, dark green. Common here on pale yellow sand with Eucalyptus leptopoda, E. platycorys, E. burracoppinensis and E. capillosa nearby. CANB, PERTH

Location: Corner Nicholson Rd & Posa Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, very ribbony and accumulating, pale grey over pale tan. Leaves glossy, green, scattered oil glands. Common here on pale yellow sand with Eucalyptus leptopoda. Also E. horistes 50 m away just downslope (no intergrades noted). CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Frog Rock, base of gully on E side, Western Australia.
Description: Robust mallee to 9 metres tall. Bark rough on lower stems. leaves glossy, dark green. Fruits particularly big on this individual. Common here at eastern base of granite rock with Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. lissophloia. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Skeleton Rocks, base on SW side, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark rough for about 1 m, coarsely shaggy and ribbony; smooth above, coppery-red and tan. Scattered in dense heath at base of granite dome with Eucalyptus petraea. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Skeleton Rocks, base on SW side, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 m tall, others to 8 m.  Dominant as emergent and within dense heathy scrub at base of granite dome with some Eucalyptus aspratilis and E. capillosa. PERTH + photos

Location: Dunbar Rd, SE of Marvel Lock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 10 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, pale grey over orange-tan. Leaves highly glossy, dark green, reticulation dense and with dense oil glands. Common here in mallet woodland on red clay-loam over limestone with Eucalyptus salubris, E. salmonophloia, E. longicornis and E. prolixa. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Forestania Rd, N of Spilt Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey over tan. Leaves glossy, blue-green maturing green, reticulation sparse with numerous island oil glands. Morphology variable here. On slightly undulating pale brown gravely sand on slight rise with Eucalyptus rigidula, E. platycorys, E. aff. incrassata, E. burracoppinensis, E. sheathiana and E. tenera. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Forestania Rd, N of Spilt Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark rough for < 1 m; smooth above. Leaves glossy, blue-green. Flowers light yellow (but only one flower seen). Morphology variable here. On slightly undulating pale brown gravely sand on slight rise with Eucalyptus rigidula, E. platycorys, E. aff. incrassata, E. burracoppinensis, E. sheathiana and E. tenera. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Forestania Rd, N of Spilt Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark rough for < 0.5 m; smooth above. Leaves glossy, more or less green. Morphology variable here. On slightly undulating pale brown gravely sand on slight rise with Eucalyptus rigidula, E. platycorys, E. aff. incrassata, E. burracoppinensis, E. sheathiana and E. tenera. CANB, PERTH

Location: Forestania Rd, N of Spilt Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark rough for 1 m, ribbony and accumulated; smooth and ribbony above. Leaves glossy, dark green; new growth very slightly bluish. A few plants only here, on slightly undulating pale brown gravely sand on slight rise with Eucalyptus rigidula, E. platycorys, E. aff. sporadica, E. burracoppinensis, E. sheathiana and E. tenera. (Also, 1 plant seen of this x E. platycorys). CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Carstairs Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 8 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey over orange-tan. leaves glossy, blue-green at first, maturing green. On lateritic slope with Eucalyptus tenera, E. phenax subsp. phenax and E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae. CANB, PERTH

Location: Stennetts Lake Rd, SE of Lake King, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 6 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over tan-coppery. Leaves consistently small and narrow, glossy, maturing green. Common here in mallet woodland in broad depression in whitish clay-loam with Eucalyptus urna and E. salubris. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Norseman - Lake King Rd, corner Frank Hahn National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over coppery. Branchlets and fruits strongly waxy and white. Leaves glossy, metallic blue-green. Features finer than typical E. incerata. Common here on white clay-loam with Eucalyptus pileata and E. sheathiana. PERTH

Location: Norseman - Lake King Rd, corner Frank Hahn National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Crown fine. Leaves glossy and green. Scattered here on white clay-loam with Eucalyptus incerata and E. sheathiana. CANB, PERTH

Location: Southern end of Bremer Range track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over very pale grey. Leaves glossy, green. Dominant here on slopes of lateritic hill, as emergent in low healthy vegetation with Eucalyptus tenera. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Southern end of Bremer Range track, Western Australia.
Description: Juvenile regrowth from lower stems. Juvenile leaves dull, grey-green, (narrow), more or less non-waxy. Dominant here on slopes of lateritic hill, as emergent in low healthy vegetation with Eucalyptus tenera. CANB, PERTH

Location: Southern end of Bremer Range track, claypan edge, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, pale grey and cream over pale orange. Leaves glossy, dark green. Common here on low dunes of white sand on south side of claypan with Eucalyptus melanoxylon and some E. salmonophloia. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Southern foot of Peak Charles, Western Australia.
Description: Thin-stemmed mallee to 5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, dark green to purplish. Crowns collectively distinctly purplish, but variable between individuals. Dominant at southern and western base of massive granite in dense tall heath with Eucalyptus sporadica. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Griggs Rd, Lort River crossing, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 6 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, silvery-grey over orange. Leaves glossy, metallic blue-green. Crown green. Morphology not variable. Dominant here in sandy creek bed with some Eucalyptus densa subsp. densa. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Corner Esperance - Norseman Rd & Wison Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over tan. Leaves glossy, green. A few mallees in roadside vegetation with Eucalyptus leptocalyx, E. kessellii subsp. eugnosta, E. occidentalis and E. uncinata subsp. 'dendra'. CANB, PERTH

Location: Scadden Rd, NW of Wittnoom Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Straggly mallee to 2 m tall. Flowers pink-red. Adult leaves measured to 260 mm long. About six plants in mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus incrassata, E. micranthera, E. pleurocarpa and E. kessellii subsp. eugnosta. CANB, PERTH

Location: 150 m NE of corner Backmans Rd & Scadden Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 10 m tall. Bark rough and ribbony for 1 to 2 m, or smooth throughout, pale grey over pink-tan. Leaves maturing glossy and green. On white sand with Banksia and Eucalyptus tetragona; E. incrassata nearby. CANB, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus kessellii subsp. eugnosta x E. obesa
Location: 150 m NE of corner Backmans Rd & Scadden Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 8 m tall. Single plant on white sand in pure stand of Eucalyptus obesa. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus kessellii subsp. eugnosta x E. semiglobosa (=E. balanopelex)
Location: Coolinup Rd, 0.5 km from Fisheries Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing glossy and green. Variable leaf width, fruit size and bud shape, size and ornamentation. About 10 to 20 plants in disturbed gravel pit area with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa, E. occidentalis, E. cooperiana and E. uncinata. Eucalyptus kessellii subsp. eugnosta seen a few km to N on Scadden Rd. PERTH

Location: Coolinup Rd, 0.5 km from Fisheries Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing glossy and green. Variable leaf width, fruit size and bud shape, size and ornamentation. Plants variable in morphology, this plant more like E. semiglobosa. About 10 to 20 plants in disturbed gravel pit area with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa, E. occidentalis, E. cooperiana and E. uncinata. Eucalyptus kessellii subsp. eugnosta seen a few km to N on Scadden Rd. PERTH

Location: 560 m SW of Thomas Fishery campsite, Cape Arid, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee 1 metre tall, reduced in size by coastal exposure and frequent fires. leaves variable in size. About 100 plants here, below lateritic breakaway on quartz gravely sand with some Eucalyptus extrica. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: 560 m SW of Thomas Fishery campsite, Cape Arid, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee 1 m tall, reduced in size by coastal exposure and frequent fires. leaves variable in size. About 100 plants, below lateritic breakaway on quartz gravely sand with some Eucalyptus extrica. PERTH

Location: 560 m SW of Thomas Fishery campsite, Cape Arid, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee 1 m tall, reduced in size by coastal exposure and frequent fires. leaves variable in size. About 100 plants, below lateritic breakaway on quartz gravely sand with some Eucalyptus extrica. Largest leaf found in population. PERTH (leaf only)

Location: Rose Beach Rd (extension of Murray Rd), Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. Scattered clumps but locally dominant, on high sand dunes over limestone in low dense shrubland with some Eucalyptus uncinata and DN 5491 nearby. PERTH

Location: Rose Beach Rd (extension of Murray Rd), Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Leaves glossy, very slightly blue-green. Scattered on high sand dunes over limestone in low dense shrubland with Eucalyptus uncinata and E. incrassata. PERTH

Location: Bluff S of Lake Quallilup, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee < 0.5 m tall. Hidden and scattered in very low and dense shrubland on high limestone bluff; Eucalyptus incrassata and E. uncinata nearby. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Headland between Barker Inlet & Shelly Beach, Western Australia.
Description: Non-lignotuberous shrub (marlock) <0.5 m to 2 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Dominant here on headland only, in dense thickets in low shrubland on almost pure limestone. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Track to Shelly Beach, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, greyish. Leaves glossy, dark green. Common here on undulating limestone with Eucalyptus conglobata (conglobata - perata intergrade) and E. uncinata; E. occidentalis just downslope. CANB, PERTH

Location: South Coast Highway, E of Mungilup River, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale orange-tan. leaves glossy, dark green. On slope of broad valley with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa and E. uncinata. Most easterly seen of this taxon. CANB, PERTH

Location: Elverdton Rd, near Mt Desmond, SE of Raventhorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey and tan. Leaves glossy, dark green. Common on lateritic hills in mallee with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa, E. preissiana subsp. preissiana and E. incrassata. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Desmond track, SE of Raventhorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee ca. 1 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves variable in width and colour, this more like densa, dull, blue-green. Scattered here on rise of white gravely sand over clay with Eucalyptus astringens subsp. redacta, E. pleurocarpa, E. incrassata, E. uncinata, E. sporadica, E. phaenophylla and E. falcata var. ecostata. CANB, PERTH

Location: Floater Rd, Raventhorpe Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, light green, reticulation dense with scattered oil glands only. Common here on reddish lateritic clay-loam with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa, E. incrassata, E. falcata var. ecostata and E. phaenophylla. PERTH

Location: King Rd, Raventhorpe Range, Western Australia.
Description: Regrowth to 0.6 m tall from lignotuber of burnt mallees. Leaves slightly waxy, dull, greyish. CANB, PERTH

Location: Near summit of Mount Short, Raventhorpe Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 1.5 m tall. Crown sparse and with much intermediate leaves due to coppice and poor health. Scattered here on lateritic slope with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa and E. falcata var. ecostata. Also, E. clivicola and E. lehmannii subsp. parallela around summit. PERTH

Location: S boundary Overshot Hill Nature Reserve, Raventhorpe Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3.5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, more or less ribbony, grey over pale grey. Leaves thick (firm), glossy, light green, reticulation moderate with dense, large island oil glands. Leaves concolorous but appearing hypostomatic and slightly different sheen on each side. Scattered here on lateritic rise in dense mallee with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa and E. falcata var. ecostata. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: Thomas Rd, 100 m S of Aerodrome Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, glossy, pale grey-tan. Leaves glossy, green. Scattered in mallee scrub with Eucalyptus suggrandis subsp. suggrandis, E. densa subsp. improcera, E. conglobata subsp. perata, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae and E. calycogona subsp. calycogona. PERTH

Location: Mallee Rd, N of Reserve Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over tan to pale orange-tan. Leaves glossy, green. Dominant here in mallee shrubland in depression of white sand with Eucalyptus dissimulata, E. blanda and a few E. sporadica. AD, CANB, NSW, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Mallee Rd, N of Reserve Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Coppice from lignotuber on graded roadside. Leaves more or less concolorous, dull, blue-grey, waxy. Stems more or less terete, minutely warty. Dominant here in mallee shrubland in depression of white sand with Eucalyptus dissimulata, E. scyphocalyx and a few E. sporadica. CANB, PERTH

Location: Mallee Rd, N of Reserve Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Coppice from lignotuber on graded roadside. Leaves more or less concolorous, dull, blue-grey, waxy. Stems more or less terete, minutely warty. Dominant here in mallee shrubland in depression of white sand with Eucalyptus dissimulata, E. scyphocalyx and a few E. sporadica. CANB, PERTH

Location: Mallee Rd, N of Reserve Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, dark green. Scattered here in mallee shrubland in depression of white sand with Eucalyptus 'lunata', E. scyphocalyx and a few E. sporadica. PERTH

Location: Mallee Rd, N of Reserve Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, dark olive-green. Common here in mallee shrubland in depression of white sand with Eucalyptus 'lunata', E. dissimulata and a few E. sporadica. PERTH

Location: E edge 'Moon Lagoon', W of Reserve Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 m tall. Bark mostly smooth , more or less ribbony, grey over pale grey and cream. Leaves glossy, green. Flowers white. On grey clay flat adjacent to lunette in open mallee in pure stand. CANB, PERTH

Location: W of Reserve Rd on 'Moon Lagoon' track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 m tall. Bark ribbony rough for 1 m, otherwise smooth, very ribbony and accumulating, grey over tan. Leaves glossy, green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus 'lunata' on white sandplain near salt lakes in open mallee. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: W of Reserve Rd on 'Moon Lagoon' track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over tan. Leaves glossy, green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus aff. captiosa on white sandplain near salt lakes in open mallee. CANB, PERTH

Location: O'Neills Rd, Fitzgerald River crossing, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Scattered here on flat of white sand adjacent to river with Eucalyptus occidentalis nearby. CANB, PERTH

Location: Fitzgerald River track, Fitzgerald River National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 10 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing glossy and dark green. Common in dense mallet forest with Eucalyptus occidentalis, E. astringens subsp. redacta and E. platypus subsp. platypus (and E. occidentalis - E. platypus hybrids). PERTH

Location: Fitzgerald River track, Fitzgerald River National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4.5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over orange-tan. Leaves glossy, green. (Juvenile leaves here ovate to orbicular and greyish). Scattered on pale grey loam on flat below breakaway with Eucalyptus ecostata, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae and E. conglobata subsp. perata. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Fitzgerald River track, Fitzgerald River National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Single-stems and no lignotubers seen, growing is vegetation 5+ years since fire. About 12 to 18 plants here, in mallee shrubland on slope of loam over sandstone with Eucalyptus redunca, E. ecostata, E. uncinata, E. incrassata, E. pleurocarpa and E. lehmannii subsp. parallela. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Fitzgerald River track, Fitzgerald River National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 m tall. Bark rough at base then smooth above. Leaves variable in size, some leaves largish and thick like E. sp. Mount Short (this specimen coarsest). In mallee shrubland on slope of loam over sandstone with Eucalyptus redunca, E. falcata var. ecostata, E. brandiana, E. incrassata, E. pleurocarpa and E. lehmannii subsp. parallela. PERTH

Location: Fitzgerald River track, Fitzgerald River National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, greyish. leaves glossy, dark green. In mallee shrubland on slope of loam over sandstone with Eucalyptus redunca, E. uncinata, E. brandiana, E. incrassata, E. pleurocarpa and E. lehmannii subsp. parallela. CANB, PERTH

Location: Greening Australia's Nawainup property, Western Australia.
Description: In open mallet stand with Eucalyptus astringens subsp. redacta, E. melanophitra, E. platypus subsp. platypus, E. flocktoniae subsp. flocktoniae, E. conglobata subsp. perata, E. vegrandis subsp. vegrandis and E. reduncta - E. pluricaulis subsp. porphyrea intergrades. Photo specimen only.

Location: Moitch Creek, north of Borden - Bremer Bay Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, green. About 30 individual mallees growing on river flat in grey loam with Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. loxophleba just above on slightly higher ground. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Millars Point camping area, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 10 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, glossy, pale grey over orange-tan. In low open forest with Eucalyptus utilis, E. astringens subsp. redacta and E. praetermissa. Photo specimen only.

Location: Paperbark Rd at Pallinup River, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 8 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey. Leaves dull, bluish-green. Appears to be broader-leaved coastal form of Eucalyptus melanophitra. In dense thickets on north bank of river with E. occidentalis. PERTH

Location: Paperbark Rd, SE of Boxwood Hill, Western Australia.
Description: Dense mallee <2 m tall. Common here on lateritic rise in open mallee shrubland with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa, E. uncinata and E. decipiens subsp. adesmophloia. Photo specimen only.

Location: Green Range, South Coast Highway, Hassell National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. On slight slope in orange lateritic soil with Eucalyptus cuspidata, E. preissiana subsp. preissiana and E. decipiens subsp. adesmophloia. PERTH

Location: Boulder Hill, S of Manypeaks, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling dense 'mallee' to 2 m tall. Leaves more or less dull, light green to dark green. Old dead flowers red to orange. About 50+ clumps on south facing slope in white peaty sand between granite boulders with some Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. Corymbia calophylla nearby but not mixed in stand. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Palmdale Rd, just S of Johnson Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves more or less glossy, green. In mallee shrubland with Eucalyptus preissiana subsp. preissiana, E. cuspidata and E. staeri. PERTH

Location: Woojenilup Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 7 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and pale grey over orange-tan. leaves glossy and dark green. On broad lateritic rise with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa, E. cuspidata and E. marginata subsp. marginata. CANB, PERTH

Location: "King Jarrah", Perup Rd, Manjimup, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 39.0 m Spread av. - 17.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 7.98 m. In forest co-dominant with Corymbia calophylla. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: "Diamond Tree", South-Western Highway between Manjimup & Pemberton, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 47.5 m (top of tree), 53.5 m (top of tower) Spread av. - 19.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 6.81 m. In tall forest with some Corymbia calophylla. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: "Big Karri", Big Brook State Forest off Channybearup Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 72.0 m Spread av. - 21.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 9.75 m. In pure karri forest. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: "Gloucester Tree", Pemberton, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 57.5 m Spread av. - 18.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 7.21 m. In pure karri forest. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: 'Redlands', off Vasse Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 34.0 m Spread av. - 20.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 6.00 m. Bark rough throughout, moderately-deeply fissured. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. In Eucalyptus diversicolor forest on low broad hill in partially cleared country. PERTH + National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: Warren National Park, Heartbreak trail near Old Vasse Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 62.0 m Spread av. - 22.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 7.99 m. In karri forest with some Corymbia calophylla. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: Warren National Park, Heartbreak trail near Old Vasse Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 52.0 m Spread av. - 22.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 6.11 m. In forest dominated by Eucalyptus diversicolor. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: "Bicentennial Tree", Warren National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 69.5 m (to top of tower) Spread av. - 18.0 m Circ 1.4 m - 5.50 m. In pure karri forest. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: Larsen Rd, SW of Nannup, Western Australia.
Description: Several-stemmed tree of poor form. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over pale creamy-yellow. Leaves dull, blue-green. No fruits found. A few plants only, in poor health, on slight north-west slope in open forest of Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. CANB, PERTH

Location: Crouch Rd, W of Nannup, Western Australia.
Description: Several-stemmed tree of poor form, to 6 m tall. Bark rough throughout, hard-fibrous and moderately to finely fissured, grey. Leaves distinctly discolorous, dull and dark green above. Common just here, on moderate easterly slope of laterite in low open forest of Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. PERTH

Location: 300 m N of Meelup hill car park, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee-like tree to 7 m tall, with numerous stems. Bark smooth throughout, pinkish-grey over white. Leaves strongly discolorous, very slightly glossy and dark green above. Three clumps here, each ca. 15 m in diameter, on slight northerly slope in low open woodland of Corymbia calophylla and some Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus x phylacis (E. decipiens x E. virginea)
Location: Meelup hill car park, Meelup Beach Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee-like trees to 5 m tall. Bark rough on older stems; smooth on regrowth since last fire. Leaves moderately discolorous, slightly glossy and dark green above. Several clumps on a rise over a 20 m diameter area with Corymbia calophylla and some Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. PERTH

Location: Cape Naturaliste Rd, Eagle Bay, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 14 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately-finely fissured and somewhat tessellated (like tuart bark), grey. Leaves slightly glossy, very slightly blue-green. On creek in gully with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus cornuta. PERTH + seed

Location: York - Williams Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 14 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale salmon-cream. Co-dominant in woodland with Eucalyptus wandoo subsp. wandoo. Photo specimen only

Location: Boyagin Rock Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, greyish over orange-tan. leaves slightly glossy, blue-green maturing dark green. A few clumps in lateritic loam with Corymbia calophylla, Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata and E. drummondii subsp. 'drummondii'. CANB, PERTH

Location: Frogmouth Rd, Boyagin Rock Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 m tall; thin-stemmed. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey and pale grey over orange-tan. leaves dull, grey-green. Branchlets strongly waxy. Common here on gravely sand and laterite on rise with Corymbia calophylla, Eucalyptus accedens and E. wandoo subsp. wandoo. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Rock 500 m to SSW of Boyagin Rock, Boyagin Rock Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout. Leaves dull, grey-green. Branchlets, buds and fruits waxy. About 100 mallees on north-west facing granite domes with Corymbia calophylla, Eucalyptus drummondii subsp. 'drummondii' and E. wandoo subsp. wandoo just downslope off rock. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: N of Pinpin Rd on farm, Berrmullah Plain, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4.5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over orange. leaves dull, slightly blue-green at first, maturing glossy and dark green. About ten mallees here in fenced uncleared patch in vast paddock on plain of grey clay. Another slightly larger population of same (about 15 mallees) about 600 m to SE of here. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: N of Pinpin Rd on farm, Berrmullah Plain, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4.5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over orange. leaves dull, slightly blue-green at first, maturing glossy and dark green. Flowers pale creamy yellow. About ten mallees here in fenced uncleared patch in vast paddock on plain of grey clay. Another slightly larger population of same (about 15 mallees) about 600 m to SE of here. CANB, PERTH

Location: Pinpin Rd, Berrmullah Plain, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 8 m tall. Bark rough for up to 3 m, somewhat loose and flaky, grey over tan; smooth  and stripy above. Leaves glossy, light green. Buds up to 13 per umble. About 14 mallees here on very low limestone rise on plain, in mostly cleared country. CANB, PERTH

Location: Nine Mile Swamp Rd, Berrmullah Plain, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 9 m tall. Bark rough to moderately-small branches. Two trees only, on reddish loam in cleared paddock with Corymbia calophylla dominant. PERTH

Location: Calcarra West Rd, S of Calingiri, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey over orange-tan. Leaves dull and blue-green at first, maturing glossy and dark green. A few mallees on broad lateritic rise with Eucalyptus wandoo nearby. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Farm off Big Springs Rd, E of Calingiri, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 17.5 m Spread av. - 19.5 m Circ 1.4 m - 6.52 m. Partially cleared woodland of this species. National Register of Big Trees record + photo

Location: Mortlock River crossing on Whitfield Rd, SW of Wongan Hills, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 m tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout, glossy, grey over coppery. Leaves maturing glossy and dark green. About six mallees in flat sandy depression in low open shrubland. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Moonijin West Rd, SE of Wongan Hills, Western Australia.
Description: Spreading mallee 7 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout. Fruit size variable, but generally mid-range. A few large mallees on SE side of granite dome, surrounded by Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. loxophleba. PERTH + seed

Location: Corner Nugadong West Rd & Gunyidi - Wubin Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 10 m tall. Bark rough for 3 to 3 m, coarsely flaky-fibrous, thick, dark grey; smooth above, glossy, grey over coppery. Leaves glossy, dark green. Pure stand forming open woodland on saline flat. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Mason Rd, W of Wubin, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over orange-tan. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. Forming a hybrid swarm here with Eucalyptus arachnaea; on lateritic rise. Also here is E. kochii subsp. kochii and E. erythronema var. marginata. PERTH + seed

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus arachnaea x E. subangusta subsp. subangusta
Location: Mason Rd, W of Wubin, Western Australia.
Description: Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. Common mallees at D.Nicolle 5552 site; apparently part of a hybrid swarm. PERTH

Location: Thomas Rd, W of Wubin, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout, ribbony and accumulated at base, grey over tan. Leaves glossy, green, with very few oil glands. On gravely laterite and sand on broad rise. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Midlands Rd, S of Coorow, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 m tall. Bark rough for 1 m. Common here on undulating low sand dunes near salt lakes with Eucalyptus brachycorys. Photo specimen only.

Location: Caron Rd, NE of Carnamah, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, some multi-stemmed, to 9 m tall; some with obvious lignotubers. Bark rough up to 3 m. Leaves very glossy, maturing dark green. In partially cleared field on stony lateritic low hill with some Eucalyptus salmonophloia. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: West Yarra Rd, S of Three Springs, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, some multi-stemmed, to 11 m tall. Bark rough for half tree height, moderately-finely fissured, grey; smooth above, grey over tan. Leaves very glossy, light green, with dense oil glands. Common on flats adjacent to salt lake with some Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. loxophleba and E. salmonophloia. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: SE of Mt Horner on farm, NE of Dongarra, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves maturing glossy and dark green. A few clumps on slope of south-facing lateritic breakaway with Eucalyptus obtusiflora. CANB, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus gittinsii subsp. gittinsii - subsp. illucida intergrade
Location: SE of Mt Horner on farm, NE of Dongarra, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 m tall. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing slightly glossy and dark green. A few mallees, leaves variable between them, as emergents in low shrubland on grey sand over laterite with Eucalyptus accedens and E. horistes. PERTH

Location: SE of Mt Horner on farm, NE of Dongarra, Western Australia.
Description: Emergent erect-stemmed mallee 8 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy and green. Single clump very high in landscape on very broad rise, emergent over low shrubland. Photo specimen only.

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus x leprophloia (E. accedens x E. zopherophloia)
Location: Tabletop, ESE of Mt Horner on farm, NE of Dongarra, Western Australia.
Description: Several-stemmed tree 4 m tall, Bark rough for 2 metres, dark grey; smooth above, yellow-coppery. Leaves glossy, dark green. Branchlets slightly waxy. Single large clump (one genet?) at top of lateritic breakaway, with Eucalyptus arachnaea, E. accedens, E. ebbanoensis ssp. photina, E. gittinsii ssp. illucida and E. obtusiflora nearby on breakaway. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Tabletop, ESE of Mt Horner on farm, NE of Dongarra, Western Australia.
Description: Emergent mallee 3 m tall. Leaves glossy and green, lenticels conspicuous. No mature flower buds or fruits found here. Single clump in low shrubland on plateau of laterite with some white sand. PERTH + photos

Location: Tabletop, ESE of Mt Horner on farm, NE of Dongarra, Western Australia.
Description: Several-stemmed tree-mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream. Leaves more or less dull, blue-green. A few clumps of this here, on lateritic breakaway with Eucalyptus arachnaea and E. subangusta ssp. subangusta emergent. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Tabletop, E of Mt Horner on farm, NE of Dongarra, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 8 m tall. Bark rough for 2 to 4 metres. Leaves dull, green. Large clump (20+ stems over 20 metres diameter) in sandy soil in cleared paddock, 100 metres below lateritic breakaway. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Burma Rd, SE of Geraldton, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee 4 m tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. Coppice growth waxy and bluish. A few mallees of this here in dense low Banksia shrubland. PERTH

Location: Burma Rd, SE of Geraldton, Western Australia.
Description: Spreading mallee 7 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey over tan. Leaves slightly glossy, blue-green maturing dark green. A few large clumps on gravely lateritic sand on slight slope, emergent in Banksia shrubland. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Port Gregory Rd, E of Port Gregory, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee to 6 m tall. Bark rough over most of stems. Crown composed mostly of adult leaves with some juvenile and intermediate leaves present. Buds and fruits variable in size, this collection near coarsest range. At base of limestone escarpment with Eucalyptus dolichocera, and with E. obtusiflora and E. oraria nearby. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Murchison House Station, N side of Murchison River, Western Australia.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very pale grey over powdery white. Leaves dull, blue-green. On sandy alluvial soil below sandstone ridge with Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. arida. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Murchison House Station, NW of homestead, Western Australia.
Description: Spreading mallee to 4 m tall. Bark rough on lower half of stems. Dense clumps on red sand with outcropping limestone, with Eucalyptus oraria, E. dolichocera and E. obtusiflora. Photo specimen only

Location: N of Nuddawallathara Soak, Murchison House Station, Western Australia.
Description: Robust but poorly-formed tree, many multi-stemmed and mallee-like, to 7 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Large stand on limestone ridge, in pure stand with Eucalyptus dolichocera nearby on somewhat softer sites. Nuytsia floribunda also growing here. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Lake Culcurdoo, Murchison House Station, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and pale grey over cream. Crowns of trees blue-green. Leaves dull and blue-green at first, maturing glossy and green. Large stand in depression between sandplains and limestone rises. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Near West Koorie Dam, Murchison House Station, Western Australia.
Description: Several-stemmed tree 4 m tall. Bark rough for 2 metres, dark grey; smooth above, yellow-coppery. Leaves glossy, dark green. Branchlets slightly waxy. Scattered in dense shrubland on red loam with Eucalyptus eudesmioides. CANB, PERTH

Location: N of Wee Warra Hill, Murchison House Station, Western Australia.
Description: Several-stemmed tree to 6 m tall. Bark rough to 3 metres; smooth above. Leaves very glossy, green, with many oil glands but venation obvious. Dominant here on massive limestone breakaways. PERTH + photos

Location: Just W of Mt Curious, Murchison House Station, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark mostly smooth but loose and ribbony. leaves glossy, green, reticulation dense with a few oil glands. A few mallees of this here, growing on whitish-yellow sand in shrubland.  CANB, PERTH

Location: Near East Koorie Dam, Murchison House Station, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, most several-stemmed, some mallee-like, to 7 m tall. Bark rough over most of stems, grey to dark grey and moderately-fissured; smooth above, grey over coppery. Leaves very glossy, green, reticulation moderate with numerous oil glands (but less dense than in E. myriadena). Dominant here on massive limestone breakaways with Eucalyptus loxophleba ssp. loxophleba nearby on deeper soils. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: SW of Bottom Dam, Murchison House Station, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves more or less dull, slightly blue-green. On deep red sand with Eucalyptus eudesmioides, E. aff. rigidula (Kalbarri form) and E. oldfieldii. PERTH

Location: E-W cutline, Murchison House Station, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 m tall, mostly single-stemmed. Bark rough to first branches, moderately-fissured, grey; smooth above, grey over coppery-tan. Leaves very glossy, green, with dense oil glands obscuring tertiary venation (only side veins seen). In open woodland on undulating shaley soil with Eucalyptus loxophleba ssp. supralaevis. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Near Warran Jababba Spring, Eurady Station, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale tan over cream. leaves glossy, green, reticulation moderately-dense with few oil glands. On pale yellow sandplain near creek in open mallee with Eucalyptus gittinsii ssp. gittinsii. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Near Warran Jababba Spring, Eurady Station, Western Australia.
Description: Coppice from lignotuber (graded track). leaves more or less concolorous, not waxy, dull, grey-green, ovate becoming broad-lanceolate later. On pale yellow sandplain near creek in open mallee with Eucalyptus gittinsii ssp. gittinsii. AD, CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Near Warran Jababba Spring on Bungabandi Creek, Eurady Station, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4.5 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey over orange. Leaves dull, blue-green, maturing slightly glossy. Scattered clumps in broad sandy bed of creek in orange-grey clay-loam. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: E-W firebreak on S boundary Kalbarri NP adjoining Eurady Station, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. leaves dull, blue-green. Buds and fruits somewhat variable in size and shape; this collection is only mallee seen here in flower. All stamens free; flowers aging to very slightly pink. On yellow sandplain in shrubland. (No E. beardiana, E. leptopoda and E. oldfieldii seen since before Eurady Homestead). CANB, PERTH

Location: E-W firebreak on S boundary Kalbarri NP adjoining Eurady Station, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. leaves dull, blue-green. Buds and fruits somewhat variable in size and shape; this collection with fruits reminiscent of Eucalyptus drummondii. (No E. beardiana, E. leptopoda and E. oldfieldii seen since before Eurady Homestead). CANB, PERTH

Location: Central N-S track, Kalbarri National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, pink and whitish. leaves dull, blue-green. Common here in low shrubland on yellow sandplain with Eucalyptus gittinsii ssp. gittinsii. (No E. beardiana, E. leptopoda and E. oldfieldii seen since before Eurady Homestead). CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Ranger Track, Kalbarri National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Whipstick mallee to 2 m tall. Bark smooth throughout. leaves dull, blue-green, reticulation moderately-dense with few if any oil glands. Common here in low shrubland on deep yellow sandplain with Eucalyptus gittinsii ssp. gittinsii. (No E. beardiana, E. leptopoda and E. oldfieldii seen since before Eurady Homestead). CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Dartmoor Rd nr Dartmoor homestead, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 9 m tall, most single-stemmed. Bark rough for 2 to 3 metres, moderately-fissured, grey to almost black; smooth above, grey over coppery-tan. Leaves very glossy, green, reticulation obscured by numerous oil glands. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus dolichocera and E. obtusiflora in low open woodland on plain of red loam. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Dartmoor Rd, just NE of Binnu East Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 8 m tall. Bark rough for 2 metres, dark grey; smooth above, grey over tan. Leaves glossy, dark green, tertiary venation obscured by dense oil glands. A few trees of this here on red loam plain with Eucalyptus loxophleba ssp. supralaevis. CANB, PERTH

Location: Windaning Hill ridge, Karara Mine, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 m tall. Bark rough for half stem height, moderately-fissured, flaky-fibrous, dark grey; smooth above, grey over tan/orange. Leaves very glossy, light green, reticulation moderate, with numerous oil glands.  Pure stands on slopes and at base of pure banded ironstone ridge in shrubland. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Ca. 700 m SW of John Forest Lookout, Karara area, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, pinkish over powdery white. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets distinctly glossy and dark purple.  About six mallees on rocky ridge of loam and banded ironstone, in open shrubland, with some Eucalyptus loxophleba ssp. supralaevis nearby. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Warriedar to 'moonscape' track, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, some several-stemmed, to 7 m tall. Bark rough for about 1 metre; smooth above, cream over tan. leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets waxy. In very open and long unburnt woodland with Eucalyptus loxophleba ssp. supralaevis. Good E. clelandii seen about 10 kms to south of here. CANB, PERTH

Location: 'Moonscape', Warriedar area, Western Australia.
Description: Trees or large mallees to 7 m tall. Branchlets generally waxy; buds variably so. Some seedlings here with lignotubers, some without. Saplings mallet-like. On breakaways and on run-off flats below breakaways (various rock types) with some Eucalyptus loxophleba ssp. supralaevis. PERTH + photos

Location: E of Southern Cross Well, Warriedar Station, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 8 m tall; clump about 10 m in diameter. Bark rough for 0.5 metres, otherwise smooth, tan. Leaves glossy, green, reticulation moderate with very few irregular oil glands. Flowers white, with conspicuous staminodes. Single large clump, isolated from other eucalypts, in red clay-loam wash area in Acacia shrubland. CANB, PERTH

Location: W side Lake Mongers near Warriedar homestead, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 m tall, mostly single-stemmed. Bark rough for 3 to 7 metres, thick and moderately fissured, dark grey; smooth above, cream and tan Leaves dull, blue-green. Buds variably waxy. Branchlets variably waxy, but mostly not waxy. Pure stand on very powdery brown loam on flat adjacent to salt lake. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: 100 m E of Mt Singleton summit, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, most several-stemmed, to 8 m tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 metres, moderately fissured, dark grey; smooth above, glossy, orange-coppery. Branchlets waxy. On rocky slope in red loam between bluestone rock. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus ewartiana x E. leptopoda subsp. arctata
Location: Goodlands Rd, N of Kalannie, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 7 m tall. Bark rough, thick and flaky on lower stems; smooth above and weakly minniritchi-type. In full flower (Eucalyptus ewartiana is not in flower here). Single large mallee with Eucalyptus ewartiana, E. subangusta ssp. pusilla, E. brachycorys and E. horistes, with E. leptopoda ssp. arctata nearby. PERTH

Location: Black Rd, S of Lake Moore, Western Australia.
Description: Slender-stemmed tree with a terminal crown, to 9 m tall. Bark rough for 1 to 3 metres, moderately-finely fissured and tightly held, grey; smooth above, grey over orange-tan. Leaves very glossy, green, with numerous oil glands. Fruits very sparse - none collected for seed. Dense, almost pure stand (some Eucalyptus salicola) forming woodland on flat of pale red loam near salt lakes. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Black Rd, W side of Lake O'Grady, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 11 m tall. Bark rough for 1 to 4 metres; smooth above. Leaves very glossy, green, with dense oil glands. Near pure stand on pale red loam on flat near salt lake, with some Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. supralaevis. PERTH + seed

Location: Scotman Rd, SE of Lake Harvey, Western Australia.
Description: In mallee scrub with Eucalyptus brachycorys. Photo specimen only.

Location: Corner of Scotman Rd & Mouroubra Rd, Western Australia.
Description: In mallee scrub with Eucalyptus tenera, E. brachycorys and E. kochii (sspp. plenissima - amaryssia intergrade). Photo specimen only.

Location: Bunce Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Bark notably ribbony, very pale pink-tan. leaves dull, blue-green. In mallee scrub with Eucalyptus celastroides ssp. virella. Photo specimen only.

Location: Dromidaries Hill, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee 5 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout. Branchlets, leaves and fruits waxy. One main clump plus a smaller mallee within 10 metres of main clump, in high valley on granite dome. PERTH + seed

Location: W base of Mt Churchman, Western Australia.
Description: Open woodland dominated by this species, with Eucalyptus petraea nearby closer to rocks. Photo specimen only.

Location: Between Mt Churchman & Beeringgnurding Hill, Western Australia.
Description: Scattered mallees on thin sandy-loam over granite on flat between granite domes in dense Acacia and Allocasuarina shrubland. Photo specimen only.

Location: S base of Beeringgnurding Hill, Western Australia.
Description: Erect-stemmed mallee to 7 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout, accumulating near base. Branchlets strongly waxy. Leaves dull, grey-green. 10 to 20 clumps seen, at southern base and side of extensive granite dome complex, in granite hollows with dense Acacia. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: NW of summit of Beeringgnurding Hill, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout, slightly glossy, red-brown. Branchlets, leaves, buds and fruits waxy. Flowers pale yellow. 20 to 25 plants seen on top, sides and near base (north-west half of complex only) of extensive granite dome complex, with scattered shrubs. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus horistes - E. sp. Mukinbudin intergrade
Location: Beringbooding Rd, ESE of Bonnie Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 m tall. Bark rough for about 1 metre; smooth above and somewhat ribbony. leaves slightly glossy, green. Branchlets not waxy. Dominant here on slope of broad rise in gravely pale orange sand with Eucalyptus leptopoda ssp. leptopoda. PERTH

Location: NE base of Geeraning Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Long-unburnt mallees to 5 m tall. Bark thick and flaky on lower stems, dark grey; minniritchi-type above, reddish. Branchlets, buds and fruits waxy. Scattered clumps at north and east base of granite dome, with Eucalyptus crucis ssp. lanceolata and E. petraea nearby. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: North-east base of Geeraning Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Long-unburnt mallees to 5 m tall. Bark thick and flaky on lower stems, dark grey; minniritchi-type above, reddish. Branchlets, buds and fruits waxy. Scattered clumps at north and east base of granite dome, with Eucalyptus crucis ssp. lanceolata. CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Geeraning Rocks to Mt Jackson track, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 m tall. Bark rough for 1.5 to 3 metres, moderately-fissured, dark grey; smooth above, pale grey over orange. leaves glossy, green, with dense oil glands. On flat of pale orange loam in open woodland dominated by this species, also some Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. lissophloia and E. salmonophloia. CANB, PERTH + photos

Location: Granite complex (Eagle Rock?) just W of Geeraning Rocks to Mt Jackson track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout, accumulating at base. Most plants appearing to be in severe drought stress. Scattered here at base and in depressions of massive granite dome complex, in places with Eucalyptus petraea. PERTH + photos

Location: Yanneymooning Hill, south-west gully, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 8 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout. Leaves dull, dark green. Branchlets, buds and fruits strongly waxy. Large population; in two gullies on south side of granite dome complex, in more or less pure stands with some Acacia.  PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Bencubbin - Kellerbellin Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 m tall. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets waxy. In roadside mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus sheathiana. PERTH

Location: South-east slope of Mt Caroline, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 m tall. Bark minniritchi-type throughout, accumulating and thick at base. Leaves dull, dark grey-green. Branchlets, buds and fruits waxy. Large population; at base and in crevices of granite dome complex. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Kiupto Forest, South Australia.
Description: NA

Location: Wangaratta to Beechworth Rd corner with River Rd, Victoria.
Description: NA

Location: Coolgardie - Esperance Highway, S of Widgiemooltha, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Dominant here on undulating topography in low open woodland with some Eucalyptus celastroides subsp. celastroides and E. ravida. Photo specimen only

Location: Coolgardie - Esperance Highway, ca. 10 km S of Coolgardie, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, glossy, bronze-coppery. Leaves dull, greyish. Branchlets, new growth, buds and fruits waxy. First of this species seen coming from south, on slight rise in open woodland with Eucalyptus celastroides subsp. celastroides, E. planipes/trachybasis and E. salmonophloia. PERTH Seeds

Location: N of Koolyanobbing, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 13 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. On pale red loam in open woodland with Eucalyptus longicornis, E. salubris, E. vittata and E. yilgarnensis. AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Between Koolyanobbing and the Helena and Aurora Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout, cream. Leaves glossy, dark green, with very scattered oil glands. On very broad rise of pale yellow sand (sandplain) dominated by Eucalyptus horistes, also some E. loxophleba subsp. lissophloia. AD, PERTH Seed

Location: NW side of Helena and Aurora Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough to 3 metres; smooth above. Leaves glossy, green. On red loam on undulating topography in open mallee with Eucalyptus ebbanoensis subsp. ebbanoensis, E. longissima and E. loxophleba subsp. lissophloia. AD, PERTH Seed

Location: NW side of Helena and Aurora Range, Western Australia.
Description: Juvenile leaves from base of stem. leaves waxy, greyish (narrow), concolorous. Stems waxy, terete. On red loam on undulating topography in open mallee with Eucalyptus ebbanoensis subsp. ebbanoensis, E. longissima and E. loxophleba subsp. lissophloia. AD, PERTH

Location: Main ridge of Helena and Aurora Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Dominant on slopes and ridges of banded ironstone range in open mallee with some Eucalyptus capillosa and E. corrugata and Triodia groundstorey. Photo specimen only

Location: Main ridge of Helena and Aurora Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 metres; smooth above. Leaves glossy, yellow-green, numerous oil glands. A few mallees on banded ironstone in south-facing gully with Eucalyptus ebbanoensis subsp. ebbanoensis. AD, PERTH

Location: Main ridge of Helena and Aurora Range, Western Australia.
Description: Juvenile coppice from lower stems. Leaves (narrow), dull, greyish. A few mallees on banded ironstone in south-facing gully with Eucalyptus ebbanoensis subsp. ebbanoensis. AD, PERTH

Location: NW end of Helena and Aurora Range, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. On flats of red clay-loam with Eucalyptus longicornis and E. yilgarnensis. Photo specimen only

Location: Track between Helena and Aurora Range and Hunt Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 8 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 metre; smooth above. leaves very glossy, green. Branchlets variably waxy. On sandy red loam in open mixed mallee woodland on level topography with Eucalyptus salmonophloia. AD, PERTH

Location: SW side of Hunt Range, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark variable between individuals, completely smooth in some, rough to one metre in others, dark grey. leaves dull, blue-green. Buds weakly waxy; fruits and branchlets waxy. In open woodland on level topography on red loam with Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. lissophloia, E. transcontinentalis and E. salmonophloia. AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Near Pittosporum Rock, N of Hunt Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough for ca. 2 metres then smooth. leaves dull, blue-green at first, soon becoming glossy and green. Buds and fruits variable in size, this among smallest. On red sandy loam in shrubland with Eucalyptus corrugata. AD, PERTH

Location: N of Hunt Range, Mount Manning Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, thick, amorphic, dark grey; minniritchi above. Scattered in dense Acacia scrub with Eucalyptus clelandii and E. salmonophloia nearby. PERTH

Location: Between Hunt Range and Mount Manning Range, Mount Manning Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark rough for 1.5 metres; smooth above, tan over cream. leaves glossy and green. On pale red sand plain in dense Acacia burkittii scrub with Eucalyptus moderata, E. longissima and E. leptopoda subsp. subluta. AD, CANB, PERTH Seed

Location: SE of Mount Manning Range, Mount Manning Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee or tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough for 3 to 4 metres; smooth above, pink-tan. Leaves glossy and green. Branchlets waxy. Dominant here on slight rise of loam with quartz gravel, with some Eucalyptus concinna and E. yilgarnensis. AD, CANB, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Mount Manning Range, ridge W of South West Peak, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall, dense habit. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, pale blue-green. Scattered clumps on pure banded ironstone ridge dominated by Eucalyptus ebbanoensis subsp. ebbanoensis. AD, PERTH

Location: Near Olby Rock, between Mount Manning Range and Die Hardy Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 9 metres tall. Bark rough to 4 metres; smooth above. leaves glossy, light green. Common here on flats of red loam with Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. lissophloia and E. moderata. PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Youanmi - Paynes Find Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough for ca. 0.5 metres; smooth above, cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. On undulating granite by roadside with Eucalyptus orbifolia. PERTH

Location: Paynes Find - Thundelarra Road, near Mongers Lake, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, non-lignotuberous, to 12 metres tall. Bark rough for ca. half tree height, dark grey, moderately compact and moderately fissured. Branchlets very slightly waxy. Leaves dull, blue-green. Large pure stand forming a low forest with chenopod understorey. PERTH Photos

Location: Farm NW of Mullewa, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale pink and pale grey. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. Locally co-dominant with Eucalyptus jucunda on very broad rise of deep yellow sand in natural windbreak on farm; also some E. eudesmioides. AD, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Farm NW of Mullewa, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Flowers cream (this plant in full flower). On deep orange sand in Banksia and Hakea shrubland with Eucalyptus jucunda and E. eudesmioides. AD, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus leptopoda subsp. arctata - E. oldfieldii intergrade
Location: Ranger Track, ca. 50 m from Station Track, Kalbarri National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall, whipstick form. Bark smooth throughout. Scattered in low shrubland on slightly undulating pale yellow sand. Eucalyptus leptopoda subsp. arctata and E. oldfieldii seen about 1 to 2 km to south-east. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus leptopoda subsp. arctata - E. oldfieldii intergrade
Location: Ranger Track, ca. 50 m from Station Track, Kalbarri National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall, whipstick form. Bark smooth throughout. Scattered in low shrubland on slightly undulating pale yellow sand. Eucalyptus leptopoda subsp. arctata and E. oldfieldii seen about 1 to 2 km to south-east. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus leptopoda subsp. arctata - E. oldfieldii intergrade
Location: Ranger Track, ca. 50 m from Station Track, Kalbarri National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall, whipstick form. Bark smooth throughout. Scattered in low shrubland on slightly undulating pale yellow sand. Eucalyptus leptopoda subsp. arctata and E. oldfieldii seen about 1 to 2 km to south-east. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus leptopoda subsp. arctata - E. oldfieldii intergrade
Location: Ranger Track W of Central Track, Kalbarri National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall. Scattered on slightly undulating yellow sand in open mallee shrubland with Eucalyptus gittinsii subsp. gittinsii and E. jucunda. Eucalyptus oldfieldii seen about 1 km to west. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus leptopoda subsp. arctata - E. oldfieldii intergrade
Location: Bunga Track, Kalbarri National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Scattered on yellow sand in low shrubland with Eucalyptus gittinsii subsp. gittinsii and E. jucunda. AD, PERTH

Location: North West Coastal Highway, Western Australia.
Description: Whipstick mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, grey over white (a little rough bark at base). Leaves dull, green, no visible intramarginal vein. In very open mallee shrubland with Eucalyptus gittinsii subsp. gittinsii and some E. rigidula (Kalbarri form). AD, PERTH

Location: Southern access of Kennedy Range track, Western Australia.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree to 8 metres tall. Bark mostly rough, tessellated, brown; some smooth white patches. leaves dull, green. First of this species seen coming from the south; scattered clumps on red sand dune. AD, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Southern access of Kennedy Range track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough for 0.5 metres, smooth above. Leaves dull, pale blue-green. Branchlets, buds and dry fruits waxy. First of this species seen coming from south; about eight plants on bare Mookarite outcrop. PERTH Photos

Location: Southern access of Kennedy Range track, Kennedy Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark variable between individuals; smooth throughout in some, rough to one metre in others. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets waxy. Plants very drought-stressed. Dominant here on massive breakaway scree, but not on plateau or plains below. Photo specimen only

Location: Central E-W Kennedy Range track, Kennedy Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough for ca. 1 metre; smooth above. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets variably waxy. First of this species seen coming from south-west, at the beginning of red sand dunes in plateau, with Corymbia lenziana. AD, PERTH

Location: Central E-W Kennedy Range track, Kennedy Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall, forming large clonal clumps. Branchlets and fruits quite waxy. First of this species seen coming from south-west, on red sand plain between dunes, with Corymbia lenziana. AD, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Central E-W Kennedy Range track, Kennedy Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark rough on lower stems. Leaves very glossy, green. In red sand swales between dunes in open mallee with Corymbia lenziana and Eucalyptus pallida. AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Eastern escarpment, Kennedy Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough to 1 metre, smooth throughout in some plants. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets and new fruits waxy. Common on upper scree slopes of massive east-facing breakaway of sandstone. PERTH Photos

Location: Lyons River crossing, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 14 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, tan over white. Leaves glossy and green. Dominant along river banks with Eucalyptus victrix. PERTH Seed

Location: Mount Augustus summit, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy shrub or mallee to 2 metres tall. bark rough, flaky-tessellated. Scattered on upper slopes and summit of massive sandstone monolith in Acacia scrub. Corymbia ferriticola on steeper sites on mid-slopes and foot-slopes. AD, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Mount Nameless, S side on road half way up, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. leaves more or less glossy, green, with scattered to dense intersectional oil glands. On very steep southerly slope and ridge, in open mallee with Eucalyptus pilbarensis, E. kingsmillii subsp. kingsmillii and E. gamophylla. AD, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Mount Nameless, S side on road half way up, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy multi-stemmed tree 4 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, coarsely-tessellated, grey-brown. Rare here, on very rocky steep southerly ridge with Corymbia hamersleyana, Eucalyptus leucophloia subsp. leucophloia, E. kingsmillii subsp. kingsmillii, E. trivalvis, E. xerothermica and E. gamophylla. AD, PERTH

Location: Mount Nameless, S side on road one third way up, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark rough to finger-diameter branches, tessellated. Leaves very slightly discolorous, glossy, green. Common here, on southerly ridge with Corymbia ferriticola, Eucalyptus pilbarensis, E. kingsmillii subsp. kingsmillii, E. aff. lucasii and E. gamophylla. AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Mount Nameless, S side on road one third way up (1088 m), Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout, yellow-tan and pale grey. Leaves more or less dull, blue-green to green. On steep south-westerly ridge with Corymbia hamersleyana, Eucalyptus pilbarensis, E. kingsmillii subsp. kingsmillii and E. repullulans. AD, PERTH

Location: Mount Nameless, S side on road near top (1110 m), Western Australia.
Description: Single plant ca. 5 metres tall. Estimated age <30 years old. Leaves very glossy, green. No fruits seen. In road windrow, possibly a semi-neophyte (grader tyres etc), none others seen. Growing with Eucalyptus pilbarensis and E. kingsmillii subsp. kingsmillii. Photo specimen only

Location: Mount Nameless, S side on road near top (1110 m), Western Australia.
Description: Dominant mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Flowers pink (others seen here are pale creamy-yellow). Growing with Eucalyptus pilbarensis, E. leucophloia subsp. leucophloia, and E. aff. lucasii. PERTH

Location: Mount Sheila summit (997 m), Hamersley Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout. Leaves dull to glossy, mostly green, some more or less blue-green. Scattered on slopes and summit in low mallee with Corymbia opaca/hamersleyana, Eucalyptus kingsmillii subsp. kingsmillii, E. leucophloia subsp. leucophloia, and E. gamophylla. AD, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Mount Sheila summit (997 m), Hamersley Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, blue-green. Common on slopes and summit in low mallee with Corymbia opaca/hamersleyana, Eucalyptus aff. lucasii, E. leucophloia subsp. leucophloia, and E. gamophylla. PERTH Seed

Location: E of Derby on Gibb River Road, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough to 3 to 4 metres, flaky-fibrous, pale brown; smooth above, white. All of this species here in full flower. On gravely orange loam on plain with Acacia tumida and Corymbia polycarpa. PERTH

Location: Gibb River Road between Derby and Napier Range, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout or rough to 1 metre, thin and compact, more or less white above. Leaves dull, green, setose, petiolate. Scattered trees in open woodland. Photo specimen only

Location: Track to Lennard River Gorge, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Open woodland dominated by Corymbia greeniana and Eucalyptus tectifica. Photo specimen only

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), near Mt Elizabeth Station cattle yards, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, finely-fissured, hard, grey and pale grey. Leaves slightly glossy, green. On sandy flat with Corymbia greeniana and C. polycarpa. AD, PERTH Seed

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), Caroline Ranges, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough on trunk but thin and flaky, grey and brown over cream. Branches more or less smooth. Leaves slightly discolorous, moderately glossy, green, Co-dominant with Eucalyptus tectifica in open woodland on undulating stony red loam. AD, PERTH

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), near Pearson Creek campsite, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Irregularly formed tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, coarsely tessellated, grey-brown. Leaves setose, dull, green. Fruits variable in size, ovoid. In open woodland on sandy soil with Corymbia latifolia, Eucalyptus tetrodonta and C. miniata (lowland form - non-waxy, broad leaves, not in flower). AD, CANB, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), near Bachsten Jump-up, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark flaky rough on trunk, otherwise smooth and cream. Leaves more or less concolorous, slightly glossy, green. Scattered in undulating hills of very rocky red loam dominated by Eucalyptus ?oligantha; also some Corymbia disjuncta. AD, PERTH Seeds

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), near Bachsten Jump-up, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, finely-fissured. leaves more or less dull, green. Trees mostly leafless (deciduous) and in fruit. Dominant in undulating hills of very rocky red loam with Corymbia byrnesii and some C. disjuncta. AD, PERTH Seed

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), S of Bachsten's camp, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, some several-stemmed, to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, blue-green. Dominant on massive sandstone outcrop with some Corymbia torta and Eucalyptus brachyandra. On plain below outcrop is E. miniata, E. tetrodonta and E. houseana. AD, PERTH Seeds + photos

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), camp at end of track at Walcott Inlet, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 6 metres tall. Bark rough to about 2 metres, hard and tessellated; smooth above, transition variably distinct. On rocky sandstone hill above estuary with Corymbia byrnesii and Eucalyptus tectifica. AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Plateau summit of Mt Daglish, off Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout. leaves slightly glossy and green, more or less glabrous. Scattered on plateau and upper scree slopes of sandstone escarpment. On rocky slopes is Corymbia byrnesii and Eucalyptus tectifica. On true cliffs is E. brachyandra. AD, PERTH + fruits Photos

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), near Calder River crossing, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Dominant on grey clay on river floodplain with some Eucalyptus tectifica. Photo specimen only

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), E of Calder River crossing, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, more or less cream. leaves slightly glossy, green. No buds or fruits. On rocky sandstone plateau in sand with Corymbia polycarpa, C. ferruginea subsp. stypophylla, Eucalyptus tetrodonta and E. miniata (broad-leaved, non-waxy). AD, PERTH

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), near Wren's Gorge, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, more or less white. leaves dull, light green. On sandy flat between sandstone ridges with Corymbia polycarpa and Eucalyptus miniata (lowland form). Also C. clavigera nearby on sandstone and E. brachyandra on rocks in Wren's Gorge. Photo specimen only

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), SE of Lemonade Spring, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Height - 34.5 m Spread average - 14.0 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 2.30 m. On sandy creek with equally tall Melaleuca leucadendra dominant. National Register of Big Trees record + photos

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), near Bachsten Jump-up, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 7 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout, some accumulation at base of some trees. Leaves glossy and green. On sandstone mesa in more or less pure stand with an open understorey. PERTH Photos

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), E of Pearson Creek, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: In open woodland on pale brown clay-loam with Eucalyptus tectifica. Photo specimen only

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), W of Magpie Jump-up, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough throughout. On sand between sandstone ridges with Eucalyptus tetrodonta and E. miniata (waxy form).  Photo specimen only

Location: Munja Track (Walcott Inlet track), W of Drysdale River, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: First of this species coming from the west, growing in open woodland with Corymbia polycarpa, C. ferruginea subsp. stypophylla, Eucalyptus tetrodonta and E. tectifica. Photo specimen only

Location: Gibb River Road, ca. 6 km E of Kalumburu junction, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. No buds or fruits present on trees. Scattered in woodland dominated by Eucalyptus tetrodonta and some Corymbia ferruginea subsp. stypophylla.  Photo specimen only

Location: Gibb River Road, 34.7 km E of Kalumburu junction, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, cream, but with accumulated grey-brown flakes. Leaves concolorous, more or less dull, green. Common here on red sandy-loam with Callitris and Eucalyptus lirata. AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Gibb River Road, 51.8 km E of Kalumburu junction, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Co-dominant with Corymbia cadophora subsp. pliantha in mallee vegetation on rocky hillslope with Triodia groundstorey. Photo specimen only

Location: Gibb River Road, 60.0 km E of Kalumburu junction, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 7 metres tall. Bark rough throughout. Leaves dull, grey-green, more or less waxy. Branchlets waxy. Like E. 'sheranica' - variable. On flat of stony loam with Corymbia curtipes, Eucalyptus obconica and E. jensenii.  AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Track to Oombulgurri from Home Valley, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: No flower buds or fruits on either eucalypt species here. Co-dominant with Corymbia drysdalensis in very open woodland on sandstone hill with soft Triodia groundstorey. Photo specimen only

Location: Track to Piccaninny Gorge, Purnalulu National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Many-stemmed tree to 6 metres tall. Bark box-type throughout. On sandy soil with Corymbia opaca (especially slightly up-slope) and with Triodia groundstorey. Photo specimen only

Location: Track to Piccaninny Gorge, Purnalulu National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white with reddish flakes. New growth silvery and crowns appearing silvery. Dominant tree on red sand adjacent to sandstone domes, with Corymbia opaca nearby on loamier soils and C. cliftoniana nearby on rockier sites. Photo specimen only

Location: Track to Piccaninny Gorge, Purnalulu National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 6 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately fissured and tessellated, grey-brown. Leaves concolorous, dull, green. Scattered generally, but locally dominant, growing on stony red sand adjacent to sandstone domes. AD, PERTH Seed + photos

Location: Mini Palm Gorge, Purnalulu National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Dominant in gorge with Livistona victoriae. Also here on cliffs is Eucalyptus brachyandra. Photo specimen only

Location: Type locality in Ragged Range, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy tree, some multi-stemmed, to 5 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, more or less thick and tessellated, grey. Leaves dull, bluish, very slightly waxy. 50+ plants on rocky W-facing slope in woodland of Corymbia collina, C. drysdalensis, Eucalyptus confluens and E. jensenii. AD, PERTH Seeds + photos

Location: Main ridge of Ragged Range, Kimberley, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Co-dominant with Corymbia collina on high ironstone ridge with Triodia understorey. Photo specimen only.

Location: El Lando (river), E of Chaos, near Viverio, Spain.
Description: Height - 35.0 m Spread average - (38 m & 30.5 m) = 35.0 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 7.82 m. Circumference at 1.0 m - 8.33 m. National Register of Big Trees record + photos

Location: El Lando (river), E of Chaos, near Viverio, Spain.
Description: Height - 68.0 m (+/- 2.0 m) Spread average - 20.0 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 4.80 m. Circumference at 1.0 m - 5.00 m. National Register of Big Trees record + photos

Location: Vale de Canas, E of Coimbra, Portugal.
Description: Height - 72.0 m Spread average - 22.0 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 5.70 m. Circumference at 1.0 m - 6.14 m. National Register of Big Trees record + photos

Location: Bussaco, near Luso, N of Coimbra, Portugal.
