Description: Height - 64.0 to 65.0 m Spread average - (38 m & 29 m) = 33.5 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 8.37 m. Circumference at 1.0 m - 9.03 m. National Register of Big Trees record + photos

Location: Foreshore between Vilagarcia and Caldiguela, Galacia, Spain.
Description: Height - 31.5 m (c. 30 m for adjacent tree) Spread average - (22.5 m & 19.0 m) = 21.0 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 3.77 m (3.89 m for adjacent tree). Circumference at 1.0 m - 3.89 m (3.96 m for adjacent tree). National Register of Big Trees record + photos

Location: Top end of Giant Stairway, Three Sisters near Katooma, Blue Mountains, New South Wales.
Description: NA

Location: Echo Point lookout, Katooma, Blue Mountains, New South Wales.
Description: NA

Location: S of Woodford, Blue Mountains, New South Wales.
Description: Single large tree in dense recovering rainforest. Height - 71.0 m (+/- 1 m) Spread average - 30.0 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 7.84 m National Register of Big Trees record + photos

Location: Cathedral of Ferns walk, Mt Wilson, Blue Mountains, New South Wales.
Description: On rainforets margin with Eucalyptus cypellocarpa, E. radiata, E. oreades and E. piperita nearby. Struck by lightning in 2008; tree now 90% dead & likely to structurally fail to NE. Height - 39.0 m Spread average - 34.0 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 9.03 m National Register of Big Trees record + photos

Location: Opposite 12 The Avenue, Mt Wilson, Blue Mountains, New South Wales.
Description: Bark rough to small branches, stringy, grey over brown. In roadside vegetation with Eucalyptus fastigata, E. radiata, E. oreades and E. sieberi. Height - 25.5 m Spread average - (25.0 m & 28.0 m) = 26.5 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 5.00 m AD, CANB + seeds + NRBT record + photos

Location: Opposite 12 The Avenue, Mt Wilson, Blue Mountains, New South Wales.
Description: Common here in roadside vegetation with Eucalyptus fastigata, E. blaxlandii, E. oreades and E. sieberi. Height - 23.0 m Spread average - (24.0 m & 19.0 m) = 21.5 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 3.52 m NRBT record + photos

Location: Mt Tomah Botanical Gardens, Blue Mountains, New South Wales.
Description: More or less pure stand on basalt slopes. Height - 36.0 m Spread average - (46.0 m & 30.0 m) = 38.0 m Circumference at 1.4 m - 7.26 m NRBT record + photos

Location: Track to Point Bollingbroke, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Sprawling, dense mallee <2 metres tall. Leaves glossy, green. Dominant here on white sand dunes and sand on cliff tops, emergent in low shrubland. Nearby on less exposed sites is Eucalyptus calcareana and E. leptophylla. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Point Bollingbroke, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee <1.5 metres tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. A few plants here, in low open mallee dominated by Eucalyptus angulosa on headland of white sandy-loam over limestone, overlooking coast. PERTH

Location: Mikkira Station, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Many-stemmed tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches (about 80 mm diameter), moderately fissured, grey. Leaves glossy, green. Dominant here on flats of reddish loam over limestone in broad depressions ,in more or less pure stands. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Fishery Bay, S of Port Lincoln, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Windswept mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, grey over cream. Common here on limestone overlooking coast in low dense mallee, with Eucalyptus angulosa and E. diversifolia subsp. diversifolia. PERTH + seed

Location: Fishery Bay Rd, near Koodinga, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Several hundred trees, none really old, on disturbed natural vegetation site alongside of roadway. Some Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. diversifolia, E. vimianlis subsp. cygnetensis and Allocasuarina verticillata and weedy Pinus halepensis. Likely natural regeneration from fence line row of oldest planted trees. PERTH

Location: Fishery Bay Rd, near Koodinga, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Juveniles from small damaged lignotuber. Leaves dull, blue-green. Several hundred trees, none really old, on disturbed natural vegetation site alongside of roadway. Some Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. diversifolia, E. vimianlis subsp. cygnetensis and Allocasuarina verticillata and weedy Pinus halepensis. Likely natural regeneration from fence line row of oldest planted trees. PERTH

Location: Summit of North Block, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Scattered on edges of rounded, exposed summit in reddish and whitish shaley rock, with Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. diversifolia and E. odorata. AD, PERTH

Location: Gully on S side of North Block, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, some box bark near base. leaves maturing glossy, olive green. In full flower (all cream). Common here in rocky gully with Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. diversifolia and E. leptophylla; nearby on lower ground is E. albopurpurea, E. porosa and E. cladocalyx subsp. cladocalyx. PERTH

Location: Gully on S side of North Block, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Flowers various shades of pink.  In rocky gully with Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. diversifolia, E. odorata and E. leptophylla; nearby on lower ground is E. albopurpurea, E. porosa and E. cladocalyx subsp. cladocalyx. PERTH

Location: Settlers Rd, W of Cummins, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Common here with Eucalyptus phenax subsp. phenax. Photo reference only

Location: Main road S of Yeelanna, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 10 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 m, coarsely-fissured and loose, grey; smooth above, glossy, pale greenish-yellow. Leaves more or less glossy, olive green. In broad slight depression, with Eucalyptus calycogona subsp. spaffordii and E. peninsularis nearby. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: NE of Yeelanna, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, but curled and persisting on lower stems. Dominant here on clay-loam in broad depression near saline creek, in mallee with Eucalyptus pileana/calcareana and E. leptophylla. Photo reference only

Location: Campground on N-S track in Hinks CP, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. On broad rise of outcropping sheet limestone with powdery grey loam, co-dominant with Eucalyptus yalatensis; also Melaleuca lanceolata. Photo reference only

Location: N-S track in Hinks CP, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Leaves mostly more or less glossy and green, but dull and bluish on some new growth and in juveniles. On slightly undulating pale grey loam over limestone in mallee, with some Eucalyptus leptophylla and E. yalatensis. Photo reference only

Location: N-S track in Hinks CP, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Dominant here on more or less level pale grey sand in open mallee, with some Eucalyptus incrassata, E. oleosa subsp. ampliata and E. socialis subsp. viridans and a Tiodia groundstorey. Photo reference only

Location: NA
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Dominant here on low sand dune of near white sand, with Eucalyptus socialis subsp. viridans. Photo reference only

Location: NA
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark completely smooth in many, some rough to 0.5 to 1 m up. Leaves completely glossy and green. Dominant here in mallee vegetation on level topography on shallow loam over limestone, with some Eucalyptus phenax subsp. phenax. Photo reference only

Location: Main road S of Darke Peak, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Dominant here, in mallee vegetation. Photo reference only

Location: Ridge track on Darke Peak Range, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark rough at base but mostly smooth, grey and coppery. leaves glossy, blue-green at first, maturing dark green. In full flower. Buds very slightly waxy. Dominant here on rocky ridge, with Eucalyptus porosa nearby on steeper sites and E. phenax subsp. phenax (Hills Variant) nearby scattered on ridge. PERTH

Location: Ridge track on Darke Peak Range, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, grey over pale grey over yellow-cream. Leaves glossy, green, reticulation moderately-dense, with scattered intersectional oil glands. Common here on rocky ridge and slopes, in low shrubland, with some Eucalyptus calycogona subsp. calycogona, E. leptophylla and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Quarry W of Darke Peak on foot of range, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over coppery-tan, some rough bark at base of some plants. Leaves glossy, green. Common here in mallee on undulating stony loam, with Eucalyptus phenax subsp. phenax (Hills Variant) and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. Also nearby is E. cretata on slightly lower ground. Photo reference only

Location: N of Wudinna on Bartley Rd, South Australia.
Description: Juvenile leaves from lower stem coppice. Leaves more or less orbicular, greyish, waxy. Common here on undulating pale red loam, with Eucalyptus calcareana (grey-leaved) and E. gracilis. PERTH

Location: N of Wudinna on Bartley Rd, South Australia.
Description: On white undulating sand in mallee scrub dominated by this, also with Eucalyptus calcareana (grey-leaved) and E. sp. Great Victoria Desert. Photo reference only

Location: N of Wudinna on Bartley Rd, Pinkawillie NP, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough for ca. 1 m, moderately-fissured and shaggy. leaves glossy, dark green. In swale or red loam between dunes, in mallee, co-dominant with Eucalyptus oleosa. PERTH

Location: Chillunie campground, Gawler Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Mallee or several- to many-stemmed tree-mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark rough for about 2 m, thick and modeartely-fissured; smooth above, grey and tan. Buds slightly waxy. Leaves glossy, blue-green maturing green. Common here, on stony red loam in broad valley, with Eucalyptus gracilis and E. porosa. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Ridge near Mt Fairview, Gawler Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over pale tan. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing glossy and green. Leaf size and colour and bud and fruit size is very variable here. Dominant on ridges with some Eucalyptus gracilis. AD, PERTH

Location: Ridge near Mt Fairview, Gawler Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over pale tan. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing glossy and green. Leaf size and colour and bud and fruit size is very variable here. Dominant on ridges with some Eucalyptus gracilis. AD, PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus gypsophila - E. calcareana - E. cretata hybrid swarm?
Location: LP Track, Gawler Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony. Leaves dull, greyish, maturing blue-green. Branchlets, buds, fruits and new leaves waxy. Two large mallees on creek bank, with Eucalyptus porosa dominant. More plants of same seen for next few kms to north on red sandy-lam flats. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Summit of Conical Hill, Gawler Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Thin-stemmed mallee to 4 metres tall, but mostly <2 m on summit. Bark mostly smooth throughout, grey over cream. Flowers mostly red, some paler and possibly hybrids. Dominant here on slopes and summit of rhyolite hill, with some Eucalyptus socialis subsp. socialis and Allocasuarina verticillata. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Road on northern boundary of Gawler Ranges National Park, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves consistently small, but variable in colour between plants; some completely glossy and green, many glossy and blue-green. Common here on rocky rise in open mallee, with Eucalyptus gracilis and E. socialis subsp. socialis (E. porosa nearby). PERTH

Location: Ilkina Dunefield, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. No parts waxy. Common here on orange sand dune plain, with Eucalyptus concinna and some E. gracilis and E. oleosa. PERTH

Location: Near Churchill Well on track between Lake Everard Station and Googs Lake, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 m, then curled then smooth. Leaves dull, very blue-green, reticulation moderate, very few oil glands. About ten mallees in minor creek in very open chenopod woodland of Casuarina pauper and some Eucalyptus gracilis. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Just W of dog fence on track between Lake Everard Station and Googs Lake, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall, sprawling. Bark rough on lower stems; smooth above, coppery. Leaves dull, blue-green. First of this species seen since DN 5936 when coming from the east, growing in red sandy swale, with Eucalyptus concinna, E. gracilis and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis nearby. PERTH

Location: Nalara Rock on track between Lake Everard Station and Googs Lake, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 11 metres tall. Bark rough on larger stems, thick, loosely coarsely fibrous, dark grey; smooth and ribbony above. None in flower. A hundred or so mallees, mainly on south side of granite outcrop in red sand, where water runs off. Also a few mallees at Lois Rocks about 10 km to the north-west. PERTH + seed

Location: Track to Lois Rocks, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough on lower stems, ribbony-fibrous. leaves glossy, dark green, thick. A few mallees (first of this species seen coming from the east), on red sand dune with Eucalyptus socialis subsp. victoriensis. (E. concinna, E. gracilis and E. gypsophila below in swales). PERTH

Location: Track between Lake Everard Station and Googs Lake, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. No parts waxy. Leaves dull, grey-green. Common here on red sand dunes, with Eucalyptus concinna and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis. PERTH

Location: Track between Lake Everard Station and Googs Lake, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 m, then smooth, pale coppery. Crown a mixture of adult, intermediate and juvenile leaves. Scattered here on pale red sand in swales between dunes, with Eucalyptus concinna and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis. PERTH

Location: Track between Lake Everard Station and Googs Lake, South Australia.
Description: Common here in open mallee shrubland, on reddish sand on dunes and in swales, codominant with Eucalyptus socialis subsp. victoriensis and with some E. gypsophila. Photo reference only

Location: Googs track, S of Googs Lake, South Australia.
Description: First of this species seen since DN 5939 when coming from the east via Googs Lake. On high east-west red sand dunes, with Eucalyptus concinna and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis. Photo reference only

Location: Googs track, Yumbarra CP, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Crown slightly blue-green but leaves glossy and green, dense oil glands. On pale red sand on dune slope in open malee, with Eucalyptus capitanea and E. yumbarrana. PERTH

Location: Dog fence gate on Googs track, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 m, then smooth. Leaves glossy, dark green. Common here on undulating pale grey loam over limestone in mallee, with Eucalyptus oleosa and some E. capitanea, E. yumbarrana and E. gracilis. Indistinguishable from E. oleosa in habit and bark. PERTH

Location: Salt lake N of Lake Iford, South Australia.
Description: First of this species seen when coming from the south. Dominant here on red sand adjacent to aline lake system, with Acacia papyrocarpa adjacent on slightly higher ground. Photo reference only

Location: Watson to Maralinga rd, South Australia.
Description: First of this species seen when coming from the south. Common here on red sand dunes, with Eucalyptus concinna and E. sp. Great Victoria Desert. Photo reference only

Location: Watson to Maralinga rd, South Australia.
Description: On swale of red sand dune, with Eucalyptus concinna, E. gracilis and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis. (E. oleosa subsp. oleosa about 0.5 km to south). Photo reference only

Location: Watson to Maralinga rd, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark white. Leaves distinctly greyish. First of this species seen when coming from the south. Growing on red sand dune, with Eucalyptus concinna, E. gypsophila and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis. Photo reference only

Location: Watson to Maralinga rd, South Australia.
Description: Bark mostly smooth, ribbony. Buds and fruits to photograph. Scattered on red sand on plain, with Eucalyptus concinna, E. gypsophila and E. ?socialis subsp. victoriensis. Photo reference only

Location: Dey Dey Rd, South Australia.
Description: On red sandy-loam plain in open mallee, with Eucalyptus concinna, E. gypsophila and E. pimpiniana. (E. vokesensis is common about 10 km to SE of here on road). Photo reference only

Location: Dey Dey Rd, about 5 km SE of Oak Valley turnoff, South Australia.
Description: On red sandy plain in open mallee, with Eucalyptus concinna, E. oleosa subsp. oleosa and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis. Photo reference only

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus canescens subsp. canescens x E. vokesensis
Location: Dey Dey Rd, near Oak Valley turnoff, South Australia.
Description: Single plant intermediate between the parental species. pale yellow flowers, slightly beaked opercula, no fruits (= E. yumbarrana subsp. striata). On red sand plain in open mallee, with Eucalyptus concinna, E. canescens subsp. canescens and E. vokesensis. PERTH

Location: Dey Dey Rd, W of Oak Valley, South Australia.
Description: On red sand plain in open mallee, with Eucalyptus concinna, E. wyolensis and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis, and a Triodia groundstorey. Photo reference only

Location: Tjuntjunjara to Oak Valley rd, W of Cook rd, South Australia.
Description: Dominant here on red sand plain between low, well-spaced dunes in open mallee, with Eucalyptus vokesensis and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis. Photo reference only

Location: Unnamed CP on Tjuntjunjara to Oak Valley rd, South Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark rough on lower stems, then smooth and white above. Leaves dull, mostly blue-green, some becoming greener with age. On sides and in swale of red sand dunes in open Acacia shrubland, with Eucalyptus gypsophila and E. socialis subsp. victoriensis. Photo reference only

Location: Unnamed CP on Tjuntjunjara to Oak Valley rd, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 8 metres tall. First seen since Maralinga-Watson road when coming from east. On red sand dune high in landscape. Photo reference only

Location: Deakin to Eucla track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark mostly rough. leaves dull, blue-green, maturing slightly glossy. Lone mallee in very open woodland of Acacia papyrocarpa, first eucalypt seen when coming from north (Deakin). PERTH

Location: Foot of scarp track between Madura and Eyre Bird Observatory, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 10 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout. Scattered trees on loamy plain below scarp, in chenopod shrubland, with scattered Acacia papyrocarpa. Photo reference only

Location: Near Toondi Rockhole between Madura and Eyre Bird Observatory, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall, sprawling. Larger stems rough-barked, moderately coarse and stringy, hard. Dominant mallee in scarp gully, on pure limestone, with some Eucalyptus gracilis, E. calcareana and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. Photo reference only

Location: Foot of scarp track between Madura and Eyre Bird Observatory, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Common on calcareous grey loam over limestone, with Eucalyptus gracilis and E. calcareana. Photo reference only

Location: Near Olwolgin Bluff on track between Madura and Eyre Bird Observatory, Western Australia.
Description: Seedling leaves dull, blue-green, ovate to elliptical. Seedlings growing in burnt mallee shrubland of Eucalyptus calcareana, E. gracilis and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. AD, PERTH

Location: Foot of scarp track between Madura and Eyre Bird Observatory, Western Australia.
Description: Seedling leaves dull, blue-green, becoming glossy and greener at 150 mm tall. Seedlings growing in burnt mallee shrubland of Eucalyptus calcareana, E. gracilis and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. AD, PERTH

Location: Foot of scarp track between Madura and Eyre Bird Observatory, Western Australia.
Description: Seedling leaves dull, blue-green. Seedlings growing in burnt mallee shrubland of Eucalyptus calcareana, E. gracilis and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. AD, PERTH

Location: Foot of scarp track between Madura and Eyre Bird Observatory, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Pith glands present. Leaves glossy, light green. On top of limestone escarpment, with Eucalyptus gracilis, E. diversifolia subsp. hesperia and E. yalatensis. AD, PERTH

Location: Foot of scarp track between Madura and Eyre Bird Observatory, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark rrough for 1 to 2 metres, moderately-fissured, grey; smooth above. Leaves glossy, green, reticulation moderate, scattered oil glands. Pith glands present, small and scattered. Common here on pale grey loam below limestone escarpment, with Eucalyptus gracilis. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Wurrengoodya Hills, track to Eyre Bird Observatory from highway, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough over lower half of stems, fibrous-stringy, grey. leaves glossy, slightly blue-green at first, maturing dark green. Mostly just finished flowering. On white sand hills, with Eucalyptus brachycalyx, E. diversifolia subsp. hesperia and E. incrassata. PERTH

Location: Kaniaal Beach, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth. Leaves glossy, light green.  Common on first line sand dunes (white sand), in low dense mallee, with Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. hesperia and E. incrassata. AD, PERTH

Location: Kaniaal Beach, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark mostly rough, stringy-fibrous but tightly held. Leaves glossy, slightly blue-green at first, maturing dark green.  In mallee vegetation on first sandhill behind beach, in white sand, with Eucalyptus brachycalyx and E. incrassata. PERTH

Location: Kaniaal Beach, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth, but very ribbony and accumulating.  In mallee vegetation on first sandhill behind beach, in white sand, with Eucalyptus brachycalyx and E. discreta. PERTH

Location: Eyre Bird Observatory to Twilight Cove track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. In full flower. Bark rough at base, otherwise smooth, pale grey over tan-orange. On white sand over limestone, high on undulating hills, with Eucalyptus brachycalyx, E. incrassata and E. discreta. PERTH

Location: Twilight Cove track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 10 x 10 metres, but much smaller on exposed limestone escarpment nearby. Larger stems rough-barked. Leaves dull, blue-green, maturing glossy green. In swales of white sand hills in dense Acacia scrub, with Eucalyptus brachycalyx. AD, PERTH

Location: Near Twilight Cove, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Leaves glossy, slightly blue-green. On top of limestone escarpment, with Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. hesperia, E. gracilis, E. incrassata, E. oleosa subsp. ampliata and E. discreta. AD, PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between Twilight Cove and John Baxter Memorial, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough. Leaves dull, grey-green. First of this species seen (coming from the east) since before Eyre Bird Observatory, on top of limestone escarpment in low mallee, with Eucalyptus cooperiana, E. incrassata and E. discreta. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between Twilight Cove and John Baxter Memorial, Western Australia.
Description: Regrowth from damaged lignotuber. Leaves broadly elliptical, dull, blue-green. On white sand over limestone in low open mallee, with Eucalyptus incrassata. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between Twilight Cove and John Baxter Memorial, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling bushy tree (obligate seeder) or mallee-like, to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, glossy, grey over orange. Leaves glossy, metallic dark olive green. Large stand (100+) over at least one square kilometre, on white sand over limestone high in landscape, with Eucalyptus incrassata and E. discreta. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Telegraph track between Twilight Cove and John Baxter Memorial, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, grey over tan. Leaves glossy, dark green. First of this species seen (coming from the east),on orange clay-loam over limestone, on flat in open mallee, with Eucalyptus gracilis, E. yalatensis and E. discreta. PERTH

Location: John Baxter Memorial track at coastal cliffs, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee <0.5 metres tall. On pure limestone tableland above high cliffs on coast in low scrubland, with Eucalyptus yalatensis. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between John Baxter Memorial and Toolinna Cove, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark ribbony rough at base, smooth above, pale grey over orange and cream. Leaves glossy, green. On plains of red clay-loam over limestone in open mallee, with Eucalyptus conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. gracilis, E. yalatensis and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. AD, PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between John Baxter Memorial and Toolinna Cove, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough for one metre, then smooth, pale pink-grey and white. On rise of pure limestone in open mallee, with Eucalyptus E. brachycalyx, E. yalatensis and E. gracilis. First of this species seen (coming from the east) since Thundulda sand ridges to east. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track near Toolinna Cove, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark rough on older stems. Leaves glossy, dark green. First of this species seen (coming from the east),in low mallee on edge of low limestone rise, with Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. hesperia, E. brachycalyx, E. yalatensis and E. discreta. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track near Toolinna Cove, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee forming dense thickets to 3 metres tall. Dominant plant on slightly undulating white sand over limestone, just inland of coastal rise, with scattered Eucalyptus discreta. Photo reference only

Location: Toolinna Cove, Western Australia.
Description: Spreading mallee <0.5 metres tall. Leaves glossy, green. In low closed shrubland on top of limestone cliffs overlooking ocean, with Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. hesperia, Banksia and Melaleuca. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between Toolinna Cove and Balladonia turnoff at Point Culver, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall. In mallee shrubland on grey loam over limestone, with Eucalyptus conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. gracilis and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. Photo reference only

Location: Telegraph track between Toolinna Cove and Balladonia turnoff at Point Culver, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth or rough for one to two metres up. Leaves glossy, green. Dominant here on grey loam over limestone, with Eucalyptus cooperiana and E. yalatensis. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between Toolinna Cove and Balladonia turnoff at Point Culver, Western Australia.
Description: Seedling following wildfire. Leaves dull, blue-green. In burnt open mallee vegetation on white sand ridge over limestone, with some Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. hesperia and E. discreta. Nearby below dune is also E. conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. cooperiana, E. brachycalyx and E. yalatensis. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between Balladonia turnoff and Wylie Scarp descent near Bilbunya Dunes, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 8 metres tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. In burnt mallee vegetation in grey loam over limestone behind white sand dune, with Eucalyptus gracilis dominant, and some E. cooperiana. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between Balladonia turnoff and Wylie Scarp descent near Bilbunya Dunes, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Burnt from wildfire about one year ago. Coppice regrowth from lignotuber. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. First of this species seen (coming from the east), growing on deep white sand at foot of dune, with Eucalyptus discreta and E. incrassata. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track between Balladonia turnoff and Wylie Scarp descent near Bilbunya Dunes, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark rough and coarsely stringy but tightly held on larger stems. Leaves mostly burnt from wildfire about one year ago. On pale grey sandy-loam over limestone ion slight rise with Eucalyptus cooperiana, E. discreta and E. incrassata. AD, PERTH

Location: Telegraph track, just below Wylie Scarp, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 5 metres tall. Burnt about one year ago. Mature plants all dead and with no vegetative regrowth. Seedlings common; leaves scabrid early, dull, blue-green, soon becoming glabrous, glossy and green. On white sand over limestone in dense mallee with Eucalyptus conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. scyphocalyx and E. uncinata. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track, just below Wylie Scarp, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2 metres tall. Burnt about one year ago. Seedling leaves dull, grey-green. On white sand over limestone in dense mallee with Eucalyptus conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. scyphocalyx and E. utilis. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track, just below Wylie Scarp, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark smooth but ribbony throughout. Leaves glossy, dark green. A few unburnt mallees in largely burnt mallee scrub on pale grey sand, with Eucalyptus incrassata and E. micranthera. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Top of escarpment to N of Telegraph track, N of Bilbunya Dunes, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough on lower stems. Leaves glossy, dark green. On more or less pure limestone on plateau at top of escarpment with Eucalyptus conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. cooperiana, E. incrassata and E. utilis. PERTH + seed

Location: Telegraph track, N of Bilbunya Dunes, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dark grey over yellow-tan. Leaves glossy, dark olive green. Small stand on grey loam in mallee shrubland of Eucalyptus brachycalyx and some E. gracilis. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Telegraph track, N of Bilbunya Dunes, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Regrowth from mallees burnt about one year ago. regrowth 800 mm tall with glossy, dark green leaves. In dense Melaleuca shrubland on flat of grey loam with some Eucalyptus brachycalyx and E. eremophila. PERTH

Location: Salt lakes on Telegraph track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. On white sand on S side of salt lake, in mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus eremophila (closest to lake), E. micranthera, E. discreta, E. incrassata and E. conglobata subsp. conglobata. AD, PERTH + seed + images

Location: Salt lakes on Telegraph track, Western Australia.
Description: Dense-crowned mallee to 4.5 metres tall. Bark rough over most of stems. Large stand forming pure stand of low mallee on white sand adjacent to salt lake with Melaleuca species. AD, PERTH + seed + images

Location: Salt lakes on Telegraph track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Leaves moderately glossy, dark green. Dominant mallee on S side of salt lake on pale grey sand in mallee shrubland with Eucalyptus angustissima nearby. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track, S of Wattle Camp, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark rough at base, then smooth, more or less white. Leaves glossy, green. In swale of white sand over limestone, emergent in low shrubland with Eucalyptus incrassata nearby. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track, S of Wattle Camp, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark mostly rough. Leaves dull, grey-green. A few mallees on pale grey sand near salt lakes, emergent above chenopod shrubland, with Eucalyptus oleosa subsp. ampliata and E. brachycalyx. AD, PERTH + seed + images

Location: Telegraph track, S of Wattle Camp, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark rough on stems. Leaves held conspicuously erect compared to associated species. In slightly undulating white sand in mallee with Eucalyptus incrassata, E. uncinata and E. leptocalyx subsp. petilipes. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track, S of Wattle Camp, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth but quite ribbony. In slightly undulating white sand in mallee with Eucalyptus incrassata, E. uncinata and E. scyphocalyx. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track, S of Wattle Camp, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3metres tall. Looks intermediate between E. scyphocalyx and E. leptocalyx subsp. petilipes here. Several plants of this here, in slightly undulating white sand in mallee with Eucalyptus incrassata, E. scyphocalyx, E. uncinata and E. leptocalyx subsp. petilipes. PERTH

Location: Telegraph track, N of Israelite Bay, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallet to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, more or less glossy, dark grey over coppery. Leaves glossy, green. Scattered stands on slightly undulating white sand near salt lakes in mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. scyphocalyx and E. uncinata (rough-barked). PERTH + images

Location: Telegraph track, N of Israelite Bay, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee to 2 metres tall. Leaves glossy, green. Dominant on white sand rises in low mallee shrubland. PERTH + seed

Location: Telegraph track, N of Israelite Bay, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth. Common here on slightly undulating white sand in mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus litorea and E. eremophila. Photo reference only

Location: Telegraph track, N of Israelite Bay, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Wax absent. Flowers white. Growing on pale yellow sand hill overlooking salt lake in open mallee with Eucalyptus incrassata (tending angulosa). First of this species seen coming from east.  PERTH + images

Location: Lake Darlingdella, SW of Israelite Bay, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 10 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 3 metres, tightly held, moderately fissured, grey. Leaves dull at first, maturing glossy and dark green. Common here on white sand adjacent to salt lake, forming mallee shrubland. PERTH + images

Location: Lake Darlingdella, SW of Israelite Bay, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth but very ribbony. Leaves glossy, green. On slightly undulating white sand on SE edge of salt lake; Eucalyptus incrassata and E. litorea nearby. PERTH

Location: Junction of Point Malcolm Road and Poison Creek Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough on larger stems; smaller mallees completely smooth-barked. Leaves dull at first, maturing glossy and dark green. More or less pure stand on white sand over limestone in dense mallee shrubland. PERTH + seed

Location: 1.5 km S of Fisheries Road on Point Malcolm Road, Western Australia.
Description: Reproductively mature sapling-stage mallet 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream. Flower buds consistently waxy; branchlets variably so. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing glossy, green; reticulation sparse? with moderate amount of island oil glands. About 50 plants here on pale grey sand on plain in mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus uncinata, E. extrica, E. litorea?, E. cooperiana, E. incrassata and E. tumida. AD, CANB, NSW, PERTH + seed + images

Location: 1.5 km S of Fisheries Road on Point Malcolm Road, Western Australia.
Description: Seedling ca. 600 mm tall. Leaves and stems waxy. Leaves dull, grey-green. No lignotubers seen. On pale grey sand on plain in mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus uncinata, E. extrica, E. litorea?, E. cooperiana, E. incrassata and E. tumida. PERTH

Location: 1.2 km S of Fisheries Road on Point Malcolm Road, Western Australia.
Description: Reproductively mature sapling-stage mallet to 4 metres tall. Flower buds conspicuously waxy. Leaves dull, blue-green (waxy on small saplings). On level topography of pale grey sand over clay in malee vegetation with Eucalyptus uncinata, E. extrica, E. leptocalyx, E. cooperiana, E. incrassata and E. tumida AD, PERTH

Location: 1.2 km S of Fisheries Road on Point Malcolm Road, Western Australia.
Description: Reproductively mature sapling-stage mallet 5.5 metres tall. Bark becoming rough for 1 to 1.5 metres.  On more or less white sand over clay in mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus uncinata, E. conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. incrassata and E. tumida Photo reference only

Location: Scadden Rd, NW of Greens Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall, open crown. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, green. On plain of white sand over clay with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa dominant. PERTH + seed + images

Location: Truslove Rd, N of Esperance, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough on larger stems. Leaves dull, distinctly blue-green at first, maturing less distinctively so. In mallee vegetation between salt lakes with Eucalyptus quadrans, E. leptocalyx (quad-twig) and E. uncinata.  PERTH

Location: SE side of Pink Lake, near Esperance, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout On hillslope above salt lake in open mallee vegetation with Eucalyptus incrassata dominant. PERTH + seed

Location: Middle Rd, between Mason Bay Rd and Fence Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 metres, tightly held, grey. leaves dull at first, maturing glossy and dark green. More or less pure stand in broad depression of saline white sand.  PERTH

Location: Junction of South Coast Highway and Cocanarup Rd, W of Ravensthorpe, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 12 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 metres; smooth above. Leaves glossy, dark green. In tall mallee shrubland on undulating hills on gravelly orange clay-loam with Eucalyptus extensa and E. oleosa subsp. corvina.  PERTH

Location: 'Moon Lagoon' track, Lake Magenta Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout but very ribbony, grey over pale grey and cream. Leaves glossy, green. Dominant here on deep white sand, eremrgent above low shrubland with some Eucalyptus sp. 'Sullivan Soak'.  PERTH

Location: Lake Magenta Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 12 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 metres, slightly tessellated, grey; smooth above, grey over pale grey and orange-tan. Leaves glossy, green. On grey loam beside salt lake with Eucalyptus kondininensis.  AD, PERTH + seed + images

Location: East Rd on W side of Lake Magenta, Lake Magenta Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark rough for < 0.5 metres. Leaves maturing glossy and green. Common here on lake flat of white sand over clay, emergent in Melaleuca shrubland.  AD, PERTH + seed + images

Location: East Rd on W side of Lake Magenta, Lake Magenta Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over orange-coppery. Leaves glossy, green. On white sand on edge of salt lake with Eucalyptus 'sp. 'southern wheatbelt' and E. phaenophylla. PERTH

Location: Sullivan Soak, Lake Magenta Nature Reserve, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, green. Scattered on deep white sand in depression, as understorey to open forest of Eucalyptus occidentalis and E. salmonophloia. Also some E. suggrandis subsp. promiscua. PERTH

Location: Mordetta Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall. Bark rough, soft but tightly-held, becoming ribbony higher. leaves glossy, green. A few mallees on granitic sand below exposed granite in partially cleared mallee vegetation. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Farm S side of Mordetta Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 16 metres tall. Bark amorphic at base of larger mallees, otherwise minniritchi and reddish. Leaves dull, blue-green. Several dozen plants on edge of granite outcrop and cleared paddock. PERTH + seed + images

Location: First highway coastal lookout coming from W, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. On sides of limestone escarpment with Eucalyptus yalatensis and some E. oleosa ampliata and E. calcareana Photo reference only

Location: SW of Penneshaw, W boundary of Dudley CP, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: NA

Location: Bomb Alley Rd, N of Burchmore Lagoon, SW of Kingscote, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: NA

Location: Seal Bay Rd, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: NA

Location: Playford Highway, just E of West End Highway, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: NA

Location: South Coast Highway, E of Rocky River, Flinders Chase NP, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: NA

Location: South Coast Highway, E of Rocky River, Flinders Chase NP, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: NA

Location: Rocky River campground, Flinders Chase NP, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: NA

Location: Ravine De Coares valley where crossing Playford Highway, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 41.0 m Crown spread: 22.5 m Circumference BH: 3.90 m Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Ravine De Coares valley where crossing Playford Highway, Kangaroo Island, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 45.5 m Crown spread: 20.5 m Circumference BH: 2.78 m Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Adjacent to skate park in Federation park, Gumaracha, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 36.0 m Crown spread: 28.5 m Circumference BH: 9.33 m Big Tree Record only

Location: Mt Moffat Track, south of Blackboy Track, Little Desert National Park, Victoria.
Description: Tree 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, platy, pale grey over yellow-cream. Leaves slightly glossy, green. Scattered on slightly undulating white sand with Eucalyptus arenacea dominant; also some E. leptophylla and E. leucoxylon subsp. pruinosa nearby. AD, CANB, MELB Photos + seed

Location: Mt Moffat Track, south of Blackboy Track, Little Desert National Park, Victoria.
Description: Whipstick mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough for ca. 1 metre, then smooth above, dark bronze. Leaves glossy, dark green. Small stands on edge of clay depression with Eucalyptus leucoxylon subsp. pruinosa, E. fasciculosa and some E. leptophylla. AD, CANB, MELB

Location: Big Red, NW side of Mullinger Swamp, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 39.0 metres Crown spread: 31.0 & 27.0 = 29.0 metres Circumference BH: 12.04 metres Hollow basal trunk. One metre diameter recent branch failure. Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: NW side of Mullinger Swamp, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 38.0 metres Crown spread: 35.0 & 32.0 = 33.5 metres Circumference BH: 9.32 metres Solid base. Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Bilston Tree, Dergholm State Forest, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 33.5 metres Crown spread: 25.5 & 24.5 = 25.0 metres Circumference BH: 7.95 metres Solid trunk; moderate lean to south. Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 1 km S of Bilston Tree, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 27.0 metres Crown spread: 31.0 & 26.0 = 28.5 metres Circumference BH: 9.72 metres Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Dwyers Creek, ca. 0.6 km downstream of bridge, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 31.5.0 metres Crown spread: 28.0 metres Circumference BH: 13.19 metres Hollow base. 500+ years old. Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Walking track to summit of Mt Thackeray, Grampians National Park, Victoria.
Description: Trees, to 18 metres tall. Dominant on high rocky ridge, both on exposed sites and in chasms. Distinct from Eucalyptus baxteri (which occurs with E. obliqua on deeper soils lower down) in more compact rough bark, more extensive smooth bark (to 100 to 300 mm diameter), and thicker leaves and larger fruits. AD, MEL Photos + seed

Location: Forest Lodge Road, ca. 80 m south of road, Grampians National Park, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 48.0 metres Crown spread: 26.0 metres Circumference BH: 7.28 metres Recently fire-hollowed base. In open forest of this and E. ovata subsp. ovata. Some E. ovata to 33 m tall here. Big Tree Record only + photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus cypellocarpa - E. goniocalyx subsp. goniocalyx intergrade
Location: Corner Mt Wallace Rd and Old Thompson Rd, Brisbane Ranges National Park, Victoria.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 9 metres tall. Bark variable, mostly partly rough, loose (like E. litoralis). Juveniles seen are variable, many green and glossy (like E. cypellocarpa). Adult leaves glossy, dark green. On undulating site in dense woodland with mainly Eucalyptus aromaphloia and E. obliqua. AD, CANB, MELB Photos + seed

Location: Djerriwahrr Creek bridge on Diggers Rest - Coidamae Road, Victoria.
Description: Tree 8 metres tall. Bark rough and finely fissured throughout. leaves dull to very slightly glossy, pale green to slightly blue-green. Only two trees on very disturbed roadside with a few Eucalyptus microcarpa plus many different planted trees; also in creek is E. viminalis subsp. viminalis. AD, MEL Photos + seed

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus cypellocarpa - E. goniocalyx subsp. goniocalyx intergrade
Location: Foxy Gully Track, Lerderderg State Park, Victoria.
Description: Variable size and bark; mostly 5 to 15 metres tall, bark mostly smooth to mostly rough (but thin), certainly intermediate between the parents. Scattered but frequently seen here in dense woodland dominated by Eucalyptus dives and some E. obliqua and E. macrorhyncha. AD, MEL Photos + seed

Location: Junction of Grassy Gully Track and Blackwood Ranges Track, Victoria.
Description: Bark rough throughout, finely-fissured, grey. Leaves glossy, dark green, but whole crown appearing bluish. Dominant tree on hills and ridges here, on stony grey clay with some Eucalyptus cypellocarpa - goniocalyx intergrades, E. obliqua and E. macrorhyncha. AD Seed

Location: Fryars Street, Guildford township, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 30.0 metres Crown spread: 38.5 & 35.0 = 37.0 metres Circumference BH: 11.00 metres over burl at 1.3 metres above ground; 9.00 m above burl at 1.6 metres above ground Solid trunk but numerous branch hollows. Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 150 metres from Smiths Reef Track on Tatt Town Track, Maldon Historic Reserve, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall, many several-stemmed. Bark deeply stringy throughout, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, green, shorter and broader than E. macrorhyncha here. In dense woodland with Eucalyptus polyanthemos subsp. marginalis, E. goniocalyx subsp. goniocalyx and E. macrorhyncha. AD, CANB, MELB Seed

Location: 150 metres from Smiths Reef Track on Tatt Town Track, Maldon Historic Reserve, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall, some several-stemmed. Bark deeply stringy throughout, grey-brown. Leaves longer and relatively narrower than E. aurifordina here. In dense woodland with Eucalyptus polyanthemos subsp. marginalis, E. goniocalyx subsp. goniocalyx and E. aurifordina. AD, MEL

Location: 150 metres from Smiths Reef Track on Tatt Town Track, Maldon Historic Reserve, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark deeply stringy throughout, grey-brown. In dense woodland with Eucalyptus polyanthemos subsp. marginalis, E. goniocalyx subsp. goniocalyx, E. macrorhyncha and E. aurifordina. AD, MEL

Location: Corner Smiths Reef Track and Tatt Town Track, Maldon Historic Reserve, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall, many several-stemmed. Bark deeply stringy throughout, grey-brown. Leaves very glossy, dark green, shorter and broader than E. macrorhyncha here. Flowers white. In dense woodland with Eucalyptus polyanthemos subsp. marginalis, E. goniocalyx subsp. goniocalyx and E. macrorhyncha. AD, CANB, MELB Photos + seed

Location: Moyreisk Bushland Reserve (at sign), Victoria.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, deeply fissured, hard, dark grey. Leaves waxy at first, becoming glossy, dark green. Variable here with regard to wax on branchlets, leaves and fruits, many non-waxy, many others slightly waxy, some others (like this collection) more so. Dominant here on undulating hills in woodland with Eucalyptus polyanthemos subsp. marginalis and E. microcarpa. AD, MEL Photos + seed

Location: Torrington State Forest, near W edge on Kanya road, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, finely to moderately fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. No parts pruinose. Common here in woodland with Eucalyptus leucoxylon subsp. pruinosa, E. melliodora, E. tricarpa, E. macrorhyncha and E. microcarpa. AD, CANB Photos + seed

Location: Corner Break Track and Wimmera Track, Wail State Forest, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. All features appear as subsp. cygnetensis except juvenile growth. Adult new growth also very slightly waxy. Bark rough to small to medium-sized branches, moderately to coarsely fissured, platy-fibrous. leaves glossy, green. Unusual habitat of pure white sand (?overlying clay) dominated by Callitris, with some Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. camaldulensis, E. arenacea and E. largiflorens. AD, MEL Photos + seed

Location: Corner Break Track and Wimmera Track, Wail State Forest, Victoria.
Description: Juvenile coppice from 1.5 m above ground level on trunk. Leaves dull, green, new growth waxy. Unusual habitat of pure white sand (?overlying clay) dominated by Callitris, with some Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. camaldulensis, E. arenacea and E. largiflorens. AD, MEL

Location: 200 metres north of rail line on Boyeo Rd from Terranginnie Rd, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 11 metres tall. Bark rough, moderately finely-fissured to small branches. Leaves glossy, dark green. A few remnant trees and a dozen semi-remnant trees in partially cleared roadside vegetation with Casuarina. AD, MEL Photos

Location: Mallee Dam Road, SW of Nhill, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 33.0 metres Crown spread: 32.5 & 30.5 = 31.5 metres Circumference BH: 9.20 metres Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Harding Springs Reserve, Bordertown - Pinnaroo Road, South Australia.
Description: In depression with Eucalyptus arenacea and E. incrassata on sand on slightly higher ground. Photo specimen only

Location: Senior Road, N of Bordertown, South Australia.
Description: Roadside vegetation with Eucalyptus phenax, E. incrassata and Melalauca uncinata. Photo specimen only

Location: Tower Road, Penola Forest Reserve, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth or rough on lower trunk to 5 m. Leaves glossy, dark green, reticulation moderate with no visible oil glands. A near pure stand forming low forest on pale grey sand in level area with some Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. cygnetensis. AD, MEL Photos + seed

Location: Snow Gum reserve, N track, Caroline Forest Reserve, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth and stripy, some accumulated on lower trunks. Scattered, mostly at west end of reserve, in low dense forest, here on brown sandy soil with Acacia melanoxylon and Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. cygnetensis. Photo specimen only

Location: Clarkes Park picnic ground, near Port Macdonnell, South Australia.
Description: Irregularly-formed trees to 8 metres tall. Dominant tree with Melalauca lanceolata. Photo specimen only

Location: Germein Reserve loop walk near Port Macdonnell, South Australia.
Description: Dominant tree in woodland on reddish clay-loam with outcropping limestone, with some Eucalyptus ovata var. ovata and a dense understorey. Photo specimen only

Location: Rusty Wire Hutt, Carpenter Rocks conservation area, South Australia.
Description: 50 to 100 plants on low rise of red clay and limestone with stunted Eucalyptus obliqua. Photo specimen only

Location: Between Tantanoola and Glencoe in forest reserve, South Australia.
Description: Trees, mostly several-stemmed, to 8 metres tall. Bark variable, mostly rough peppermint type, to mostly smooth, but most plants largely rough-barked. leaves glossy and green. Dominant here on grey sand with some Eucalyptus obliqua, also E. ovata var. ovata nearby. AD, CANB Photos + seed

Location: Umpherston Sinkhole, Mt Gambier, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 24.0 metres Crown spread: 16.0 & 15.0 = 15.5 metres Circumference BH: 4.96 metres Estimated age 30 - 40 years. Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: O'Neils Lane, north of Mt Burr, South Australia.
Description: Tree 9 metres tall. Bark rough for 1.5 metres, smooth above, orange-tan over cream. leaves glossy, green, apparently glandless. A few roadside trees on plain with Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. camaldulensis. AD, CANB Photos + seed

Location: Clay Wells - Penola Road, NE of Furner, South Australia.
Description: Bark mostly fully rough. Near pure stand on grey sand surrounded by Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. cygnetensis, and further and non-associated is E. obliqua, E. ovata and E. camaldulensis subsp. camaldulensis. Photo specimen only

Location: Ca. 15 km north of Mt Hope towards Cobar, New South Wales.
Description: Several-stemmed tree or mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, +/- green. No parts pruinose. Common here on broad rocky rise with Callitris glaucophylla. Also nearby on lower ground is Eucalyptus intertexta and E. populnea subsp. bimbil. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Nymagee - Hermidale Rd, ca. 7 km east-north-east of Nymagee, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, platy. Leaves dull, blue-green. No parts pruinose. A few dozen trees here (first of species seen coming from south), on broad creek floodplain in loamy soil with Eucalyptus populnea subsp. bimbil dominant, and some E. microcarpa. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Tailby State Forest, west of Gulargambone, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream and pale grey. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. No parts pruinose. On sandy soil on flat with Callitris glaucophylla dominant, and some Eucalyptus populnea subsp. bimbil. AD Photos

Location: Road to Siding Springs Observatory, Warrumbungles, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark mostly rough, moderately fissured. Leaves glossy, dark green. Juvenile leaves glossy, green, +/- orbicular. Common on slopes with a stringybark species. AD Photos

Location: Road to Siding Springs Observatory, Warrumbungles, New South Wales.
Description: Several-stemmed tree-mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Branchlets pruinose. Leaves dull, +/- grey-green, pruinose when new. Small population on granite boulder outcrop with Eucalyptus volcanica and E. ?macrorhyncha, and some E. melliodora nearby. AD Photos

Location: Road to Siding Springs Observatory, Warrumbungles, New South Wales.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 8 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately to finely fissured. Leaves dull, grey-green. Branchlets pruinose. On steep slope in +/- dense woodland with Eucalyptus ?macrorhyncha, also some E. volcanica nearby without any apparent interbreeding. AD

Location: Road to Siding Springs Observatory, Warrumbungles, New South Wales.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Small stand on steep slope with Eucalyptus nortonii, E. colcanica, E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha and Angophora floribunda. AD Photos

Location: Road to Siding Springs Observatory, Warrumbungles, New South Wales.
Description: Coppice from lignotuber. Leaves ovate, dull, blue-green. Stems square, very slightly pruinose. On steep slope with Eucalyptus nortonii, E. colcanica, E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha and Angophora floribunda. AD

Location: West of Coonabarabran towards Warrumbungles, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches. Leaves +/- glossy, dark green. Common along creek flat with Angophora floribunda, also some Eucalyptus albens and E. blakelyi. AD Photos

Location: Gowan rest area, Newell Hwy north of Coonabarabran, New South Wales.
Description: Several-stemmed tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, quite colourful. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Scattered on high broad ridge of sandstone in woodland with Corymbia trachyphloia subsp. amphistomatica, Eucalyptus rossii and E. crebra/beyeri. AD Photos

Location: Road up Mt Kapultar, Mount Kapultar National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to about 1/2 tree height, finely fissured, smooth above, cream and tan. Leaves glossy, dark green. On steep slope in dense woodland with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus melliodora and E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha. AD Seeds

Location: Mt Kapultar summit, Mount Kapultar National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, quite colourful, grey over cream and tan. Leaves glossy, green. Common on rocky summit with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora dominant, and some E. laevopinea. AD Seeds

Location: At car park for Bundabulla Circiut, Mt Dowe, Mount Kapultar National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, slightly powdery, tan over pale grey over white over yellow-cream. Leaves +/- glossy, green. Common here on edge of knoll with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora dominant, and some E. laevopinea. AD Seeds

Location: ca. 4.6 km down Barraba Fire Track from locked gate, Mount Kapultar National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, greenish cream and grey. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green, new growth slightly pruinose. On granite outcrop in mostly pure stand but with some Eucalyptus prava, E. andrewsii (non-pruinose) and E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha, and slightly lower down is E. volcanica and E. elliptica. AD Photos + seeds

Location: ca. 4.6 km down Barraba Fire Track from locked gate, Mount Kapultar National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall, mostly of poor form. Bark smooth throughout, grey over orange-cream. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets and new fruits variably pruinose. Below granite outcrop in mostly pure stand but with some Eucalyptus nandewarica, E. andrewsii (non-pruinose), E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha and E. volcanica. AD Photos

Location: ca. 300 down Barraba Fire Track from locked gate, Mount Kapultar National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Fallen tree 15 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, some ribbony bark near base. Leaves slightly glossy, +/- green. Scattered on plateau in open forest with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora, E. laevopinea and E. viminalis subsp. viminalis, with E. elliptica nearby. Differs from E. elliptica in its more rough bark, its less colourful smooth bark, its taller habit, its umbles in 3's, its larger buds, and its shorter pedicels and peduncles. AD

Location: ca. 300 down Barraba Fire Track from locked gate, Mount Kapultar National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Juveniles from fallen tree. Leaves dull, greyish, pruinose on new growth, rounded initially, then pointed-ovate. Scattered on plateau in open forest with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora, E. laevopinea and E. viminalis subsp. viminalis, with E. elliptica nearby. AD

Location: Track to Waa Gorge, above Mill-Bullah plunge pools, New South Wales.
Description: Slender or multi-stemmed tree-mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, streaked grey, tan and cream. leaves dull, slightly blue-green. On steep slopes and top of granite escarpment adjacent to gorge, with some Corymbia trachyphloia subsp. amphistomatica. AD, CANB Photos + seeds

Location: East side entrance to Warialda town, New South Wales.
Description: Laser height: 27.0 metres. Crown spread: 27.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 4.05 metres.  On sandy soil with Callitris glaucophylla and Eucalyptus chloroclada.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Warialda Rd, south of Yetman, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 metres, then abruptly smooth, pale grey over greenish cream. Leaves dull, +/- concolorous, green. No mature buds or fruits. On creek flats with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus albens and E. melanophloia subsp. melanophloia. AD

Location: Nicholls Rd, Bebo State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 8 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth. Branchlets pruinose when new. Leaves dull, blue-green. Scattered on broad sandstone ridge in tall dense shrubland dominated by Callitris and Acacia. AD Photos

Location: Nicholls Rd, Bebo State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Scraggly mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough over most of stems, moderately coarsely fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. Small stand on top of sandstone rise with Corymbia trachyphloia subsp. amphistomatica, and with Eucalyptus dealbata and E. melanophloia subsp. melanophloia nearby. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Boundary track on edge of Bebo State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Erect-stemmed mallee to 9 metres tall. Bark rough on lower half of stems. Stand of c. 200 plants on low lateritic rise in Acacia scrub with Eucalyptus dealbata, E. melanophloia subsp. melanophloia, E. panda and Callitris glaucophylla. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Road ca. 10 km east-north-east of Texas, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, ironbark, almost black. Branchlets pruinose. Leaves dull, greyish, pruinose when new. On stony rise in woodland with Eucalyptus dealbata and E. microcarpa. AD Seeds

Location: Road ca. 10 km east-north-east of Texas, Queensland.
Description: Tree, mostly several-stemmed, to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Branchlets, new leaves and new fruits pruinose.  On stony rise in woodland with Eucalyptus aff. crebra and E. microcarpa. AD Seeds

Location: Ca. 5 km south of Inglewood towards Texas, Queensland.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, grey and coppery tan. Leaves slightly blue-green at first, maturing glossy and dark green. Small clump of c. 15 mallees in woodland dominated by Eucalyptus woollsiana, E. sideroxylon and E. ?crebra. AD, CANB Photos + seeds

Location: Near Tabacco Rd, just south-west of Coolmunda Dam, Queensland.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 8 metres tall. Bark rough for 1/3 to 1/2 tree height, moderately finely fissured, grey-brown. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Common here on gritty grey loam in dense Callitris scrub. AD Photos + seeds

Location: 4.5 km north of Terrica junction on Gore Rd, Queensland.
Description: Tree, mostly of poor form, to 10 metres tall. Bark variable, mostly rough on lower to most of trunk. Scattered on rolling stony hills, mostly at foot of hills with Eucalyptus dealbata, E. crebra, E. caleyi subsp. caleyi and E. microcarpa. AD

Location: Durikai State Forest, Queensland.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, dark grey over coppery. Leaves +/- glossy, dark green. A few mallees on flat of stony loam in open forest of Eucalyptus fibrosa, E. ?crebra and E. microcarpa/moluccana. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Durikai State Forest, Queensland.
Description: Erect-stemmed mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, grey over orange-tan. Leaves glossy, dark green. A dozen or so mallees in clump as understorey (like E. infera) to Eucalyptus fibrosa, E. ?crebra, E. terrica and E. moluccana. AD, CANB Seeds

Location: Durikai State Forest, Queensland.
Description: Erect-stemmed mallee to 7 metres tall. Large stand scattered as understorey to forest of Eucalyptus fibrosa, E. ?crebra and E. moluccana. Common in forest here and this stand covering several hectares. AD Seeds

Location: Durikai State Forest, Queensland.
Description: Tree 22 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Leaves +/- glossy, mid green. In forest on brown-grey loam with Eucalyptus melliodora, E. ?crebra and E. moluccana. AD

Location: Dalrymple Creek, west of Main Range, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 26 metres tall. Bark rough and ribbony on lower trunk, smooth and cream above. Leaves glossy, mid green. In full flower. Scattered trees beside creek with Casuarina cunninghamiana. AD Photos

Location: Main Range National Park, Goomburra Section, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey over yellow-cream. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. On steep slope in forest with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus eugenioides, E. melliodora and Allocasuarina torulosa. AD Photos

Location: Araucaria Falls car park, Main Range National Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 40 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 m on larger trees, otherwise smooth throughout, streaked cream over yellow-cream. Branchlets not pruinose. Leaves discolorous, green. On creek on orange loam surrounded by rainforest. AD Photos

Location: Ca. 1 km from Cunningham Hwy on Mt Mitchell walk track, Main Range National Park, Queensland.
Description: Trees to 35 metres tall. Bark rough to c. 100 mm diametre, finely fissured, grey. Leaves glossy, dark green, scalloped. On steep slope of ecotone between rainforest and eucalypt woodland with Lophostemon confertus, Eucalyptus biturbinata and Allocasuarina torulosa. AD Photos

Location: Croftby to Killarney road, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 48 metres tall (laser measured). Bark rough for 1 to 2 m, then smooth, pale grey over white. leaves slightly discolorous (?intermediate leaves), +/- glossy, green. Forming open forest with Angophora subvelutina - A. floribunda intergrades as a secondary storey. AD Photos

Location: North-east of Cherry Gully towards Elbow Valley, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, distinctly more colourful that E. tereticornis and E. blakelyi, pale grey over pale orange. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. On slight slope of gravelly loam in low woodland with Eucalyptus crebra and E. subtilior. AD Photos

Location: Sugarloaf Rd, just east of Stanthorpe, Queensland.
Description: Tree 14 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, +/- tessellated, grey. Leaves +/- glossy, dark green. Remnant roadside woodland with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus blakelyi, E. caliginosa and E. conica. AD

Location: Sugarloaf Rd, east of Stanthorpe, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 11 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. In woodland on granitic sand with Angophora subvelutina and Eucalyptus caliginosa. AD Photos

Location: Sugarloaf Rd, east of Stanthorpe, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, hard-fibrous, grey-brown. Leaves distinctively pruinose and silvery when new, maturing +/- glossy and dark green. Branchlets variably pruinose. Dominant here on granitic sand with some Eucalyptus bridgesiana downslope. AD Photos

Location: Sugarloaf Rd, east of Stanthorpe, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. Juvenile leaves on roadside large, broad, dark green. Remnant roadside woodland with Eucalyptus conica, E. nova-anglica and E. bridgesiana. AD Photos

Location: South of Wilsons Downfall on Mt Lindesay Hwy, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately fissured, grey-brown. Leaves dull, light green. Growing in dense forest with Eucalyptus brunnea (emergent to 30 m tall), E. radiata subsp. sejuncta, E. dalrympleana subsp. heptantha and a stringybark. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Link Rd, Boonoo Boonoo National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-platy, grey-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy, dark green above. No mature fruits present. Scattered trees on level granitic sand (but somewhat swampy) in open forest with Eucalyptus andrewsii and E. brunnea. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Boundary Trail, Boonoo Boonoo National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, +/- stringy. Leaves discolorous, dark green above. Growing on mall granite outcrop on slope under open forest of Eucalyptus andrewsii. AD Seeds

Location: Just north of Bruxner Hwy on road to Boorook, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 30 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, but ribbony rough on lower trunk. Leaves +/- dull, slightly blue-green. Buds and fruits distinct from E. viminalis group and like E. benthamii. Seedlings here dull and pale green, E. benthamii-like. On river flat in remnant forest with Angophora subvelutina, Eucalyptus amplifolia subsp. sessiliflora and E. interstans. AD Photos

Location: Just north of Bruxner Hwy on road to Boorook, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 23 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, mostly cream. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. On river flat in remnant forest with Angophora subvelutina, Eucalyptus amplifolia subsp. sessiliflora and E. dorrigoensis. AD

Location: Timbarra Rd, ca. 3 km from Bruxner Hwy, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. Remnant trees in degraded roadside vegetation with Angophora subvelutina, Eucalyptus melliodora, E. blakelyi, E. ?caliginosa, E. bridgesiana and possibly E. banksii. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Mt McKenzie Rd, south-west of Tenterfield, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately fissured, grey-brown. leaves +/- glossy, dark green. On shallow soil on granite hillslope with Eucalyptus blakelyi and E. subtilior. AD Photos

Location: Near Bald Rock, south-west of Tenterfield, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, +/- white. Leaves glossy and green. 20+ trees scattered on west side of granite hill, mostly on bare granite boulders and slabs with some scattered Angophora subvelutina and Eucalyptus andrewsii. AD Photos + seeds

Location: South facing ridge of Bolivia Hill complex, New South Wales.
Description: Sprawling multi-stemmed tree to 7 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy, grey-brown over reddish brown. New leaves, buds and branchlets pruinose. A few clumps high on south-east-facing granite slope with Eucalyptus prava, E. andrewsii and a few E. youmanii. AD Photos + seeds

Location: South facing ridge of Bolivia Hill complex, New South Wales.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale yellow-orange. Leaves dull, grey-green. Growing high on south-east-facing granite slope with Eucalyptus boliviana, E. andrewsii and a few E. youmanii. AD Photos

Location: 2.3 km from Torrington on Silent Grove Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, somewhat stripy and attached on trunk, brown over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green above. In low forest with Eucalyptus andrewsii and E. youmanii. AD Photos

Location: Track to Mystery Face, north-west of Torrington, New South Wales.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale orange. Leaves dull, grey-green. No parts pruinose. On outcropping granite in woodland with Eucalyptus andrewsii and E. youmanii. AD Photos

Location: Gwydir Hwy, west of Black Mountain, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, orange-brown over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green above. In open forest with Eucalyptus nobilis, E. radiata subsp. sejuncta and E. caliginosa. AD Photos

Location: Gwydir Hwy, west of Black Mountain, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark ribbony-rough at base, otherwise smooth, greenish grey over white. Leaves glossy, mid green. In open forest with Eucalyptus brunnea, E. radiata subsp. sejuncta and E. caliginosa. AD

Location: Peregrine Point, Barool National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Several-stemmed mallee or tree to 8 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy. Leaves +/- glossy, dark green above. New growth and branchlets slightly pruinose. Common here on top of north-facing cliff with Eucalyptus scopulorum, E. agglomerata, E. microcorys and E. campanulata. AD Seeds

Location: Track to Mulligans Hut, Gibraltar Range National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. Common here on granitic sand flat adjacent to frost hollow in woodland with Eucalyptus radiata subsp. sejuncta and E. ligustrina. AD

Location: Diggers Camp Rd, Yuraygir National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee-like tree to 4 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy. Leaves discolorous, glossy, dark green above. Small pure stand, emergent but windswept in low heath in swampy depression. AD Seeds

Location: Junction Wooli - Grafton road & Minnie Water Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 28 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy, grey-brown over red-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. On slightly undulating hills with Eucalyptus seeana, E. ?tindaliae and E. ?siderophloia. AD Seeds

Location: Grafton - Wooli road, Yuraygir National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, tan-grey over cream. Leaves slightly glossy, +/- green. Common here on swampy flats, with scattered Eucalyptus resinifera subsp. hemilampra. AD Photos

Location: Halfway Creek to Kungala road, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale yellow-orange. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. Scattered in Melaleuca swamp, where emergent with some Eucalyptus ?tetrapleura and E. ?tereticornis. AD

Location: Corner Moleton Rd & Mountain Rd, Bagawa State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark rough to 7 metres, smooth creamy white above. Leaves +/- concolorous, glossy, dark green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus saligna in forest on broad ridge. AD Photos

Location: Mole Creek crossing on Moleton Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Laser height: 49.5 metres. Crown spread: 36.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 8.76 metres. Estimated age: 200+ years.  Large remnant tree, much larger than any surrounding trees. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus saligna.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 'Jack Feeny Tree', Old Coramba Rd, east of Megan, New South Wales.
Description: Laser height: 55.5 metres. Crown spread: 32.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 10.09 metres. Estimated age: 200+ years.  Massive remnant tree, much larger and older than surrounding regrowth forest. Growing with Eucalyptus saligna.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 'Tibbs Tree', Tibbs Tree Reserve off Lower Bielsdown Rd north of Dorrigo, New South Wales.
Description: Laser height: 50+ metres. Crown spread: 22.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 7.69 metres. Estimated age: 200+ years.  Large remnant tree surrounded by regrowth on slightly undulating ground. Growing with Eucalyptus saligna.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: North of Dorrigo on Megan Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark loosely rough on lower trunk, otherwise smooth, pale grey over white. Leaves conspicuously bluish and pruinose when new, maturing slightly glossy and green. Remnant trees on hillslope of orange loam. AD

Location: The Waterfall Way, immediately below Sherrard Falls, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, tightly held and finely fissured, grey with pale grey bleached patches. Leaves concolorous, glossy, green, variably scalloped. In ecotone between rainforest and eucalypt woodland on very steep slope with Eucalyptus saligna, E. microcorys and E. pilularis. AD Photos

Location: Point Lookout car park, New England National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark rough for 5 metres, thin but tightly held, smooth pale grey over white above. Leaves glossy, green. On rocky broad ridge in low forest with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD

Location: Beech Lookout, Cunnawarra National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall (supposedly to 80 metres in valley). Bark mostly smooth, tan over cream, some rough bark near base. Leaves glossy, mid green. In grassy forest dominated by Eucalyptus obliqua. AD

Location: Point Lookout Rd, south of Ebor, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, finely to moderately fissured, grey, with much attached lichen. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. On rolling hills in woodland with Eucalyptus nova-anglica and E. pauciflora and pauciflora. AD

Location: Point Lookout Rd, south of Ebor, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall, but mostly poor-formed. Bark rough to small branches, moderately fissured, grey. Leaves silvery and pruinose when new, maturing +/- glossy and dark green. On rolling hills in woodland with Eucalyptus acaciiformis and E. pauciflora and pauciflora. AD

Location: Warra National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, ribbony, orange-tan and grey. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. Stand of 50+ plants on creek flat in sphagnum swamp with some Eucalyptus stellulata and immediately surrounding swamp is E. nova-anglica and E. pauciflora and pauciflora. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Sunnyside Rd, north of Armidale, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 9 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately fissured, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, dark green. In grassy woodland on hill with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus caliginosa and E. ?melliodora. AD

Location: New England Hwy, north-east of Bendemeer, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very pale grey over white. Leaves very slightly glossy, blue-green, maturing green. Remnant roadside vegetation on rolling hills in woodland at 1003 metres ASL, with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus blakelyi, E. melliodora, E. bridgesiana and E. youmanii. AD

Location: New England Hwy, north-east of Bendemeer, New South Wales.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 7 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, grey over pale grey. Leaves slightly glossy, green.
