Remnant roadside vegetation on rolling hills in woodland at 1003 metres ASL, with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus elliptica, E. melliodora, E. bridgesiana and E. youmanii. AD

Location: New England Hwy, north-east of Bendemeer, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately finely fissured, dark grey with paler bleached patches. Leaves glossy, dark green. Branchlets, buds and new fruits pruinose. On broad hill in woodland with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus blakelyi, E. melliodora, E. prava, E. elliptica and E. youmanii. AD

Location: New England Hwy, north-east of Bendemeer, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey and pale orange. Leaves dull, blue-green. On broad hill in woodland with Angophora floribunda, E. blakelyi, E. elliptica, E. malacoxylon, E. melliodora and E. youmanii. AD

Location: Hanging Rock, north edge of 'town', New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over white. Leaves maturing glossy, green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora on rise adjacent to abandoned 'prase' mine. AD Photos

Location: Hanging Rock, north edge of 'town', New South Wales.
Description: Seedling coppice from roadside. Leaves narrowly elliptical, dull, blue-green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora on rise adjacent to abandoned 'prase' mine. AD

Location: Hanging Rock lookout, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately finely fissured, dark grey-brown. Leaves glossy, dark green. All adult parts non-pruinose. Otherwise typical of E. malacoxylon in leaves, habit, habitat, bark, buds, fruits and large, opposite, sessile, grey juvenile leaves. On top of granite escarpment in woodland with Eucalyptus caliginosa and E. melliodora. AD Photos

Location: Apsley Falls, car park at top of falls, Oxley Wild Rivers National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very pale grey over white. Leaves glossy, mid green. On granite escarpment edge with Eucalyptus laevopinea and some E. nobilis. AD Seeds

Location: Oxley Hwy, just west of Apsley Falls, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 16 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey. Leaves glossy, green. Large, round, green juvenile leaves. In disturbed remnant roadside vegetation in woodland in slight depression. AD

Location: Oxley Hwy, between Apsley Falls and Tia Falls turnoffs, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall, compact crown. Bark rough to small branches, finely fissured, +/- grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. Scattered clumps of remnant trees on rolling hills with a stringybark species. AD

Location: Tiara View Lookout, Tia Falls, New South Wales.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 8 metres tall. Bark rough for about half tree height, finely to moderately fissured, grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. On top of massive south facing cliffs with Eucalyptus caliginosa and E. melliodora. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Corner Oxley Hwy & Myrtle Scrub Rd, Cotton Bimbang National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 40 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 3 metres, then smooth, bluish grey over yellow-cream. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. In forest with some Eucalyptus microcorys. AD Photos

Location: 'Old Bottle Butt', Burrawan State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Laser height: 51.5 metres. Crown spread: 21.5 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 16.30 metres.  Adjacent to small creek in headwaters of broad valley with Eucalyptus pilularis dominant and some E. microcorys.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Old Pacific Hwy, just north of Lake Cathie turnoff, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and pale orange-cream. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. Common here in Melaleuca and Casuarina swampland. AD

Location: 'Bird Tree', Middle Brother State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Laser height: 58.5+ metres. Crown spread: 38.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 11.94 metres.  Pure stand, mostly regrowth with a few remnant trees.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Grey Gum Ridge Rd, Middle Brother State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and cream (much less colourful than adjacent E. propinqua with pale orange new bark). Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. In forest-woodland ecotone on steep slope with Eucalyptus carnea, E. acmenoides and E. propinqua. AD

Location: 'The Grandis', Stony Creek Rd, north of Bulahdelah, New South Wales.
Description: Laser height: 70.5 metres. Crown spread: 36.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 10.07 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Monkerai Rd, north of Stroud, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, grey-tan and cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. Scattered along creek flat with some Angophora floribunda and Casuarina cunninghamiana. AD

Location: Monkerai Rd, north of Stroud, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 16 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey over cream. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. On hillslope in remnant roadside vegetation with Corymbia maculata. AD

Location: East Gresford to Dugong Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout (rough like E. tereticornis/camaldulensis on lower trunk), pale grey over cream. Leaves maturing +/- dull, slightly blue-green. New growth and buds conspicuously pruinose. Dominant tree here on low hills in broad valley. AD

Location: North of Cessnock, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream. Leaves dull, pruinose at first, maturing slightly glossy, dark blue-green. On slightly undulating area with Eucalyptus moluccana and E. crebra. AD Seeds

Location: Glen Gallic Track, Wollemi National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Sprawling mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey. Leaves pruinose at first, maturing dull and +/- blue-green. Fruits somewhat variable, some with prominent annular disc (like this), some more E. dealbata-like. About 20+ plants scattered on sandstone ridge in woodland of Eucalyptus aff. nubilis, E. punctata and E. sparsifolia. AD, CANB Photos + seeds

Location: Glen Gallic Track, Wollemi National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, deeply fisured, hard, almost black. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets, buds and fruits variably pruinose. Dominant here, growing on sandstone ridge in woodland with Eucalyptus dealbata, E. punctata and E. sparsifolia. AD, CANB Seeds

Location: Glen Gallic Track, Wollemi National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 14 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey over pale orange-tan. Leaves discolorous, glossy and green above. Growing on sandstone ridge in woodland with Eucalyptus aff. nubilis, E. dealbata and E. sparsifolia. AD

Location: Glen Gallic Track, Wollemi National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Sprawling mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey. Leaves pruinose at first, maturing dull and +/- blue-green. Fruits somewhat variable, some with prominent annular disc, some more E. dealbata-like. 100+ plants scattered over at least one kilometre, on sandstone ridge in woodland of Eucalyptus aff. nubilis, E. punctata and E. sparsifolia. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Jerrys Plains, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough to 100 mm diameter branches, finely fissured, grey and pale grey. Leaves very slightly glossy, +/- green. A few trees in roadside remnant woodland with Eucalyptus dawsonii dominant. AD

Location: Wollombi Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, mottled grey over cream (like C. maculata). Leaves dull to slightly glossy, green. In open forest in creek gully with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus punctata and E. eugenioides. AD

Location: Sawpit Track, Pokolbin State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 22 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. Scattered in open forest on sandstone ridge with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus punctata, E. prominula and Allocasuarina torulosa. AD

Location: East of Ellalong towards Quorrobolong, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall, crown narrow. Bark rough to small branches, moderately fissured and somewhat stringy, grey. Leaves +/- dull, slightly blue-green. In open remnant forest with Eucalyptus fibrosa. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Quorrobolong, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. On slight rise with Angophora costata, Eucalyptus globoidea, E. resinifera subsp. resinifera and E. punctata. AD

Location: Heaton State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, +/- white. Crown leaves (mostly intermediate) +/- dull, green. On steep south facing slope with Eucalyptus saligna, E. acmenoides, E. ?siderophloia and Syncarpia. AD Photos

Location: Leggets Drive, south of Kurri Kurri, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. Common here in low open woodland with Angophora bakeri and Eucalyptus capitellata. AD

Location: North side of Cessnock racecourse, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 7 metres tall, crown heavy. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Leaves +/- glossy, dark green. Common here in dense low woodland on level topography with Eucalyptus capitellata. AD

Location: Maitland to Paterson Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, tan over cream. Leaves slightly glossy, green. Growing on low rolling hills with Corymbia maculata and Eucalyptus crebra. AD

Location: Near Hungry Hill, north-east of Dunns Creek, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey over cream. Leaves discolorous, glossy and green above. On hill at 500 metres ASL in low forest with Corymbia maculata, Eucalyptus fibrosa, E. carnea and E. acmenoides. AD

Location: Soldiers Rd, Pelican Flat, Lake Macquarie, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, grey. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. In level swampy area in dense scrub with Casuarina glauca, Melaleuca and Livistona. AD

Location: Naru St adjacent to airstrip, Pelican Flat, Lake Macquarie, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to about 120 mm diameter branches. leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. Dominant here in woodland stand with some Angophora costata. Nearby, Eucalyptus robusta is common on somewhat more swampy sites. AD

Location: Corner Wyee Rd and Gosford Rd, Wyee, New South Wales.
Description: Scraggy tree to 8 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately to coarsely fissured, grey-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. Mostly dehisced fruits. Growing in dense low woodland with Corymbia gummifera and Eucalyptus haemastoma. AD Seeds

Location: Dickson Rd, north of Jilliby, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 30 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very pale grey over pale orange. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. On lower slopes of valley in remnant roadside forest with Corymbia maculata, Eucalyptus umbra and E. ?siderophloia. AD

Location: Nepean River at Blaxland Crossing Reserve, Wallacia, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 28 metres tall. Bark rough and loose for 2 to 3 metres, then smooth, tan over cream. Leaves dull, blue-green, new growth pruinose. On river flat in partially cleared forest with Angophora subvelutina and Eucalyptus tereticornis subsp. tereticornis. AD Photos

Location: Bents Basin, river flat 100 m east of picnic area, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. New growth conspicuously pruinose and silvery. Adult leaves maturing green. Scattered on sandy river flat with Acacia dominant and some Eucalyptus elata. AD

Location: National Pass trail below Wentworth Falls, Blue Mountains National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, +/- blue-green. Growing as partial emergent in rainforest scrub on near-sheer south facing sandstone cliff. Some Angophora costata,Eucalyptus saligna and E. punctata adjacent on slightly drier sites.  AD Photos + seeds

Location: Wentworth Pass trail near Wentworth Falls town, Blue Mountains National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 40 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, mostly creamy white. Leaves discolorous, green. In deep valley below south facing sandstone cliffs in tall open forest with massive Syncarpia and some Angophora costata and Eucalyptus ?pilularis.  AD

Location: Great Western Hwy, adjacent to Browntown Oval, Blue Mountains, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark somewhat loosely rough for 1 metre, otherwise smooth throughout, pinkish and white. Leaves slightly glossy, green. In remnant roadside dense woodland with Eucalyptus sieberi, E. sparsifolia and some E. oreades.  AD

Location: Castlereagh Hwy, just north of Great Western Highway, east of Wallerawang, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very pale grey to white. Leaves +/- dull, slightly blue-green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus rossii on shallow soil on rise in woodland, with some E. dives.  AD Photos

Location: Castlereagh Hwy, just south of Running Stream, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, tan-grey over pale grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. In broad valley on lower slopes with Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. viminalis, E. dives and E. macrorhyncha subsp. cannonii. AD

Location: Castlereagh Hwy, just south of Ilford in front of Ilford Catholic Church, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over powdery white. Leaves very slightly glossy, +/- blue-green. Distinct from E. lactea here in its much narrower juvenile leaves and its smaller , narrower and duller adult leaves. On broad rise in woodland with Eucalyptus lactea, E. macrorhyncha subsp. cannonii and E. tenella.  AD Photos

Location: Bylong Rd, north-east of Ilford, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale orange-cream. Leaves discolorous, glossy, dark green. On hills in low forest with Eucalyptus blakelyi, E. macrorhyncha subsp. cannonii and E. sparsifolia.  AD

Location: Bylong Rd, south-west of Kandos in Clandulla State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale yellow-orange. Leaves +/- dull, blue-green. Dominant in broad depression in sandy soil with Eucalyptus mannifera and E. tenella.  AD

Location: Track into Dunns Swamp, east of Rylstone, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, ribbony. Leaves +/- dull, blue-green maturing green. Dominant here in broad valley on swampy ground surrounded by Eucalyptus ?lactea, E. viminalis subsp. viminalis and E. dives.  AD

Location: East of Olinda, Wollemi National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately fissured, grey-brown. Leaves dull, blue-green. Growing on sandy soil below sandstone outcrops in woodland with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus rossii and E. dives.  AD

Location: East of Olinda, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 14 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very pale grey over pale orange-yellow. Leaves +/- dull, blue-green. Growing on sandy soil with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus rossii and E. macrorhyncha subsp. cannonii.  AD

Location: East of Olinda, New South Wales.
Description: Seedling growing on road verge (with many others of the same). leaves dull, blue-green. Growing on sandy soil with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus rossii and E. macrorhyncha subsp. cannonii.  AD

Location: East of Olinda (outside Wollemi National Park), New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to 60 mm diameter branches, moderately to finely fissured, grey-brown. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Growing on slight rise in woodland with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus rossii, E. lactea and E. dives.  AD

Location: East of Olinda (outside Wollemi National Park), New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately to moderately finely fissured, grey-brown. Leaves dull, blue-green. Growing on level topography in open forest with Eucalyptus rossii, E. rubida subsp. rubida and E. ?lactea.  AD Seeds

Location: Wattle Flat Heritage Lands North, New South Wales.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough, stringy, deeply stringy, grey over red-brown. Leaves juvenile, strongly pruinose. In woodland with Eucalyptus blakelyi and some E. goniocalyx subsp. goniocalyx and E. polyanthemos subsp. polyanthemos. AD Seeds

Location: Entrance to Wattle Flat Heritage Lands North, New South Wales.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 8 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately finely fissured, grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. On low hill in woodland with Eucalyptus blakelyi, E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha, E. melliodora and E. polyanthemos subsp. polyanthemos. AD

Location: Orange View Lookout, Canobolas Way, Mount Canobolas Scientific Conservation Area, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 14 metres tall. Bark ribbony and loosely rough for a few metres, otherwise smooth, tan over greenish cream and pale grey. In dense woodland on side of knoll with Eucalyptus dives. AD

Location: Mount Canobolas summit, Mount Canobolas Scientific Conservation Area, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pink-tan over white. Buds variably pruinose. On rounded summit in low woodland with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD

Location: Mount Canobolas, south-east of summit, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 18 metres tall. Bark loosely ribbony rough near base, otherwise smooth, pale green-grey over cream. Leaves glossy, light green. On steep east-facing slope with Eucalyptus canobolensis and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD

Location: Boyd River crossing on Kanangra Rd, Boyd Plateau, Kanangra Boyd National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Erect-trunked tree to 25 metres tall. Bark rough to medium branches, then very ribbony, moderately-fissured, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, mid green. Along flts of creek in low open forest with Eucalyptus dalrympleana subsp. dalrympleana and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD Seeds

Location: Boyd River camping ground, Boyd Plateau, Kanangra Boyd National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark variable, from mostly smooth to rough to half tree height. Leaves slightly glossy, green, crown slightly bluish. Scattered in open forest on gritty sand with Eucalyptus macarthurii, E. dalrympleana subsp. dalrympleana and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Kalang Falls walk track, Kanangra Boyd National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 6 to 20 metres tall. Bark rough to small to medium branches, conspicuously smooth above. Leaves concolorous, glossy, green. On very rocky, steep ridge with some Eucalyptus aff. radiata, E. sieberi and E. stricta. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Kanangra Rd, Kanangra Boyd National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, greenish grey over cream. Leaves glossy, mid-green. Scattered trees emergent in heath with Eucalyptus stricta and E. aff. radiata. AD

Location: North of Richlands on Goulburn - Oberon Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately-fissured, slightly stringy, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, dark green. On creek flat with Eucalyptus stelulata, E. rubida subsp. rubida and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora nearby. AD

Location: Just north of Richlands on Goulburn - Oberon Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 14 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 metres, moderately fissured, smooth above, pinkish grey over cream. Leaves concolorous to very slightly discolorous, glossy, green. First trees of this seen on this trip, in pure stand in wide valley flat, with Eucalyptus aggregata nearby but not associated. AD

Location: Wombeyan Caves Rd, near Wollondilly Lookout, Nattai National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey and pale orange. Leaves discolorous, slightly glossy and green above. In low forest on hill with Eucalyptus agglomerata, E. smithii and Angophora costata subsp. costata. AD

Location: Wombeyan Caves Rd, nr. Wollondilly Lookout, Nattai National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 15 metres tall. Bark rough for 3 to 4 metres, moderately finely-fissured, dark grey, smooth above, grey over cream. In low forest on hill with Eucalyptus agglomerata, E. punctata and Angophora costata subsp. costata. AD

Location: Nr. Wanganderry on Wombeyan Caves Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 28 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey-tan over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. Juvenile leaves conspicuously large and green. In broad flat in remnant roadside forest (presumably swampy). AD

Location: Corner Wombeyan Caves Rd & Soapy Flat Rd, west-north-west of Mittagong, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 10 metres tall. Bark rough for two thirds tree height, moderately fissured, then smooth above. Leaves glossy, green. On edge of broad river flat with Eucalyptus amplifolia subsp. amplifolia and E. ovata subsp. ovata. AD

Location: Wombeyan Caves Rd, west-north-west of Mittagong, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall, umbragatous. Bark rough to 100 to 150 mm diameter branches, moderately to finely-fissured, grey with pale grey bleached patches. Leaves very slightly discolorous, glossy, green, with conspicuous lenticels. Remnant roadside and paddock trees in largely cleared landscape. AD

Location: Paddys River crossing on Hume Hwy, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough to medium-sized branches, moderately-fissured, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, green. On river edge in disturbed woodland, in +/- pure stand, with Eucalyptus cinerea subsp. cinerea, E. dives and E. mannifera subsp. gullickii on higher ground. AD

Location: Paddys River crossing on Hume Hwy, New South Wales.
Description: Scraggy tree to 6 metres tall. Bark rough and stringy throughout. Crown silvery. All adult parts very pruinose. On thin soil over granite, above river in woodland with Eucalyptus dives and E. mannifera subsp. gullickii. AD Photos

Location: Paddys River crossing on Hume Hwy, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white. Leaves slightly glossy, slightly blue-green. On thin soil over granite, above river in woodland with Eucalyptus cinerea subsp. cinerea and E. mannifera subsp. gullickii. AD Photos

Location: Paddys River crossing on Hume Hwy, New South Wales.
Description: Seedling from nearby ground (old track). Leaves long-elliptical, dull, blue-green, not pruinose. On thin soil over granite, above river in woodland with Eucalyptus cinerea subsp. cinerea and E. mannifera subsp. gullickii. AD

Location: 0.5 km north of Windellama towards Bungonia, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 6 metres tall. Bark loosely rough for 1 metre, then smooth, tan-grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. A few remnant trees on slight rise in open grassy woodland with some scattered Eucalyptus macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha and E. mannifera. AD Seeds

Location: Hi-Quality clay quarry site, south of Windellama, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 3.5 metres tall. Bark Smooth throughout, ribbony. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. In open woodland dominated by Eucalyptus mannifera and with some E. cinerea subsp. cinerea. AD

Location: South of Windellama, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 11 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very pale grey over white. Leaves slightly glossy, very slightly blue-green to dark green. Dominant tree here, on clayey soil in slightly undulating topography with Eucalyptus cinerea subsp. cinerea, E. dives, E. rossii and E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha. AD

Location: South of Windellama, New South Wales.
Description: Heavily-crowned tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough and stringy throughout. All parts highly pruinose when new. On clayey soil in slightly undulating topography with Eucalyptus mannifera subsp. mannifera, E. dives, E. rossii and E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha. AD

Location: North-west edge of Morton National Park, Mongalowe road, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over pale yellow-cream. Leaves becoming slightly glossy, very slightly blue-green. In woodland with Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora, E. dives, E. rossii and E. moorei subsp. moorei. AD

Location: Half Moon Rd, north of Mongalowe, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee 2.5 metres tall. Bark smooth and ribbony throughout. Leaves glossy and green above. One clump in poor health, in Allocasuarina nana heathland with scattered Eucalyptus pauciflora susbp. pauciflora, E. mannifera subsp. gullickii, E. rubida subsp. rubida and E. radiata subsp. radiata. AD Photos

Location: Bulee Lookout area, Nerriga - Sassafras road, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough for c. 1 metre, smooth above. Leaves highly glossy, green. On massive sandstone outcrops in open woodland with some Eucalyptus agglomerata, E. sieberi and E. smithii. AD Seed + photos

Location: Bulee Lookout area, Nerriga - Sassafras road, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough for 3 to 4 metres, moderately finely fissured, grey, smooth above. Leaves glossy, green. On massive sandstone outcrops in open woodland with some Eucalyptus agglomerata, E. sieberi and E. triflora. AD

Location: Nr Tianjarra Falls, Nowra - Sassafras road, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall. Bark rough to small to medium branches, moderately finely fissured, grey. Leaves +/- glossy, dark olive green. In low forest in undulating area with Eucalyptus sieberi and Corymbia gummifera. AD

Location: Jerrawangala Lookout, Jerrawangala National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Dense-crowned tree to 5 metres tall. Bark rough to small twigs, moderately deeply fissured and stringy, grey-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. On sandstone escarpment in low scrubby woodland with Corymbia gummifera, Eucalyptus sieberi, E. racemosa and E. botryoides. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Jerrawangala Lookout, Jerrawangala National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark rough to 100 to 120 mm diameter, moderately fissured, grey-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and mid-green above. Below and on sandstone cliff/escarpment in +/- pure forest stand. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Turpentine Rd, just east of Braidwood Rd, Tomerong area, New South Wales.
Description: Whipstick mallee 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves thick, +/- dull, green. Most stems of plant with juvenile leaves. One clump in heathy clearing dominated by Banksia ericifolia on thin soil over sandstone. AD Photos + seeds

Location: 'Old Blotchy', off 18 Mile Peg Rd, Murramarang National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Laser height: 58.5 metres. Crown spread: 30.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 10.76 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Informat car park at 'Old Blotchy', off 18 Mile Peg Rd, Murramarang National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 30+ metres tall. Bark rough for 1 metre, then smooth, pale blue-grey over cream. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. In tall forest on moderate slope with Syncarpia, Corymbia maculata, E. paniculata and E. botryoides (with E. saligna influence). AD

Location: Princes Hwy, Murramarang National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 30 metres tall. Bark rough to small twigs, moderately to finely fissured and somewhat flaky, light grey. Leaves +/- dull, slightly blue green. In mixed eucalypt forest near swampy creek with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus scias, E. globoidea, E. saligna and E. piperita subsp. urceolaris. AD Photos

Location: Mount Sugarloaf, north of Kings Hwy, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, tan over pale greenish yellow. leaves slightly glossy, dark green. Large, +/- pure stand on very steep north slope of rock scree with some Eucalyptus sieberi, E. dendromorpha, E. smithii and E. fraxinoides on edges of stand. AD, CANB Photos + seeds

Location: Kings Hwy at end of upper emergency ramp, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 to 3 metres, dark grey-brown, then smooth, cream, very scribbled. Leaves glossy, mid-green. On sleep slopes in forest with Eucalyptus sieberi and E. cypellocarpa. AD

Location: Braidwood - Araluen Rd, nr. Stony Creek, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 20 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 3 m, then smooth, ribbony, pale grey over cream. leaves dull, blue-green, whole crown greyish. On low hill with Acacia melanoxylon, Eucalyptus radiata subsp. radiata, E. viminalis subsp. viminalis and E. melliodora. AD

Location: Majors Creek (creek), about half way between Majors Creek (town) and Araluen North, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 28 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 m, then smooth, pale grey over cream. Leaves pruinose and grey initially, becoming dull, slightly blue-green. On river flat with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus melliodora and E. tereticornis subsp. tereticornis. AD

Location: Apple Tree Flat, north-west of Araluen, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over nearly white. Leaves +/- glossy, dark green. On river flat and adjacent footslopes with Eucalyptus kartzoffiana and E. melliodora. AD

Location: Ca. 5 km south-east of Araluen, adjacent to Araluen Creek, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 30 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, finely fissured, grey with pale grey bleached patches. Leaves moderately discolorous, glossy and dark green above. Above creek on steep slope with Angophora floribunda and Eucalyptus melliodora. AD

Location: Tinderry Rd, north-west of Jingera, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 11 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately fissured, dark grey-brown. Leaves glossy, dark green. Remnant trees in broad depression in +/- pure stand. AD

Location: Tinderry Rd, north-west of Jingera, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 16 metres tall. Bark loosely rough near base, otherwise smooth, grey over cream and pinkish. Leaves maturing glossy and green. Branchlets slightly pruinose. On undulating hills with Eucalyptus bridgesiana and E. dives. AD

Location: Tinderry Rd, north-west of Jingera, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches (c. 80 mm diameter), moderately finely fissured and tessellated, grey. Leaves glossy and dark green. On undulating hills with Eucalyptus dives and E. rubida subsp. rubida. AD

Location: Tinderry Range, south end, north of Tinderry Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Mallees to 7 metres tall (mostly burnt 1 to 2 years ago). Leaves highly glossy, green. Dominant on massive granite boulder ridge with some Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora and E. dalrympleana subsp. dalrympleana. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Tinderry Rd, east of Michelago, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately fissured, grey. Leaves dull, grey-green. Branchlets pruinose. On very steep north slope in woodland with Eucalyptus rossii and E. melliodora. AD Photos

Location: Mt Dowling Fire Trail, east of Bredbo, Mt Dowling Nature Reserve, New South Wales.
Description: Whipstick mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, bronze-brown. Leaves very pruinose, fully juvenile. 10+ plants on high stony ridge, as understorey in woodland of Eucalyptus macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha and E. mannifera. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Mt Dowling Fire Trail, east of Bredbo, Mt Dowling Timber Reserve, New South Wales.
Description: Thin-stemmed mallee to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over coppery orange. Most plants fully juvenile-leaved. Common here on steep stony ridges, in woodland of Eucalyptus macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha and E. mannifera. AD

Location: Wadbilliga Rd, near Tuross River crossing, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 6 metres tall, crown rounded and moderately dense. Bark rough and thin for 1 metre, then smooth, dark grey and tan. Leaves +/- dull, green. On undulating low ground near river with some Eucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora, E. stellulata and E. viminalis subsp. viminalis. AD Photos

Location: Nimmitabel - Bega Rd, west of Pipers Lookout, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 30+ metres tall. Bark rough for 2/3 tree height, moderately finely fissured, dark grey-brown, smooth and ribbony above. Leaves glossy, green. In forest on broad hilltop with Eucalyptus elata, E. nitens and E. fastigata. AD

Location: Nunnock Swamp, just east of New Line Rd, South East Forests National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Robust tree-like mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Mainly intermediate leaf canopy, but some adult leaves present. Dominant along swamp margin with someEucalyptus pauciflora subsp. pauciflora and E. viminalis subsp. viminalis. AD Photos + seeds

Location: 50 metres down Stoves Rd from Mt Darragh Rd, Cathcart State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 38 metres tall. Bark rough on lower trunk, gradually becoming ribbony and smooth. Leaves glossy, dark green. In forest on undulating hills with various other eucalypt species. AD Photos

Location: Ca. 500 m downstream from creek crossing on Mistake Fire Trail, just above junction with Desert Creek, South East Forests NP, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 10 metres tall. Bark rsmooth throughout, orange-tan and slightly greenish grey. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. In canyon on almost cliff of conglomerate, with Angophora floribunda, Eucalyptus agglomerata and E. sieberi. AD, CANB

Location: Ford Park, Merimbula Beach, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to 80 mm diameter branches, moderately deeply fissured but +/- soft, brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. Behind first sand dune in dense pure stand. AD

Location: Ca. 100 m east of Mt Imlay Summit, mallee tagged '44', New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 9 metres tall. Bark rough for c. 1 metre, then smooth. Leaves very slightly discolorous, glossy, light green. No buds or fruits present. Some dieback since last visit. On very steep (cliff-like) rocky south-facing slope, as emergent in dense shrubs, with some Eucalyptus fraxinoides and E. sieberi. AD Photos

Location: Ca. 100 m east of Mt Imlay Summit, mallee tagged '29', New South Wales. (15 m from D.Nicolle 6331).
Description: Mallee to 9 metres tall. Bark rough for c. 1 metre, then smooth. Leaves very slightly discolorous, glossy, light green. No buds or fruits present. Some dieback since last visit. On very steep (cliff-like) rocky south-facing slope, as emergent in dense shrubs, with some Eucalyptus fraxinoides and E. sieberi.  AD Photos

Location: Just inside Victorian border on Bonang - Delegate Rd, Victoria.
Description: Tree 10 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, ribbony, grey over cream. Leaves dull to slightly glossy, slightly blue-green. On edge of valley with Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. viminalis and some E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora, E. stellulata and Acacia melanoxylon. AD Seeds

Location: Kosciuszko National Park, north-west of Snodgrass Plain, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, grey-green. Branchlets pruinose. Plants in poor health (prolonged drought?) and few buds and no fruits seen. On very rocky ridge with Callitris, Acacia and Eucalyptus nortonii (also in poor health).  AD

Location: Corrowong Creek, Brown Camp road, New South Wales.
Description: Spreading tree 10 metres tall. Leaves slightly glossy, slightly blue-green. In full flower. Along creek with scattered Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. viminalis and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD

Location: Benambra - Suggan Buggan Rd, south-west of Suggan Buggan, Victoria.
Description: Tree 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over powdery white. Leaves dull very slightly glossy, slightly blue-green. On hillside in woodland with Eucalyptus dives and E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha. AD

Location: Buchan Creek picnic area at Native Dog Flat, Alpine National Park, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 22.0 metres. Crown spread: 19.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 4.60 metres.  Numerous similar-sized trees on swampy flat with some Eucalyptus rubida subsp. rubida, Eucalyptus dalrympleana subsp. dalrymopleana and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Limestone Rd, tributary of Mount Leinster Creek, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 14 metres tall. Bark rough for 3 to 4 m then smooth. Leaves +/- glossy, +/- green. In creek headwaters with Eucalyptus stellulata and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD

Location: Great Alpine Way, north-west of Mt St Bernard, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 30 metres tall. Bark rough for 1/2 tree height, moderately fissured, grey-brown, smooth above, grey/cream. Leaves +/- glossy, blue-green. On very steep slope with Eucalyptus dalrympleana subsp. 'alpine' and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD Seeds

Location: Tookayerta Creek crossing on Goolwa to Strathalbyn road, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately to deeply fissured, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, green. Along creek with some Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. camaldulensis and E. leucoxylon subsp. leucoxylon. AD

Location: Nangkita Rd, Nangkita, South Australia.
Description: Poor-formed trees to 8 metres tall. A few remnant trees on roadside, with Eucalyptus cosmophylla nearby. AD

Location: Morgan Rd, east of Ironbank, South Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallees to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves slightly glossy, slightly blue-green. On steep stony hill in low scrubby forest with Eucalyptus obliqua and E. leucoxylon subsp. leucoxylon. AD

Location: Corner Morgan Rd and Scott Creek Rd, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 metre, loose and platy, then smooth above, white. Leaves moderately glossy, green. In valley with some Eucalyptus obliqua and E. leucoxylon subsp. leucoxylon. AD

Location: Old Mt Barker Rd below Eagle on the Hill, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 3 metres, thin, smooth above, tan over cream. Leaves glossy, green. On sleep slopes and ridges in woodland with Eucalyptus leucoxylon subsp. leucoxylon. AD

Location: Balladonia to Culver track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall.  A little rough bark near base, smooth above, pale grey over white. Leaves glossy, green. On powdery grey loam with Eucalyptus gracilis, E. conglobata subsp. conglobata and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. (E. urna and E. fraseri common further north on track). PERTH

Location: Balladonia to Culver track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall.  Bark smooth throughout, grey over greenish-grey. Leaves dull and slightly blue-green at first, maturing glossy and dark green. On powdery grey loam with Eucalyptus gracilis, E. melanoxylon and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. (E. fraseri and E. urna common further north on track). PERTH

Location: Gora Rd, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall.  Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, grey. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Buds waxy. In mallee shrubland on pale grey gravelly clay with mallee Eucalyptus occidentalis, E. conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. micranthera, E. leptocalyx and E. uncinata. PERTH

Location: Gora Rd, N of Mica Hill, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall.  Bark more or less smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, dark green. Scattered on very thin white sand over limestone with Eucalyptus cooperiana dominant, also some E. conglobata subsp. conglobata and E. discreta. PERTH

Location: Summit of hill at NE end of Russell Range, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee to 1.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony. Leaves glossy and green. Scattered over slopes and summit of decomposing granite hill in low dense scrub with some Eucalyptus discreta and E. tumida. CANB, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: W slope of hill at NE end of Russell Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 1.5 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout. Common on slopes of granite hill with Eucalyptus tumida, E. tetraptera and Hakea species. PERTH + seed

Location: W slope of hill at NE end of Russell Range, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee one metre tall.  Single mallee clump on slopes of granite hill with Eucalyptus discreta, E. tumida and E. tetraptera. PERTH

Location: NE end of Russell Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark mosty smooth, grey. No parts waxy. Leaves dull, blue-green, maturing slightly glossy and green. In mallee shrubland on white sand with Eucalyptus conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. tumida, E. discreta and E. uncinata. PERTH

Location: Near Kangawarie Rockhole, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 or 2 metres, smooth above, pale grey. Leaves glossy, green, with scattered oil glands. Common on powdery grey loam over limestone with Eucalyptus yalatensis on edge of grassy plain. AD, CANB, PERTH + seed

Location: Track to Kangawarie Rockhole, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately-fissured, grey. leaves dull, blue-grey. Common here on red loam over limestone with Eucalyptus aff. laevis. PERTH

Location: Tower Peak summit and ridge, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee, erect-stemmmed and emergent, to 4 metres tall. Growing on upper stepp west-facing slopes in low shrubland with Eucalyptus tetraptera. Photo Specimen Only

Location: Sheoak Hill to Tookle-Jenna Rock track, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Leaves glossy, mid-green. A few plants on white sand in dense mallee shrubland with Eucalyptus angulosa, E. cooperiana, E. leptocalyx, E. extrica and E. uncinata. AD, PERTH

Location: Sheoak Hill to Tookle-Jenna Rock track, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet, burnt stems to 6 metres tall, new seedling to 3 metres. Bark more or less smooth throughout, dull, greyish. Leaves maturing glossy and green but dull and bluish at first. Buds and fruits consistently and distinctively waxy. Dense stand on slight slope of grey clay-loam with Eucalyptus brachycalyx, E. conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. leptocalyx subsp. leptocalyx, E. cooperiana and E. uncinata. AD, PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Sheoak Hill to Tookle-Jenna Rock track, just N of Tookle-Jenna Rock, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 9 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves maturing glossy and green. On puffy grey loam with Eucalyptus brachycalyx and E. oleosa subsp. ampliata. PERTH

Location: Tookle-Jenna Rock, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 12 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 3 metres, smooth above, white bark powdery. Leaf width variable here, this specimen near broadest. More or less pure stand on rise of grey loam. PERTH

Location: Junction of Fisheries Rd and Tookle-Jenna to Pt Malcolm track, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 4 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout. Leaves with moderately dense reticulation with scattered to numerous island and intersectional oil glands. Buds waxy. Flowers mid-yellow. On grey clay-loam with Eucalyptus leptocalyx and E. uncinata. AD, PERTH + photos

Location: Telegraph Track, N of Mt Pasley, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 1.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves held erect, glossy, green. Flowers creamy-white. Scattered in low shrubland on white sand with Eucalyptus extrica. AD, PERTH + photos

Location: Telegraph Track, N of Mt Pasley, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. Scattered clumps in very broad swales of white sand, emergent in very low Banksia heath. PERTH

Location: Telegraph Track, Mt Arid to Pt Malcolm section, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Leaves glossy, green. Flowers creamy-white. Emergent in very low shrubland with Eucalyptus extrica and E. micranthera. AD, PERTH

Location: Telegraph Track, Mt Arid to Pt Malcolm section, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. In broad shallow gully on white sand with mallee Eucalyptus occidentalis and E. micranthera. PERTH

Location: Near Poison Creek mouth on Poison Creek Rd, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall, crown dense. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey. Leaves maturing glossy and dark green. Small clumps behind coastal dunes, emergent in low Banksia heath. PERTH

Location: N of Mt Arid, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey. Leaves glossy, green. In very broad and shallow valley on white sand with Eucalyptus occidentalis and E. extrica. PERTH + photos

Location: Mt Arid summit, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: True mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, dark green. Common on upper slopes between granite domes with Eucalyptus ligulata subsp. ligulata and E. dorotoxylon. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: E side of Mt Arid on upper slopes, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, but stems thin. A few plants on very steep upper east slope of granite dome with Eucalyptus ligulata subsp. ligulata and E. lehmannii subsp. parallela. CANB, PERTH

Location: E side of Mt Arid on upper slopes, Cape Arid Nat. Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey. Common on upper slopes and summit, between massive granite domes with Eucalyptus lehmannii subsp. parallela and E. dorotoxylon. PERTH

Location: Merivale Rd, 4.2 km from Orleans Bay Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall, in poor health (nearly dead). Single mallee in remnant roadside vegetation with Eucalyptus conglobata subsp. conglobata, E. leptocalyx, E. extrica and E. micranthera. PERTH

Location: Ridgelands Rd, N of Conginup, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee, terminal crown, to 9 metres tall. Bark lososly rough for 1 metre, otherwise smooth, pale grey and cream. Leaves more or less glossy, green. Scattered clumps on broad low rises in Banksia shrubland. PERTH

Location: Howick Rd, between Meyer Rd and Coolinup Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee to 4 metres tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. Flowers pink. Common here on level topography of gravelly sand with Eucalyptus leptocalyx subsp. petilipes and E. uncinata. AD, PERTH

Location: Howick Rd, between Mt Ney Rd and Coolinup Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark srough for up to 2 metres in taller and larger mallees, tightly-held, thin, grey; smooth above. Leaves becoming glossy and dark green. Buds variable with wax, from not to slightly, some with new growth, branchlets and leaves somewhat waxy. In mallee scrub with Eucalyptus leptocalyx subsp. petilipes, E. indurata and E. uncinata. AD, PERTH

Location: Howick Rd, between Mt Ney Rd and Coolinup Rd, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey over cream-tan. Leaves glossy, dark green. In mallee scrub with Eucalyptus leptocalyx subsp. petilipes, E. varia, E. uncinata, E. flocktoniae subsp. hebes and E. kessellii subsp. eugnosta. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Old quarry at end of Quarry Rd, NE of Esperance, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, glossy, coppery-brown. Leaves glossy, dark green. A few clumps on S side of granite hill between exposed granite with some Eucalyptus pleurocarpa. AD, PERTH + seed

Location: Old quarry at end of Quarry Rd, NE of Esperance, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Scattered clumps at south base of granite hill with Eucalyptus incrassata, E. uncinata and E. pleurocarpa. AD, PERTH

Location: Helms Arboretum, bush section, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee 1 metre tall. Leaves variable in size here, but generally intermediate in size between tetraptera to west and sweedmaniana to east. Flowers pink. Growing in frequently-burnt low shrubland with Eucalyptus incrassata and some E. pleurocarpa. PERTH

Location: Helms Arboretum, bush section, Western Australia.
Description: Dense mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth , but becoming thin rough on lower stems. Scattered clumps on white sand in low shrubland on level topography. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus kessellii subsp. kessellii - subsp. eugnosta intergrade
Location: Sunrise Hill Rd, E of Salmon Gums, Western Australia.
Description: Many-stemmed and single-stemmed here, to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, grey. On slight slope of grey clay with Eucalyptus eremophila, E. valens, E. kumarlensis, E. leptocalyx subsp. leptocalyx and E. urna. PERTH + seeds

Location: Kumarl Rd, just E of Coolgardie - Esperance Hwy, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee  to 4.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony, pale grey-tan. Leaves glossy, green, with numerous oil glands. In pure stand as scattered mallees in open sedge shrubland on red clay-loam with limestone. Nearby on deeper soil is Eucalyptus diptera and E. prolixa. AD, PERTH + seeds

Location: Lookout on Eyre Highway (looking towards Wilson Bluff), South Australia.
Description: Mallee 1 metre tall. Co-dominant here forming low open shrubland on limestone escarpment with Eucalyptus yalatensis. Photo Specimen Only

Location: Coxes Scrub CP, Ashborne-Goolwa Rd, South Australia.
Description: Scrubby mallee to 4 metres tall. Forming shrubland on slight sandstone rise with Eucalyptus baxteri and E. fasciculosa. AD

Location: Corner Razorback and Sidler Rds, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. In roadside vegetation with Eucalyptus fasciculosa. AD

Location: Summit of St Mary Peak, Wilpena Pound Range, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over white. Leaves dull, blue-green. Co-dominant on massive sandstone with Eucalyptus goniocalyx subsp. exposa around summit, but on slightly more sheltered sites. AD Seed + photos

Location: Summit of St Mary Peak, Wilpena Pound Range, South Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth throughout, pale grey over yellow-cream, but variable and some rough bark on larger plants. Leaves mostly glossy, olive-green. Branchlets and fruits variable pruinose. Dominant on the most exposed sandstone ridges, with some Eucalyptus flindersii. AD Seed + photos

Location: Wilpena Creek, Wilpena resort area, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 40+ metres tall. Branchlets slightly pruinose. Dominant tree forming forest along creek. AD Seed + photos

Location: E side Wearing Gorge, northern Flinders Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Tumbledown mallee to 5 metres tall. Pure stand, on slightly undulating limestony soil. First of this species seen when coming from south. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Balconoona, just inside Gammon Ranges Nat. Park, South Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout in some, with rough basal bark in others. Plants fully juvenile. Pure stands on footslopes and some higher slopes in open mallee on stony powdery loam. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Yerila Creek, W of Lake Callabonna, South Australia.
Description: Poor-formed, usually multi-stemmed trees to 9 metres tall. Bark rough to 5 to 15 cm diameter, smooth and white above. Leaves dull, grey-green. Along creek channel and immediately adjacent floodplain, in pure stand. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Darby's Bore, S of Innamincka on new Strzelecki Track, South Australia.
Description: Tree 7 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, tessellated, grey-brown. Leaves +/- concolorous, dull, green. Buds scurfy. On sides and in swales of red sand dunes, as very scattered trees. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Cooper Creek at Innamincka causeway, South Australia.
Description: Causeway flooded and impassable. Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. arida along main channel, with E. coolabah on edges and on surrounding floodplain. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Dig Tree, Nappa Merrie Station, Cooper Creek, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Dominant on grey clay banks and floodplain, forming open woodland. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Cluny Sandhills, SE of Bedourie, Queensland.
Description: Tree 5 metres tall. All plants of this here are in full bud. On red sand dunes, and sand between dunes, as scattered trees in low shrubland. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Diamantina Development Rd, between Dajarra and Boulia, Queensland.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white. Leaves dull, blue-green. In flower.  On broad stony rise with Eucalyptus normantonensis. AD Photos

Location: Dajarra - Mt Isa Rd, just north of Urandangi turnoff, Queensland.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Branchlets pruinose. Leaves slightly glossy, slightly blue-green.  On stony red sandy loam with Corymbia terminalis, Eucalyptus gamophylla and E. gamophylla - E. odontocarpa intergrades. AD

Location: Hills c. 500 metres north of track to Warrigal Waterhole, c. 10 km east of Mt Isa, Queensland.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green.  On quartz outcrop and scree on north slope of hill with Corymbia apsera, C. capricornia and Eucalyptus leucophloia subsp. euroa. AD

Location: Hills c. 500 metres north of track to Warrigal Waterhole, c. 10 km east of Mt Isa, Queensland.
Description: Scraggy tree or mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream. Leaves scabrid, dull, pale green.  On very steep, north-facing quart slope with some Corymbia capricornia, Eucalyptus nudicaulis and E. leucophloia subsp. euroa. AD

Location: Ridge immediately south-west of Fountain Spring, Queensland.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, blue-green.  On top of granite and quart ridge in very rocky sites with Corymbia apsera dominant, and C. capricornia and Eucalyptus leucophloia subsp. euroa on slightly less harsh sites. AD Seed + photos

Location: Ridge immediately south-west of Fountain Spring, Queensland.
Description: Scraggy tree-mallee to 4 metres tall. Leaves scabrid. In flower. On top of granite and quart ridge in very rocky sites with Corymbia capricornia, Eucalyptus nudicaulis and E. leucophloia subsp. euroa. AD Photos

Location: Lake Julius, north-north-east of Mt Isa, Queensland.
Description: Mallee-like tree to 4 metres tall. bark smooth throughout, powdery and white. Leaves dull, blue-green. Scattered on upper steep slope of rocky hill in gullies and on slopes, with Corymbia aspera and C. capricornia. AD Seed + photos

Location: Burke Development Rd, north of Burke & Wills roadhouse, Queensland.
Description: Dense-crowned tree, many multi-stemmed, to 5 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, tessellated. Leaves setose, dull, pale green.  Scattered plants on flat in Acacia scrub. AD Photos

Location: Burke Development Rd, between Burke & Wills roadhouse and Normanton, Queensland.
Description: Trees, many several-stemmed, to 7 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches. Branchlets pruinose when new. Leaves dull, blue-green.  In broad depression in open woodland with some Eucalyptus pruinosa. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Gulf Development Rd, north-west of Croydon, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 metres, papery-flaky, tan, smooth above, white. Leaves discolorous, dull, green.  In woodland with Corymbia pocillum. AD Seed

Location: Gulf Development Rd, north-west of Croydon, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark variable, rough for c. half tree height. Leaves +/- concolorous, dull, green.  In woodland on +/- level site with Eucalyptus chartaboma. AD

Location: Gulf Development Rd, north-west of Croydon, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white, or with some irregularly tessellated grey bark for < 1 metre. Leaves scabrid, dull, green, lanceolate.  On broad red gravely rise in lancewood scrub with Corymbia pocillum and Eucalyptus distans. AD Photos

Location: Gulf Development Rd, between Croydon and Georgetown, Queensland.
Description: Slender tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous. Leaves very slightly glossy, green.  On broad rise in woodland with Corymbia pocillum and Eucalyptus chartaboma. AD

Location: Gulf Development Rd, between Croydon and Georgetown, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 metres, loose and flaky-papery, pale tan, then smooth and white above. Branchlets and fruits strongly pruinose.  On broad rise in woodland with Corymbia pocillum and Eucalyptus tetrodonta. AD Seed

Location: Immediately south of rubbish dump c. 1.5 km south of Georgetown, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, ironbark, dark grey. Leaves dull, blue-green.  Common here on undulating hills in open woodland with Corymbia pocillum and Eucalyptus microneura. AD Seed + photos

Location: Forsayth to Einasleigh rd, Queensland.
Description: Trees to 12 metres tall. Bark distinctly two-toned.  Dominant here on gravely pale grey sand, as emergent in thick lancewood shrubland with some Eucalyptus ligans subsp. novacastrensis. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Forsayth to Einasleigh rd, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 11 metres tall. Bark rough throughout (to very small branches), moderately fissured, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, dark green.  On undulating hills in lancewood woodland with Corymbia gilbertensis, C. ligans subsp. novacastrensis and Eucalyptus whitei. AD Seed + photos.

Location: Forsayth to Einasleigh rd, Queensland.
Description: Scraggy tree-mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, ironbark, almost black. Whole plant silvery and pruinose.  On upper lip of escarpment with Corymbia erythrophloia, C. peltata, Eucalyptus similis and E. crebra. AD Seed

Location: Forsayth to Einasleigh rd, Queensland.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree to 6 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, flaky and soft, orange-brown. Leaves distinctly discolorous, slightly glossy and green above.  On upper lip of escarpment with Corymbia erythrophloia, C. peltata, Eucalyptus shirleyi and E. crebra. AD Seed

Location: Road to Undara Lodge, south-east of Mt Surprise, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Leaves dull, blue-green. In +/- pure stand (some Eucalyptus crebra) in swampy flat, forming open woodland. First of this species seen coming from west. AD Photos

Location: Kennedy Hwy, south-east of Mt Garnet, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall, some several-stemmed. Bark rough throughout, moderately finely fissured, grey-brown. Leaves dull, dark green.  In woodland scrub with Corymbia dimorpha. AD

Location: Entrance to Evelyn property, north-west of Tumoulin, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough moderately finely fissured, grey. Leaves dull, dark blue-green. Branchlets slightly pruinose (most wax seasonally lost).  On slight rise with Eucalyptus atrata and with E. moluccana on flatter ground. AD

Location: C. 1 km south of Herberton towards Irvinebank, Queensland.
Description: Several-stemmed tree to 7 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, finely fissured, grey. Leaves becoming slightly glossy, dark blue-green. Wax lost from older material.  Scattered here on hills with Corymbia citriodora, C. abergiana, Eucalyptus granitica, E. irritans, E. shirleyi and E. atrata. AD Seed

Location: C. 3 kms from Herberton towards Atherton, Queensland.
Description: Tree 22 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above.  In forest with Corymbia intermedia, C. citriodora, Eucalyptus tereticornis subsp. tereticornis and E. reducta. AD

Location: C. 1 km north of Walkamin towards Atherton, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, moderately finely fissured, grey with pale grey patches. Leaves dull, green. Leaves long and coarse and fruits large. Co-dominant with Corymbia clarksoniana on level reddish loam with basalt. AD Seed + photos

Location: Peninsula Development Rd, W of Mt Carbine, Queensland.
Description: Mallee or multi-stemmed tree to 5 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, finely- fissured. On low hills with Corymbia dallachiana, C. hylandii and Eucalyptus cullenii. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Peninsula Development Rd, c. 10 km south-east of Laura, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, grey. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. In full flower (creamy white). No fruits present. On sandstone rise with Corymbia hylandii subsp. hylandii. AD, BRI

Location: Peninsula Development Rd, c. 4 km south-east of Laura, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough up to 6 m, +/- hard and moderately fissured, grey. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. On sandy soil at head of shallow gully with Corymbia clarksoniana, C. hylandii subsp. peninsularis, and Eucalyptus tetrodonta. AD

Location: Peninsula Development Rd, c. 15 km north of Coen, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale pink-grey over white. Leaves dull, +/- green.  On level topography in woodland with Corymbia paracolpica, C. confertiflora, Eucalyptus leptophleba and E. tetrodonta. AD

Location: Peninsula Development Rd, c. 15 km north of Coen, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 14 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout or with <0.5 metre thin flaky brown bark at base (smooth bark cream). Adult leaves slightly glossy, green. No inflorescences, but juvenile leaves measured to 270 mm long x 120 mm wide. A +/- pure stand on +/- level topography, forming very open woodland with some Melaleuca. AD Photos

Location: Peninsula Development Rd, c. 10 km south of Coen, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall, some several-stemmed. Distinctly half-barked. Leaves dark green. A good-sized stand in slight depression but on high ground, in low open forest with Corymbia ?paracolpica, C. ?nesophila and E. leptophleba. AD

Location: Peninsula Development Rd, near Pt Stewart turnoff, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, tessellated, grey-brown. Leaves weakly discolorous, glossy, light green.  Dominant tree here, forming open forest with some Eucalyptus brassiana and E. tetrodonta. AD Photos

Location: Lily Vale turnoff on Musgrave - Marina Plains Rd, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 26+ metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately to moderately finely fissured, grey. Co-dominant with Corymbia nesophila, forming forest on gritty sand on level topography. Photo Specimen only.

Location: C. 25 km east of Musgrave on Musgrave - Marina Plains Rd, Queensland.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 8 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, tessellated. Scattered here on plain dominated by Melaleuca, with some Corymbia clarksoniana. AD Seed

Location: Lakefield Nat. Park, Lakefield Rd from Musgrave, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough for c. one third tree height. Old dead fruits and new growth only.  Scattered trees on plain in low Melaleuca thickets. AD Photos

Location: Track to Bathurst Bay, Cape Melville Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 18 metres tall. Distinctly half-barked or blackbutted. Leaves +/- dull, dark green.  On creek flats in white sandy soil in dense scrubby woodland with Corymbia clarksoniana, C. tessellaris and Melaleuca. AD

Location: Track to Ninian Bay, Cape Melville Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately fissured and +/- fibrous. Leaves slightly discolorous, moderately glossy, green.  About three plants on white sand with Corymbia clarksoniana, Eucalyptus brassiana and E. tetrodonta. No E. biterranea seen on this track. AD, BRI

Location: Cape Melville Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree 14 metres tall. On undulating ground with Corymbia tessellaris and Eucalyptus leptophleba. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Normanby River, Lakefield Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: +/- pure stands forming open woodland on grey clay. Nearby on river is Corymbia tessellaris and Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. simulata. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Battlecamp Rd, Lakefield Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 16+ metres tall, mostly single-trunked. Bark rough to 30 mm diameter branches, thick but soft and flaky-fibrous, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, dull to very slightly glossy, green. Branchlets and buds slightly and variably pruinose. Flowers orange (in full flower). Dominant here, on level topography with some Eucalyptus tetrodonta. AD Seed + photos.

Location: Battlecamp Rd, north-west of Cooktown, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. Emergent above low, very dense scrubby rainforest on undulating low hills with some Eucalyptus tetrodonta. AD, BRI Seed

Location: Near junction of Daintree - Mossman Rd and Cape Tribulation Rd, Queensland.
Description: Tree 18 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. A few remnant trees on roadside in largely cleared flats (now sugar cane fields) below hills. AD

Location: Just off Kuranda - Mareeba Rd, near Karunda, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark rough for c. 2 m, then smooth, glossy, green-grey. Most trees with mostly juvenile leaves only, this one with mostly adult leaves (discolorous, slightly glossy and green). On steep rolling hills in marginal rainforest with Eucalyptus tereticornis subsp. tereticornis. AD

Location: El Arish, Bruce Hwy junction with Granadilla Rd, Queensland.
Description: Tree 16 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, fibrous-platy, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. In cyclone-damaged rainforest in remnant roadside vegetation surrounded by sugar cane fields. AD

Location: Bruce Hwy, south of Cardwell, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. Scattered clumps on level ground below hills in dense low forest with Corymbia tessellaris, C. clarksoniana and Melaleuca. AD

Location: Road to Wallaman Falls, Girringun Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 35+ metres tall. Bark rough for 2 to 3 m, then smooth. Trees severely cyclone damaged (Cyclone Yasi), with mainly epicormic regrowth. On high ridge in dense rainforest with some Corymbia torelliana. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Road to Wallaman Falls, Girringun Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree 18 metres tall, others nearby to 30 m. Bark rough for c. 2 m only, then satiny and greenish grey. Juvenile leaves dull and setose, adult leaves glossy and glabrous.  On steep hill slope in woodland-rainforest ecotone with Eucalyptus platyphylla. AD

Location: Road to Wallaman Falls, Girringun Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Spreading tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream. Leaves dull, blue-green.  On steep hill slope in woodland-rainforest ecotone with Corymbia torelliana. AD

Location: Near summit of Mt Stuart, near Townsville, Queensland.
Description: Poor-formed trees to 6 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, moderately finely fissured, grey. Leaves very slightly glossy, dark green. All vegetation unhealthy due to cyclone damage (Cyclone Yasi). Growing on rocky slope with Eucalyptus paedoglauca. AD

Location: Conway Nat. Park car park, c. 2 km west of Shute Harbour, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, stringy-fibrous, moderately fissured, red-brown. Leaves moderately discolorous, glossy and light green above.  On lower hill slopes in dense woodland with Corymbia clarksoniana, Eucalyptus insulana and E. drepanophylla. AD Seed

Location: Conway Nat. Park car park, c. 2 km west of Shute Harbour, Queensland.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 8 metres tall. Bark rough +/- throughout, moderately finely fissured, brown. Leaves +/- dull, very slightly blue-green. On lower hill slopes in dense woodland with Corymbia clarksoniana, Eucalyptus portuensis and E. drepanophylla. AD

Location: Track to The Diggins campground, Crediton State Forest, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, platy-fibrous, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above.  Common here on hill slopes in forest vegetation with Corymbia intermedia. AD Seed

Location: Eungella - Eungella Dam road, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark rough for 4 m, finely textured, dark grey, smooth above, cream. Leaves  discolorous, glossy and green above. No parts pruinose. No fruits seen. Emergent in forest with Corymbia intermedia. AD, BRI Seed

Location: Hazelwood Creek, SW of Eungella Dam, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark rough for c. half tree height, finely fissured, grey and pale grey, smooth above, grey over cream. Growing along stream. Above on creek flats is Corymbia dallachiana, C. tessellaris and Eucalyptus drepanophylla. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Fitzroy Development Rd, near Flora Range, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream, except some thin flaky pale brown bark at base. Leaves very glossy, yellow-green.  On slightly undulating ground in woodland dominated by Eucalyptus crebra and E. populnea subsp. populnea, and with some Corymbia brachycarpa. AD

Location: Fitzroy Development Rd, near Flora Range, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, ironbark, nearly black. Leaves dull, blue-green. Juvenile leaves fairly narrow. On slightly undulating ground in woodland co-dominant with E. populnea subsp. populnea, and with some Corymbia dallachiana and C. brachycarpa. AD Seed + photos

Location: Fitzroy Development Rd, near Flora Range, Queensland.
Description: Tree 6 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, tessellated, brown. Leaves discolorous, dull and dark green above. On slightly undulating ground in woodland dominated by Eucalyptus crebra and E. populnea subsp. populnea, and with some Corymbia brachycarpa. AD Seed

Location: Blackdown Tableland Nat. Park, c. 18 km south-west of Umolo, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 14 metres tall. Bark rough to very small branches, stringy-fibrous, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy, dark green. At foot of hillslope in woodland with Corymbia hendersonii and Eucalyptus cloeziana. AD Seed

Location: Mimosa Creek, c. 500 metres downstream from campground, Blackdown Tableland Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree 8 metres tall, others much taller. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, red-brown. Leaves slightly to moderately discolorous, glossy and green above. On sandstone in creek valley in open forest with Angophora leiocarpa, Eucalyptus sphaerocarpa and E. melanoleuca. AD Seed

Location: Mimosa Creek, where main access track crosses, Blackdown Tableland Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree 11 metres tall, others to 30+ m. Bark smooth throughout, mottled grey over pale grey and orange-cream. Leaves discolorous, slightly glossy and green above. On sandstone outcrop in creek valley with Angophora leiocarpa, Eucalyptus sphaerocarpa, E. constricta and E. melanoleuca. AD Seed

Location: Mimosa Creek, Blackdown Tableland Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tumbledown tree 6 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth throughout, grey over pale grey, some flaky loose bark near base. Leaves +/- dull, green. A few trees on sandstone in creek with Angophora leiocarpa, with surrounding forest of Eucalyptus sphaerocarpa, E. constricta, E. propinqua and E. melanoleuca. AD

Location: Car park to Rainbow Waters, Blackdown Tableland Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree 30 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, granular, dark grey over pale grey over cream. Leaves discolorous, slightly glossy, dark blue-green. On broad ridge with Corymbia intermedia, Eucalyptus sphaerocarpa, E. constricta, E. saligna and E. ?mensalis. AD

Location: Mimosa Creek camp ground, Blackdown Tableland Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, brown. Leaves slightly glossy, blue-green. Common here on undulating ground in open forest with Angophora leiocarpa, Eucalyptus constricta and E. propinqua/major. AD

Location: Ascent up to Blackdown Tableland from Umolo, Blackdown Tableland Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Laser height: 44.5 metres. Crown spread: 25.5 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 5.55 metres. In open forest on steep slope with Corymbia intermedia or C. hendersonii, Eucalyptus cloeziana and E. baileyana. Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Blackwater to Rolleston rd, Queensland.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree to 7 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, moderately fissured, grey. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. On low rocky rise in open shrubland with some Eucalyptus crebra and E. populnea subsp. populnea. AD

Location: Carnarvon Hwy, ca. 0.3 km north of 3rd crossing of Dawson River, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves discolorous, slightly glossy and dark green above. On sandstone rise and small breakaway in burnt woodland with Angophora leiocarpa, Corymbia trachyphloia, Eucalyptus mediocris, E. exserta, E. melanophloia subsp. melanophloia and possibly C. petalophylla (no buds or fruits). AD

Location: Just W of Carnarvon Hwy on rd to Yellowbank Junction, Queensland.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 6 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, grey over cream, somewhat retained on lower trunks. Leaves dull, grey-green, maturing greener. Juvenile leaves with pruinose growth. On pale yellow sandy soil in woodland dominated by Callitris glaucophylla and with some Corymbia dolichocarpa, C. tessellaris, Eucalyptus melanophloia subsp. melanophloia, E. crebra and E. populnea subsp. populnea. AD Seed

Location: Westgrove Rd, near Sunrise homestead, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, ironbark, nearly black. Common here, on pale yellow sand in woodland dominated by Callitris glaucophylla with Corymbia tessellaris and Eucalyptus populnea subsp. populnea. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Westgrove Rd, near Sunrise homestead, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey-tan over cream, with some loose flaky bark near base. Leaves slightly glossy, green. On slightly swampy sand on +/- flat terrain in woodland with Angophora floribunda and Eucalyptus populnea subsp. populnea. AD Photos

Location: Westgrove Rd, near Sunrise homestead, Queensland.
Description: Juvenile leaves from regrowth 1 m tall. Leaves large, orbicular to broadly ovate, dull, green to slightly blue-green. On slightly swampy sand on +/- flat terrain in woodland with Angophora floribunda and Eucalyptus populnea subsp. populnea. AD

Location: Mt Moffat access rd to Carnarvon Nat. Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 13 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, ironbark, nearly black. On sandstone breakaway with Angophora leiocarpa, Eucalyptus panda and E. mediocris. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Marlong Arch, Carnarvon Nat. Park, Mt Moffat section, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 28 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, red-brown under. Scattered trees on deep white sand with outcropping sandstone, forming tall open woodland with Angophora leiocarpa and A. floribunda. Photo Specimen only.

Location: Marlong Arch, Carnarvon Nat. Park, Mt Moffat section, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream. Leaves discolorous, slightly glossy, dark slightly blue-green. On sandstone outcrop in open woodland dominated by Angophora leiocarpa, also with some A. floribunda and Eucalyptus erosa. AD Photos

Location: Rd to Kookaburra Cave, Carnarvon Nat. Park, Mt Moffat section, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark loosely rough for 1 to 2 metres, then smooth, pale grey over cream. Leaves slightly glossy, dark green. In broad depression in woodland with Eucalyptus conica, E. melanophloia subsp. melanophloia and E. populnea subsp. populnea. AD

Location: Car park at Isla Gorge National Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree 12 metres tall, others to 18 m. Bark rough to branches c. 30 mm diameter, then smooth. Leaves somewhat discolorous, dull, blue-green. On steep sandstone escarpment in woodland with Corymbia hendersonii, C. watsoniana subsp. watsoniana, Eucalyptus tenuipes, E. cloeziana and E. suffulgens. Also nearby is E. baileyana and E. rubiginosa. AD Seeds

Location: Car park at Isla Gorge National Park, Queensland.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy, red-brown. Leaves discolorous, +/- dull, green. On steep sandstone escarpment in woodland with Corymbia hendersonii, C. watsoniana subsp. watsoniana, Eucalyptus beaniana, E. cloeziana and E. suffulgens. Also nearby is E. baileyana and E. rubiginosa. AD Seeds

Location: Barakula State Forest scientific area, Queensland.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 6 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, ironbark, nearly black. Leaves +/- dull, dark green. In +/- pure stand as scattered trees emergent in shrubland on plateau of pale yellow-brown sand. Nearby is Corymbia bloxsomei and Eucalyptus tenuipes. AD Seeds

Location: Barakula State Forest scientific area, Queensland.
Description: Multi-stemmed erect tree to 7 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, stringy-fibrous, grey-brown over red-brown. Leaves discolorous, slightly glossy and dark green above. On pale grey-brown sand with Corymbia bloxsomei, Eucalyptus panda and E. fibrosa. AD Seeds

Location: Pine Corner Creek, Barakula State Forest, Queensland.
