Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Leaves discolorous, +/- dull, very slightly blue-green. On sandy soil near creek with Callitris glaucophylla, Angophora floribunda and Eucalyptus chloroclada. AD Seeds

Location: Pine Corner Creek, Barakula State Forest, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough and loose for 1 m then smooth. Leaves +/- dull, slightly blue-green. On sandy soil along creek with Callitris glaucophylla, Angophora floribunda and Eucalyptus longirostrata. AD

Location: Brovinia State Forest, east-south-east of Brovinia, Queensland.
Description: Tree 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey. Leaves dark green. Three plants at top of sandstone and laterite breakaway (on plateau) with Corymbia trachyphloia, C. variegata, C. bloxsomei, Eucalyptus fibrosa and E. exserta. AD, BRI Seed + photos

Location: Brovinia State Forest, east-south-east of Brovinia, Queensland.
Description: Poor-formed tree 7 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. At top of sandstone and laterite breakaway (on plateau) with Corymbia trachyphloia, C. variegata, C. bloxsomei, Eucalyptus fibrosa and E. broviniensis. AD

Location: Rd to Buxton from Bruce Hwy, east of Childers, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over orange-tan. Leaves dark green. On +/- swampy level ground in woodland with Corymbia trachyphloia subsp. trachyphloia and Eucalyptus latisinensis. AD

Location: Maryborough - Cooloona Rd, Poona National Park, Queensland.
Description: Heavy-crowned tree to 9 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pink-grey and cream. Leaves slightly blue-green. On low-lying swampy but level ground in dense low woodland thicket with Melaleuca, Angophora woodsiana and Eucalyptus ?insulana. AD

Location: Maryborough - Cooloona Rd, Poona National Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough to finger-diameter branches, moderately fissured, grey-brown. Leaves green. Scattered trees on low-lying swampy but level ground in dense low woodland thicket with Melaleuca, Angophora woodsiana and Eucalyptus bancroftii. AD Seed

Location: Maryborough - Cooloona Rd, Tuan State Forest, Queensland.
Description: Several-stemmed tree to 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, fairly deeply fissured, brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. In shallow creekline in white sandy soil with Eucalyptus latisinensis dominant in slightly higher ground. AD

Location: Doggrell walk, Toolara State Forest, Queensland.
Description: Laser height: 50.0 metres. Crown spread: 20.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 7.80 metres. Numerous trees of Eucalyptus cloeziana of similar girth and similar or greater height here. As an emergent in tall forest with Lophostemon confertus, Corymbia intermedia and Eucalyptus grandis, with dense rainforest secondary storey. Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Between Traveston and Cooran, south-east of Gympie, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale orange-grey over cream. On undulating slopes in open forest with Corymbia intermedia and Eucalyptus tereticornis subsp. tereticornis. AD

Location: Imbil to Kandanga rd, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and pale grey-orange. Leaves discolorous. On low hills in low open forest with Angophora leiocarpa, Eucalyptus acmenoides, E. moluccana and E. ?siderophloia. AD Seed

Location: Clifford St, between Maleny and Montville, Queensland.
Description: Tree 7 metres tall. Leaves discolorous, highly glossy and light green above, paler below. Cold damaged cultivated trees with mature flower buds and immature fruits. AD, BRI

Location: North of Peachester on Peachester - Maleny Rd, Queensland.
Description: Tree 24 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and dark green above. In forest vegetation on undulating hills with Corymbia intermedia, Eucalyptus pilularis and E. tereticornis subsp. tereticornis. AD

Location: Commissioners Flat, south-west of Peachester, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. In remnant roadside woodland on flat with Angophora ?woodsiana, Corymbia ?intermedia, Eucalyptus racemosa, E. siderophloia. Also, E. tereticornis subsp. tereticornis common nearby as larger trees with coarser crowns. AD

Location: North of Caboolture, Queensland.
Description: Tree 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and orange-grey over cream. Leaves +/- dull, +/- green, not as coarse as E. bancroftii elsewhere, but still ok. On swampy roadside drain with Melaleuca, Casuarina and Eucalyptus racemosa. AD

Location: Ca. 4 km north-east of Helidon, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, fibrous-platy, brown. Leaves moderately discolorous, green above, paler below. On low broad rise in roadside dense woodland with Corymbia ?trachyphloia, C. variegata, Eucalyptus ?taurina and E. ?carnea (rain-wet site). AD Seed

Location: Ca. 10 km north-east of Helidon, Queensland.
Description: Several-stemmed tree 10 metres tall. Leaves +/- dull, slightly blue-green. On slight rise on gently undulating sandstone in forest with Angophora woodsiana, Eucalyptus pilularis and E. microcorys. AD Seed

Location: Hampton - Crows Nest Rd at Goombungee turnoff, Queensland.
Description: Tree 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves discolorous, green above, paler below (very rainy collection). On low rolling hills in gravelly clay-loam with Eucalyptus tereticornis subsp. basaltica and E. eugenioides. Also nearby on lower sites is E. saligna. AD

Location: Hampton - Crows Nest Rd at Goombungee turnoff, Queensland.
Description: Tree 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout (very rainy collection). On low rolling hills in gravelly clay-loam with Eucalyptus longirostrata and E. eugenioides. Also nearby on lower sites is E. saligna. AD

Location: Ca. 5 km west of Eulorel, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, ironbark. Leaves dull, blue-green. Flowers white. On broad rise in sandy soil in woodland dominated by Callitris glaucophylla and with Corymbia dolichocarpa and Eucalyptus melanophloia subsp. melanophloia. AD Seed

Location: Ca. 12 km west of Eulorel, Queensland.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree-mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green at first, maturing greener. On rise of shallow soil in shrubland with some Eucalyptus populnea and E. crebra. AD

Location: Bollon Rd, ca. 70 km south-east of Charleville, Queensland.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches ()but not as far up branches as in E. exserta), hard and moderately fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. On broad rise of yellow sand in shrubland with Eucalyptus melanophloia subsp. melanophloia and a Triodia groundstorey. AD Seed

Location: Access track to Wongalee, north of Wongalee, Queensland.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough for half plant height, moderately fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. On red sand plain in open woodland with Corymbia terminalis and Eucalyptus melanophloia subsp. melanophloia. AD

Location: Walk track to Mulgowan rock-art site, Gundabooka Nat. Park, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark variable, rough on stems or nearly completely smooth. Rough bark moderately fissured, tightly-held or loose, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. Common here on low ridges of sandstone boulders and slabs with Callitris glaucophylla and some Eucalyptus vicina on slightly lower sites. AD Seed + photos

Location: Walk track to Mulgowan rock-art site, Gundabooka Nat. Park, New South Wales.
Description: Large tree-like mallee 6 metres tall, others to 10 m. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Leaves slightly glossy, green. On footslopes and in creek gullies on sandstone ridges, with some Eucalyptus morrisii and E. intertexta, also Callitris glaucophylla, Brachychiton populneus and Angophora melanoxylon. AD Seed

Location: N slope Mt Gunderbooka, Gundabooka National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall. Bark rough over stems, but variable amoung individuals, some loose and matt-like. Leaves dull, blue-green. Scattered on steep north slope of sandstone in very open woodland with scattered Corymbia terminalis. AD

Location: Rockholes loop walk, Homestead Creek, Mutawintji Nat. Park, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey-brown over cream. Leaves dull, very slightly blue-green. In cracks of massive sandstone in creek gully and on slopes, with Callitris glaucophylla. Slightly lower in creek gullies is Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. arida. AD, CANB Seed + photos

Location: Kangaroo Creek Reservoir wall, Torrens River gorge, South Australia.
Description: Tree, many several-trunked, to 10 metres tall. Bark rough over most of stems, moderately fissured, grey. leaves glossy, dark green. On steep rocky slope forming woodland in +/- pure stand. AD

Location: Tapanappa Hill, Deep Creek Conservation Park, South Australia.
Description: Dominant here, on high rounded hills in low dense woodland with some Eucalyptus fasciculosa and Xanthorrhoea semiplana. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Between Tapanappa Hill and Boat Harbour Beach, Deep Creek Conservation Park, South Australia.
Description: Dominant here, on high coastal bluffs in low dense scrub with some Eucalyptus fasciculosa. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Waite Arboretum, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 18.0 metres. Crown spread: 18.5 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 2.14 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Waite Arboretum, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 20.5 metres. Crown spread: 19.5 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 2.88 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Waite Arboretum, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 23.0 metres. Crown spread: 18.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 1.96 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Waite Arboretum, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 13.0 metres. Crown spread: 23.5 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 3.29 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Emu Springs Rd, east of Tintinara, South Australia.
Description: In mallee scrub in undulating sand over limestone with Eucalyptus diversifolia subsp. diversifolia dominant and some E. leucoxylon subsp. stephaniae. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Rescue Track, Ngarkat Conservation Park, South Australia.
Description: Dominant in broad sandy swales as emergent clumps. Also a large mallee ring of Eucalyptus incrassata x E. leucoxylon subsp. stephaniae. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Rescue Track, Ngarkat Conservation Park, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Dominant in swale with Eucalyptus incrassata and E. leptophylla. Also seen in this area is E. socialis subsp. viridans. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Baan Hill Track, Ngarkat Conservation Park, South Australia.
Description: Scattered on sandhills with Eucalyptus incrassata. Becoming more common to the north. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Box Flat, Ngarkat Conservation Park, South Australia.
Description: Dominant tree on flat, surrounded by sandhills dominated by Eucalyptus arenacea. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Billiatt Conservation Park, Lameroo - Alawoona Rd, South Australia.
Description: Mallee 4.5 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, ribbony near base. Leaves glossy, green, new growth duller. On slightly undulating ground with Eucalyptus incrassata and E. leptophylla. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Corner Billiatt Rd and Schell Well Rd, south of Alawoona, South Australia.
Description: Mallee, but many single-stemmed, to 6 metres tall. Bark variable, mostly rough for 0.5 to 3 metres, a few completely smooth-barked. All white-flowered. On puffy red clay-loam in +/- pure stand. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Billiatt Road, south of Alawoona, South Australia.
Description: Spreading mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark rough up to 2 metres or smooth throughout. Leaves dull, greyish. On deep yellow sand over limestone on dunes with some Eucalyptus incrassata and lower in swales is E. oleosa subsp. oleosa. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Loxton - Alawoona Road, north of Alawoona, South Australia.
Description: Common on undulating sand over limestone with Eucalyptus socialis subsp. socialis and E. gracilis - E. calycogona intergrades. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Murray River, Loxton, South Australia.
Description: Dominant on clay flats with Eucalyptus camaldulensis subsp. camaldulensis in better-watered sites. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: 300 metres south-east of Gunyah Road, north of Wilmington, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 32.0 metres. Crown spread: 26.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 14.05 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Stirling North to Quorn road, South Australia.
Description: In powdery pinkish loam in valley of open chenopods and some Eucalyptus socialis subsp. socialis and E. gracilis. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Hancock Lookout road, Flinders Ranges, South Australia.
Description: Leaves slightly glossy, very slightly blue-green. In flower. Co-dominant here with Eucalyptus leucoxylon subsp. pruinosa, also some E. cajaputea and E. camaldulensis subsp. minima. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Almond Corner Road, south of Kapunda, South Australia.
Description: Looks very close to E. microcarpa 'Adelaide variant' but with narrower juveniles. Dominant over hills with some Eucalyptus leucoxylon subsp. pruinosa and E. porosa. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Near Rooney Point, Beachport Conservation Park, north-west of Beachport, South Australia.
Description: Trees to 7 metres tall, crown dense and heavy. Scattered trees between dunes and salt lake in dense Acacia scrub. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Catford Road, Halbury, South Australia.
Description: On pale red-brown loam over limestone with Eucalyptus odorata, E. socialis subsp. socialis and some E. phenax subsp. phenax. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: 'The Devils Garden', Balaklava - Halbury road, South Australia.
Description: Pure stand on clayey flat. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Tanami Rd at Puyurru turnoff, Northern Territory.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Scattered in clumps on reddish sand plan in open Acacia shrubland with Eucalyptus gamophylla and some Corymbia opaca. AD Seeds

Location: Tanami Rd, south-east of The Granites mine, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall, some several-stemmed. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves setose, acuminate (triangular). Scattered on red sand plain with Eucalyptus gamophylla and Corymbia opaca nearby. Photo specimen only.

Location: Tanami Rd, near The Granites mine, Northern Territory.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, finely fissured. Whole plant silvery-waxy. First of this species seen coming from the south-east. Growing on red sandplain with outcropping granite with some Corymbia opaca and C. candida subsp. dipsodes. AD

Location: Tanami Rd, just west of Conglomerate Creek, Northern Territory.
Description: Several-stemmed tree to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, powdery white and pink. Leaves dull, bluish. First of this species seen coming from the south-east. Growing in burnt open woodland on red gravely loam with Corymbia opaca, C. candida subsp. dipsodes, Eucalyptus pachyphylla and E. odontocarpa. AD Seeds

Location: The Black Hills, Lajarnanu Rd, Northern Territory.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, powdery white over pinkish tan. Branchlets pruinose. Leaves dull, grey-green. Dominant on low granite boulder rise, but as scattered plants. On plain below is Corymbia opaca, Eucalyptus brevifolia and E. victrix. AD Seeds

Location: Sturt Creek floodplain, east of Billiluna, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 7 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth throughout, powdery white. Dominant here in woodland on red loam of floodplain. Photo specimen only.

Location: Wolfe Creek Meteorite Crater, south-east edge, Western Australia.
Description: Tree, mostly several-stemmed, to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white. Branchlets variably pruinose when new. Leaves dull, bluish. On rocky slopes of crater in open woodland with some Corymbia opaca and C. flavescens and Triodia groundstorey. Nearby in crater are a few plants of Eucalyptus victrix. AD Photos

Location: Great Northern Hwy, south of Alice Hill, 300 m west of Hwy, Western Australia.
Description: Robust mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, powdery white. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Branchlets and fruits variably pruinose. Scattered on rocky granite slopes with Eucalyptus brevifolia common and some Corymbia x opacula. AD Photos

Location: Mt Nyulasy, Great Northern Hwy, Western Australia.
Description: Several-stemmed tree to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, powdery white. All parts pruinose. Leaves more orbicular than in E. brevifolia. Scattered on steep slope of granite boulders. Below on flat is Eucalyptus pruinosa and E. brevifolia. AD Seeds + photos

Location: Great Northern Hwy, Jailhouse Creek, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 7 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, finely fissured, grey. Growing on flats above creek in open woodland with Corymbia grandifolia. AD Seeds

Location: Great Northern Hwy, Dunham Hill, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white. Leaves glossy, yellow-green. Growing on steep rocky slope in open woodland with Corymbia drysdalensis. AD Photos

Location: Great Northern Hwy, north side of Dunham Hill, Western Australia.
Description: Poor-formed, several-stemmed tree to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, powdery white and pink-grey. Leaves greyish. All parts strongly pruinose. Scattered on steep west-facing slope with Corymbia drysdalensis and Eucalyptus confluens. AD Photos

Location: Great Northern Hwy, 100 metres south of Durham River crossing, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over pale salmon. Leaves very large (as are the buds), glossy, green. First of this species seen coming from the south. Growing in low ground in dense cane-grass with Corymbia confertiflora and Eucalyptus pruinosa. AD Photos

Location: Junction of Victoria Hwy and Great Northern Hwy, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 7 metres tall, mostly several-stemmed. Bark smooth throughout, powdery white. Whole plant grey and pruinose. Scattered on flat in open woodland with Corymbia ferruginea, C. grandifolia and Eucalyptus bigalerita. AD

Location: Lake Argyle Rd, c. 27 km from Great Northern Hwy, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white. Leaves glossy, light green. On footslopes of large rocky ridges in open woodland with Corymbia grandifolia and C. disjuncta. AD

Location: 500 m south of Jasper Gorge Rd, Northern Territory.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, powdery, white and pale grey. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Only two plants seen here, on top of sandstone plateau in clefts between rock with Corymbia cliftoniana, C. capricornia and Eucalyptus aurantiaca. AD Seeds + photos

Location: Victoria Hwy, rest area north-east of Mt Leonard, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white over orange-tan. Leaves very glossy, green. Growing on gravely loam on broad low rise with Corymbia grandifolia and Eucalyptus tectifica. AD

Location: Douglas Rd, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey and cream over pale orange. Leaves dull, green. On slightly undulating area in woodland with Corymbia disjuncta and Eucalyptus tectifica. AD

Location: Litchfield Rd, Tabletop Range, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough for about half tree height, fibrous, grey-brown, then smooth and white above. Leaves dull, green. No buds of fruits except specimen from recently fallen tree. In low forest, co-dominant with Eucalyptus tetrodonta. AD Photos

Location: Just east of Lost City, Litchfield National Park, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark rough for about quarter tree height, fibrous-flaky, brown, then smooth above, white and cream. Leaves very slightly glossy and green above. In full flower (compare with lowland form). On sandstone plateau with outcropping sandstone, in open woodland with Corymbia porrecta, C. kombolgiensis, Eucalyptus tetrodonta and E. brachyandra (on rocks). Nearby is E. phoenicea. AD, DNA Photos

Location: Litchfield Rd turnoff from Batchelor Rd, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall, many several-stemmed. Bark rough to small branches, yellow-brown, flaky-fibrous. leaves dull, green. On low rise in open woodland with Corymbia polysciada, Eucalyptus miniata (lowland form) and E. tetrodonta. AD

Location: Litchfield Rd turnoff from Batchelor Rd, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall, many several-stemmed. Bark rough to small branches, yellow-brown, flaky-fibrous. leaves dull, green. Note leaf width variation between this and D.Nicolle 6657. On low rise in open woodland with Corymbia polysciada, Eucalyptus miniata (lowland form) and E. tetrodonta. AD

Location: Stuart Hwy, between Mataranka and Larrimah, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream over pale orange. Leaves dull to very slightly glossy, green to slightly blue-green. Scattered on flat topography in woodland with Corymbia ferruginea, C. umbonata, C. ?polysciada and Eucalyptus patellaris. AD

Location: Arltunga Tourist Drive, south-east of The Garden Homestead, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree, many several-stemmed, to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over very pale grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. First of this species seen coming from the west. Scattered trees growing on low broad rise of orange loam and stony surface. Nearby is Corymbia opaca, C. aparrerinja, Eucalyptus socialis subsp. eucentrica and E. camaldulensis subsp. arida. AD Photos

Location: Trephina Gorge to Arltunga Reserve road, Northern Territory.
Description: Burnt mallees to 5 metres tall, regrowth to 2 metres. Juvenile regrowth leaves large and ovate. Leaves and branchlets grey and pruinose. Growing on footslope of stony hill with Eucalyptus gamophylla, and with Corymbia opaca and C. aparrerinja nearby. AD, CANB, DNA Seeds + photos

Location: Trephina Gorge to Arltunga Reserve road, Northern Territory.
Description: Unburnt mallees to 4.5 metres tall. Bark rough near base but otherwise mostly smooth. Leaves, fruits and branchlets strongly pruinose. Growing in minor creek in mulga scrub. AD, DNA Seeds + photos

Location: Trephina Gorge Nature Park, Northern Territory.
Description: Laser height: 27.0 metres. Crown spread: 32.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 4.43 metres.  On creek floodplain in open mulga shrubland, with E. camaldulensis subsp. arida in creek and Corymbia opaca and E. socialis subsp. eucentrica nearby.   Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Trephina Gorge campground, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree 11 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, tessellated, grey-brown. Leaves more-or-less dull, green. On red-brown loam on flat with Eucalyptus intertexta. Nearby is Corymbia aparrerinja, Eucalyptus gamophylla, E. socialis subsp. eucentrica and E. camaldulensis subsp. arida. AD, CANB Photos

Location: County Peak, south-east of Merredin, Western Australia.
Description: Slender tree to 11 metres tall. Bark rough up to 6 m, smooth above. Leaves very glossy, dark green. Scattered on gravely ironstone slope with Eucalyptus capillosa, E. celastroides subsp. virella, E. longicornis, E. loxophleba subsp. loxophleba, E. phenax subsp. phenax and E. salmonophloia. Nearby upslope is E. astringens subsp. astringens.  AD, PERTH

Location: Corner of Briant Road and Allsop Road, south-east of Merredin, Western Australia.
Description: All red-flowered. Growing with Eucalyptus capillosa, E. loxophleba subsp. lissophloia, E. salmonophloia, E. tenera and E. subangusta subsp. subangusta. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Allsop Road, south-east of Merredin, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream. Leaves very glossy, light green, with fairly numerous oil glands (many more than typical E. sporadica). Growing in dense Casuarina shrubland with Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. lissophloia and E. subangusta subsp. subangusta. AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Chingah Hills, south-east of Merredin, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 10 metres tall. A few scattered mallees at the base of a granite valley with Casuarina and Acacia.  AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Dulyalbin Road, Bodallin South, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony. Leaves small, somewhat glossy, bluish. Common here, growing on broad ridge in Casuarina shrubland with Eucalyptus burracoppinensis and E. rigidula. AD, PERTH

Location: Dulyalbin Road, Bodallin South, Western Australia.
Description: Shrub 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony. Leaves small, somewhat glossy, bluish. Common here, growing on broad ridge in Allocasuarina shrubland with Eucalyptus burracoppinensis and E. rigidula. PERTH

Location: Bodallin South Road, Western Australia.
Description: Erect-stemmed mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough up to 1.5 m, finely fissured and tightly held. Growing in broad depression with Eucalyptus olivina and E. pluricaulis. AD, PERTH

Location: Bodallin South Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream. Leaves +/- glossy, olive green (very slightly blue-green). Growing in broad depression with Eucalyptus arachnaea subsp. arachnaea and E. pluricaulis. AD, PERTH

Location: Bodallin South Road, Western Australia.
Description: Coppice from stems. Leaves narrowly elliptic, dull, greyish, slightly pruinose. PERTH

Location: Bodallin South Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, accumulating at base. Leaves dull, bluish, very much like E. densa subsp. improcera. Growing in broad depression with Eucalyptus arachnaea subsp. arachnaea and E. olivina. AD, PERTH

Location: Bodallin South Road, Western Australia.
Description: Seedling from road verge. Leaves dull, blue-green. PERTH

Location: Bennett Road, South Bodallin, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall, many several-trunked. Bark rough for half tree height, moderately fissured. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing on slightly undulating topography with Eucalyptus celastroides subsp. virella, E. longicornis and E. yilgarnensis. PERTH

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus horistes subsp. Southern smooth bark
Location: Corner of Marvel Loch Road and Patroni Road, west of Marvel Loch, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, colourful, powdery white streaked with yellow-orange. Leaves glossy,light green, with numerous oil glands. Growing on slight rise in Acacia scrub with Eucalyptus moderata and E. sheathiana. PERTH Photos Seeds

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus horistes subsp. Southern smooth bark
Location: Corner of Marvel Loch Road and Patroni Road, west of Marvel Loch, Western Australia.
Description: Juvenile regrowth to 1 metre tall. Leaves rough-glandular, ovate, greyish, pruinose. PERTH

Location: Ghooli South Road, near Lenneburg Mine, south of Marvel Loch, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 11 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream and yellowish grey. Leaves moderately glossy, green. Branchlets variably pruinose. Growing on red clay with Eucalyptus longicornis, E. polita and E. salubris. PERTH Seeds

Location: Ghooli South Road, near Lenneburg Mine, south of Marvel Loch, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet to 11 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, cream and yellowish grey. Leaves slightly glossy, green. Branchlets variably pruinose. Growing on red clay with Eucalyptus longicornis, E. polita and E. salubris. PERTH

Location: Marvel Loch - Forrestania Road, south of Marvel Loch, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream. Leaves glossy, green. On red loam in level topography with Eucalyptus longicornis, E. moderata, E. polita and E. salmonophloia. AD, PERTH Photos

Location: Parker Range Road, south of Marvel Loch, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale tan over grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Common here in mallet woodland on gravely red loam with Eucalyptus extensa, E. polita and E. salubris. AD, CANB, PERTH

Location: Waterbidden Road, south-west of Holleton, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves thick, dark green, no oil glands visible. Common here, growing on broad rise in low open mallee with Eucalyptus olivina, E. platycorys, E. densa subsp. improcera and E. sporadica. AD, PERTH

Location: Waterbidden Road, south-west of Holleton, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves +/- glossy, slightly blue-green. Growing on broad rise in low open mallee with Eucalyptus rigidula, E. platycorys, E. densa subsp. improcera and E. sporadica. PERTH

Location: Waterbidden Road, south-west of Holleton, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall. Leaves dull, bluish. Growing on broad rise in low open mallee with Eucalyptus rigidula, E. platycorys, E. olivina and E. sporadica. AD, PERTH

Location: Woogenilup North Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, ribbony. Leaves glossy, dark green. Western-most population seen, in roadside vegetation with Eucalyptus pleurocarpa, E. pachyloma, E. preissiana subsp. preissiana and E. uncinata. PERTH

Location: Woogenilup North Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over pale grey. Leaves slightly glossy, light green. Large clump on side road with Eucalyptus decipiens, E. decurva, E. marginata subsp. marginata, E. pachyloma and E. preissiana subsp. preissiana. AD, PERTH Seeds

Location: Woogenilup North Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Leaves dull, green. Growing with Eucalyptus decipiens, E. decurva, E. pachyloma, E. pleurocarpa and E. uncinata. PERTH Seeds

Location: Chester Pass Road, north of Formby Road South junction, Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2.5 metres tall. Leaves +/- dull, blue-green.  Growing as a scattered understorey in Eucalyptus wandoo subsp. wandoo and E. occidentalis woodland, also with some mallee E. marginata subsp. marginata. PERTH Photos

Location: Mt Talyuberlup, about half way up walking trail to summit, Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey-tan over pale grey. Leaves slightly glossy, green.  Dense thickets on steep rocky south-facing slope with Corymbia calophylla; nearby is Eucalyptus ligulata subsp. stirlingica and E. talyuberlup. PERTH Seeds

Location: Mt Talyuberlup, about half way up walking trail to summit, Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee to 3 metres tall. Fruits very variable in size and shape, both between and on individual plants.  On steep rocky south-facing slope with Eucalyptus megacarpa, E. ligulata subsp. stirlingica and E. talyuberlup. AD, PERTH

Location: Mt Talyuberlup, quarter way up walking trail to summit, Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee 3 metres tall. Leaves discolorous, glossy and green above. Leaf oil glands very sparse.  Scattered plants in a thicket of Eucalyptus talyuberlup. AD, PERTH Seeds

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata x E. preissiana subsp. preissiana
Location: Stirling Range Drive, Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves slightly discolorous, glossy, slightly blue-green. Large clump of mallees in low dense mallee shrubland with Eucalyptus decurva, E. lehmannii subsp. lehmannii, E. ligulata subsp. stirlingica, E. pleurocarpa, E. preissiana subsp. preissiana, E. staeri and E. thamnoides. PERTH

Location: Stirling Range Drive, Stirling Range National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 8 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, grey. Leaves glossy, dark green. Flowers lemon-yellow. Common here in sandy creek flat with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus thamnoides. PERTH Photos

Location: West of Boags Country Road, north of Burns Creek, Tasmania.
Description: Laser height: 74.0+ metres. Crown spread: 18.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 12.10 metres. Ground level to first major branching: 31.5 metres.  Remnant tree surrounded by Eucalyptus regnans regrowth and 6-year-old E. nitens plantation.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Tasman Hwy, south-west of Scottsdale, Tasmania.
Description: Co-dominant with Eucalyptus amygdalina. Also nearby is E. ovata subsp. ovata and E. delegatensis subsp. tasmaniensis. Photo Specimen Only

Location: Crystal Hill, west of Lottah, Tasmania.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 metres in some plants, thin and flaky-stripy, otherwise smooth throughout, grey over green-yellow. Leaves glossy, dark green, narrower than in typical E. subcrenulata. Buds and fruits look typical for E. subcrenulata. Less than 10 trees here, on obscured rock outcrop in dense tall forest of Eucalyptus regnans and E. obliqua. AD, CANB Photos

Location: Crystal Hill, west of Lottah, Tasmania.
Description: Juveniles from old stem at 1 metre. leaves large, nearly orbicular, slightly discolorous, glossy, dark green. Less than 10 trees here, on obscured rock outcrop in dense tall forest of Eucalyptus regnans and E. obliqua. AD

Location: 'Sir Vim', Evercreech Forest Reserve, Tasmania.
Description: Climbed height: 91.3 metres. Crown spread: 19.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 11.00 metres.  Tree in health decline, but other trees of same species here are healthier.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Lookout Rock, Bicheno, Tasmania.
Description: Tree of poor form, to 8 metres tall. Bark +/- smooth throughout, grey over cream. Branchlets, buds, new growth and new fruits pruinose. On top of large granite outcrop with some Eucalyptus globulus. AD Seeds

Location: Cape Tourville lighthouse, Freycinet Peninsula, Tasmania.
Description: Stunted tree, many multi-stemmed, to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, stripy, tan-grey over cream. Leaves glossy, dark green. Common here, growing on granite bluff with Eucalyptus amygdalina and E. tenuiramis subsp. Northern. AD Photos Seeds

Location: Cape Tourville, Freycinet Peninsula, Tasmania.
Description: Mallee and poor-formed trees to 4 metres tall. Bark mostly rough, finely fissured, grey. Dominant here, growing in scrub with some Eucalyptus globulus and E. tenuiramis subsp. Northern. AD Seeds

Location: Devils Kitchen, near Doo Town, Tasman Peninsula, Tasmania.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall, but many smaller and poorly-formed. Bark mostly smooth throughout and with scribbles, some with platy bark on lower trunk. Leaves becoming slightly glossy, dark olive green. Branchlets pruinose. Dominant here, growing with some Eucalyptus amygdalina, E. globulus and E. obliqua. AD Photos Seeds

Location: South Coast Track, about 4/5 way to coast (between South Cape Beach and Cockle Creek), Tasmania.
Description: Mallee-like tree 3 metres tall, elsewhere here between 2 and 10 metres tall. Bark rough near base then smooth. Scattered here, growing in dense scrub with some Eucalyptus nitida. Also nearby on better-drained sites is E. obliqua. AD Photos Seeds

Location: Cape Queen Elizabeth, Bruny Island, Tasmania.
Description: Mallees of scraggy and dense habit, 2 to 3 metres tall. AD Photos Seeds

Location: 'Swearing Bobs Beast', Tasmania.
Description: Laser height: 63.0 metres. Crown spread: 24.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 16.60 metres.  On easterly slope in pure E. regnans forest (old growth + regrowth).  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 'Strong Girl', near corner of Johns Road and Rutherfords Road, Tasmania.
Description: Climbed height: 82.3 metres. Crown spread: 25.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 19.00 metres.  Single tree, leaning trunk, surrounded by E. regnans.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 'Troll', off Hermons Road, Tasmania.
Description: Climbed height: 56.5 metres. Crown spread: 18.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 18.00+ metres.  In rainforest and tall eucalypts.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 'Centurion', Tahune area, Tasmania.
Description: Climbed height: 99.6 metres. Crown spread: 18.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 13.70 metres.  Mixed rainforest and E. regnans forest on moderately steep north-east slope.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 'The Prefect', 100 metres downslope of 'Centurion', Tahune area, Tasmania.
Description: Climbed height: ? Crown spread: 18.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 15.40 metres.  Mixed rainforest and E. regnans forest on moderately steep north-east slope.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Lake Pedder lookout, Gordon River Road, Southwest National Park, Tasmania.
Description: Dominant here on hills as emergent eucalypt above low dense shrubland. Photo Specimen Only

Location: Lake Dobson, east side, Mount Field National Park, Tasmania.
Description: Growing with Eucalyptus coccifera dominant, and with E. subcrenulata and pruinose E. urnigera nearby. Photo Specimen Only

Location: Lake Dobson Road, Mount Field National Park, Tasmania.
Description: Laser height: 45.0 metres. Crown spread: 15.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 5.50 metres.  Tall open forest with rainforest understorey, co-dominant with E. subcrenulata and E. delegatensis subsp. tasmaniensis.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Lake Dobson Road, Mount Field National Park, Tasmania.
Description: Laser height: 51.5 metres. Crown spread: 18.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 6.90 metres.  Dominant here in tall open forest with beech myrtle understorey.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Lyell Hwy, just south-east of Bronte, Tasmania.
Description: Tree 22 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey over cream. Leaves glossy, mid-green, undulate. Growing on slightly undulating ground in low forest with Eucalyptus rodwayi and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. AD Seeds

Location: Lyell Hwy, just south-east of Bronte, Tasmania.
Description: Seedling leaves from roadside verge. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green, not pruinose, orbicular to ovate. Seedling stems rounded. AD

Location: Pumphouse Point Road, south-east shore of Lake St Clair, Tasmania.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, colourfully-streaked. On shore of lake with Eucalyptus nitida and some E. rodwayi. Photo Specimen Only

Location: Lake St Clair Road, between Derwent Bridge ad Lake St Clair, Tasmania.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Common along flats of Derwent River channel with Eucalyptus nitida and some E. dalrympleana subsp. Tasmania. Photo Specimen Only

Location: Saddle between Frenchmans Cap and Lions Head, Tasmania.
Description: Sprawling mallee shrub 0.5 metres tall, and seen up to 6 metres tall near Barons Pass. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey and tan. Leaves glossy, green. Common here as scattered plants on steep quartz slopes and ridge. AD, CANB Seeds Photos

Location: Henty Dunes, Zeehan - Straham Road, north of Strahan, Tasmania.
Description: Tree to 16 metres tall. Bark rough on lower stems. Leaves slightly discolorous, glossy and dark green above, slightly paler below. Common here in dense Leptospermum shrubland. Nearby is Eucalyptus nitida and E. viminalis subsp. viminalis. AD Seeds

Location: Pieman Road, about 3 km east of Wilson River, Serpentine Ridge, Tasmania.
Description: Poorly-formed tree 6 metres tall. Bark srough for 1 metre, smooth above. Leaves becoming glossy and dark green. New growth and new branchlets pruinose. Dominant here on serpentine hills in open shrubland. AD, CANB Seeds

Location: Murrays Plain, just east of Murchison Hwy, Tasmania.
Description: Trees to 28 metres tall. Adult material is typical of E. nitida, but slightly pruinose tips and slightly larger fruits. Sapling growth looks like E. nebulosa (pruinose tips). Seedling leaves more typical of E. coccifera and not pruinose. Probably E. nitida x E. coccifera hybrid swarm tending mostly towards E. nitida. Disturbed site with remnant trees, regrowth saplings and seedling along old track, dominated by this and with some Eucalyptus subcrenulata. AD

Location: Murrays Plain, just east of Murchison Hwy, Tasmania.
Description: Trees to 28 metres tall. Adult material is typical of E. nitida, but slightly pruinose tips and slightly larger fruits. Sapling growth looks like E. nebulosa (pruinose tips). Seedling leaves more typical of E. coccifera and not pruinose. Probably E. nitida x E. coccifera hybrid swarm tending mostly towards E. nitida. Disturbed site with remnant trees, regrowth saplings and seedling along old track, dominated by this and with some Eucalyptus subcrenulata. AD

Location: Murrays Plain, just east of Murchison Hwy, Tasmania.
Description: Trees to 28 metres tall. Adult material is typical of E. nitida, but slightly pruinose tips and slightly larger fruits. Sapling growth looks like E. nebulosa (pruinose tips). Seedling leaves more typical of E. coccifera and not pruinose. Probably E. nitida x E. coccifera hybrid swarm tending mostly towards E. nitida. Disturbed site with remnant trees, regrowth saplings and seedling along old track, dominated by this and with some Eucalyptus subcrenulata. AD

Location: Mona Vale Road, New South Wales.
Description: Very scraggy shrub to 4.5 metres tall. Locally common here, scattered in Banksia erecifolia shrubland, with Eucalyptus haemastoma and some Angophora crassifolia. AD Seed

Location: 200 metres down Ryland Track from Mona Vale Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Very scraggy, erect-stemmed shrub to 3 metres tall. Common here in Eucalyptus haemastoma dominated open woodland, in white sand on plateau with some Corymbia gummifera and E. capitellata. AD, CANB Seed + photos

Location: Blue Pool car park, Blue Mountains National park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 8 metres tall. Mostly in mid to late flower here. Common here on sandstone slope with Corymbia eximia, Eucalyptus agglomerata and E. piperita. AD Seed

Location: Milmed Swamp, Wiperfield National Park, Victoria.
Description: Mallee to 8 metres tall. Bark rough for < 1 metre, then smooth, dark olive-grey. Leaves slightly glossy, olive-green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus leucoxylon subsp. stephaniae here, on slightly undulating orange sandy loam, also with some E. porosa nearby. Elsewhere here is dominated by E. incrassata and E. leptophylla on white sand. AD

Location: C. 2 km north of Brim towards Beulah, Victoria.
Description: Several- to multi-stemmed tree of poor form, to 7 metres tall. Bark rough to half tree height. Leaves dull, bluish at first, maturing glossy and dark green. Growing on brown clay-loam on flat with Eucalyptus largiflorens and intermediates between E. odorata and E. largiflorens. AD, MEL Seeds

Location: Corner Vaughan Spring Rd and To Up And Down Track, Fryers Range, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 17 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, moderately fissured, flaky-fibrous, grey-brown. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Growing in valley in low forest with Eucalyptus obliqua, E. nortonii and E. polyanthemos subsp. vestita. AD, MEL Seeds

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus bunyip (= E. camphora subsp. humeana - E. strzeleckii intergrade)
Location: Creek crossing c. 1 km east of Camp Rd on Tonimbuk Rd, Bunyip State Park, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 4 metres then smooth above. Leaves slightly discolorous, glossy and green above. Patches of trees in swampy creek, in open forest with Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. viminalis and E. cypellocarpa. Just above creek is E. radiata subsp. radiata and tall E. fulgens. AD Seeds

Location: Avon River channel, Avon - Mt Hendrick Scenic Reserve, Victoria.
Description: Multi-stemmed tree to 20 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout or rough for 1 to 2 metres, E. elata-like, dark grey, then smooth above, pale grey over cream. Juvenile leaves pruinose. All adult parts non-pruinose. Adult leaves glossy, +/- green. About 50 plants on edge and in island of rocky-gravely river channel, some broken but regrowing from lignotuber following floods, in +/- pure stand. Nearby is Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. viminalis, and higher on slopes is E. tricarpa, E. goniocalyx subsp. goniocalyx and E. polyanthemos subsp. vestita (pruinose). AD, MEL Seeds

Location: Dermody Rd, Avon - Mt Hendrick Scenic Reserve, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, deeply fissured, hard. Waxiness variable between trees, some very pruinose and grey, others not pruinose and dark green-leaved. In full flower (cream to very pale yellow). Common here on stony hills with Eucalyptus polyanthemos subsp. vestita, E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha, E. consideniana, E. globoidea, E. cypellocarpa and E. ?muelleriana. AD Seeds

Location: Dermody Rd, Avon - Mt Hendrick Scenic Reserve, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, finely fissured, grey and pale grey. Leaves pruinose, greyish. Buds and branchlets conspicuously grey. In full flower. Dominant here on stony hills with Eucalyptus tricarpa, E. macrorhyncha subsp. macrorhyncha, E. consideniana, E. globoidea, E. cypellocarpa and E. ?muelleriana. AD Seeds

Location: Western Boundary Track, Holey Plains State Forest, Victoria.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 10 metres tall, spreading to tumbledown habit. Bark rough throughout, finely to moderately fissured, grey-brown. Leaves glossy, green. Pure stand on slightly undulating grey sand, forming low open woodland with Banksia serrata. AD Seeds

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus caroliniae (= E. cypellocarpa - E. goniocalyx intergrade)
Location: Norfolk Rd at Hopetoun Creek crossing, Mt Martha, Victoria.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall. Bark variable, rough on trunk or to small branches, moderately coarsely fissured (like E. goniocalyx), brown. Leaves glossy, dark green. Scattered in weedy creek valley with Eucalyptus viminalis subsp. viminalis. AD Seeds

Location: Micalong Swamp Flora Reserve, Brindabella Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 18 metres tall, some multi-trunked. Dominant here in swampy creek with Eucalyptus stellulata and E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Brindabella Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 35 metres tall. Bark rough for <1 metre, then smooth, pale grey over white. In forest on orange clay-loam at 1080 m ASL, with Eucalyptus robertsonii, E. pauciflora subsp. pauciflora and E. viminalis subsp. viminalis. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Tianjara Falls car park, Morton National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Poor-formed tree 6 metres tall. Co-dominant with Corymbia gummifera on sandstone plateau. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Braidwood Rd, Parma Creek Nature Reserve, New South Wales.
Description: Whipstick mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over coppery-tan. No parts pruinose. Leaves glossy, green. In full flower. Clumps of mallees on sandstone soil with Corymbia gummifera and Eucalyptus racemosa. AD Seeds + photos

Location: Sir Bertam Stevens Drv, Royal National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Common in area, in dense shrubland high in landscape with Angophora hispida and Corymbia gummifera. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Sir Bertam Stevens Drv, Royal National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Whipstick mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Buds and branchlets strongly angular, pruinose. Leaves quite glossy, green. Scattered on slightly undulating sandstone in dense mallee shrubland with Angophora hispida, Corymbia gummifera, Eucalyptus obstans and depauperate E. sieberi. AD Seeds + photos

Location: West Head Rd, Elvina Track turnoff, Ku-Ring-Gai Chase National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Dense-crowned mallee 3 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy. Leaves thick, glossy, green. Locally frequent over a few hectares, in low dense shrubland on sandstone rise with Angophora hispida, Corymbia gummifera and some Eucalyptus haemastoma. AD Seeds + photos

Location: Cambell Drv, Munmorah State Conservation Area, New South Wales.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey over cream, with scribbles. Leaves glossy, mid green. Growing on undulating hills in low open woodland with Angophora costata, Corymbia gummifera and Eucalyptus capitellata. AD Seeds

Location: Scotchmans Range Rd, Scotchman State Forest, east of Bellingen, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, but many flakes attached, grey-brown over pale orange. Leaves discolorous, glossy and green above. Scattered here, growing on ridge in dry forest of Corymbia intermedia, Eucalyptus pilularis, E. siderophloia, E. carnea and E. propinqua. AD, CANB Seed

Location: Tyringham Rd at Double Creek, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark loosely rough for 2 to 8 metres, stripy, grey-brown over yellow-cream. Leaves dull and grey-green at first, maturing glossy and green. Scattered stands on slopes and in valleys, with some Eucalyptus saligna and E. campanulata. AD Seeds

Location: Davies Creek Circuit, Lamington National Park, Queensland.
Description: Laser height: 38.0 metres (under-crown measurement, true height potentially 5 to 10+ metres more). Crown spread: 20.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 9.45 metres.  Scattered old trees in rainforest, some Casuarina.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Surprise Rock, Davies Creek Circuit, Lamington National Park, Queensland.
Description: Tree 8 metres tall, others 5 to 20 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, stringy. Leaves glossy, green. Scattered on top of rocky plateau, especially around outcrops, with Eucalyptus campanulata and E. microcodon, and E. notabilis nearby. AD, BRI Seeds + photos

Location: 'Bigfoot', Bellbird Lookout track, Binna Burra, Lamington National Park, Queensland.
Description: Laser height: 47.0 metres (under-crown measurement, true height potentially 5+ metres more). Crown spread: 20.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 8.25 metres.  Remnant tree in rainforest, also with emergent Eucalyptus saligna.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Bellbird lookout track, c. 200 m from lookout, Binna Burra, Queensland.
Description: Laser height: 49.5 metres (+/- 0.5 metres). Crown spread: 18.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 7.80 metres.  Emergent tree in rainforest.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Newell Hwy, Pilliga East State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Tree, most several-trunked, to 10 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches here, finely to moderately fissured, brown. Leaves dull, green. Common here on red sandy loam with Angophora floribunda and Eucalyptus rossii. AD Photos

Location: C. 5 km west of Nymagee on Cobar Rd, New South Wales.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, yellow-tan and brown. Leaves glossy, light green. On low, broad rise in mallee shrubland dominated by Eucalyptus dumosa and E. socialis susbp. socialis, and also with some E. intertexta, E. sideroxylon and E. viridis. AD, CANB Seeds + photos

Location: Barrier Hwy between Wilcannia and Cobar, New South Wales.
Description: Scattered clumps on red sandy loam with scattered Eucalyptus populnea subsp. bimbil and E. intertexta. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Barrier Hwy between Wilcannia and Cobar, New South Wales.
Description: In very open woodland on red loam on plain with open Acacia shrubland understory. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Ghost Gum Walk, Simpsons Gap, West MacDonnell National Park, Northern Territory.
Description: Laser height: 22.5 metres. Crown spread: 27.5 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 5.05 metres (primary trunk).  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Kata Tjuta Rd, c. halfway between Uluru and Kata Tjuta, Northern Territory.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Leaves very glossy, green. Single clump of mallees about 15 metres in diameter, on red sand of broad swale between dunes with Eucalyptus gamophylla and Allocasuarina decaisneana. Photo Specimen Only.

Location: Mambray Creek campground, c. 15 metres west of toilet block, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 28.0 metres. Crown spread: 25.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 13.92 metres.  Very old tree, fragmented almost to ground level but originally one trunk.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Mambray Creek campground, c. 15 metres south-west of toilet block, South Australia.
Description: Laser height: 39.0 metres. Crown spread: 27.0 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 7.58 metres. Estimated age: 150+ years.  Tall, solid-trunked tree.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: 400 metres north of Broughtons Waterhole, then 100 metres east of track, Little Desert National Park, Victoria.
Description: Mallee to 8 metres tall. Leaves glossy, dark green. Two clumps, about 50 m apart, in Eucalyptus wimmerensis dominated vegetation, with some E. arenacea, E. leucoxylon subsp. pruinosa. Probably a hybrid or backcross involving E. wimmerensis. AD, CANB, MELB Seeds + photos

Location: McDonald Hwy, Little Desert National Park, Victoria.
Description: Mallee or scraggy tree to 7 metres tall. On white sand with Eucalyptus arenacea, E. incrassata and E. leptophylla. AD Seeds + photos

Location: 2/3 way up south-west slope of Mt Jefcott, Victoria.
Description: = E. viridis - E. polybractea intergrade/hybrid. One clump over 12 x 6 metre area. Burnt one year ago. No mature fruits. Photo Specimen Only

Location: Clive & Catherine's private property, Fyans Creek, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 38.5 metres. Crown spread: 27.5 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 13.99 metres. Distance to first branch: 6.8 metres. Distance to bifurcation: 11.8 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Private property south of D.Nicolle 6914, Fyans Creek, Victoria.
Description: Laser height: 44.0 metres. Crown spread: 26.5 metres average. Trunk circumference at breast height: 8.58 metres.  Big Tree Record only + photos

Location: Finey Road, south-east of Tammin, Western Australia.
Description: Mallees to 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout (some rough up to 200 mm above ground level only). Leaves glossy, mid-green. More or less pure stand, growing on white sandy loam flat, with some Eucalyptus capillosa and E. loxophleba subsp. loxophleba on slightly higher ground. AD, CANB, PERTH Photos

Location: Finey Road, south-east of Tammin, Western Australia.
Description: Juvenile and intermediate leaves from lignotuber coppice. Leaves rounded, grey, glaucous (like those of Eucalyptus horistes). More or less pure stand, growing on white sandy loam flat, with some Eucalyptus capillosa and E. loxophleba subsp. loxophleba on slightly higher ground. AD PERTH

Location: Great Eastern Highway, south-west of Boorabbin, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, mid-green. Dominant here, growing on a slight rise of sandy loam, with some Eucalyptus pileata. PERTH

Location: Great Eastern Highway, south-west of Boorabbin, Western Australia.
Description: Juveniles from lignotuber coppice. Leaves elliptical, dull, green-green, slightly waxy. Dominant here, growing on a slight rise of sandy loam, with some Eucalyptus pileata. PERTH

Location: Jaudi Hills, Western Australia.
Description: Scraggy mallee to 4 metres tall (this one 2 metres tall). Bark minniritchi throughout. Leaves dull, greyish. Branchlets and buds waxy. Dozens of scattered mallees growing in dense Acacia shrubland with lots of Eucalyptus ewartiana on low hills of stony red loam. AD PERTH Photos

Location: Jaudi Hills, Western Australia.
Description: Spreading mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark minniritchi. Fruits more or less variable in size and mostly smooth. All buds in threes. Hundreds growing here, scattered on red stony hills in Acacia scrub with some Eucalyptus longissima. PERTH Seed

Location: Just east of Coolgardie North Road near Rowles Lagoon (just south of Credo turn-off), Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark variable, smooth throughout or rough for 1 metre. Leaves glossy, light green. Branchlets glaucous on some, but variable. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus yilgarnensis (some E. salmonophloia), growing on low flat of red clay-loam. PERTH

Location: Coolgardie North Road, Western Australia.
Description: In very open woodland with Eucalyptus salubris, E. salmonophloia and E. transcontinentalis. Photo specimen only.

Location: Coolgardie North Road, Western Australia.
Description: Common here, growing on very low rolling hills in stony red loam with Eucalyptus celastroides, E. clelandii, E salmonophloia and E. transcontinentalis. Photo specimen only.

Location: Granite outcrop, west-south-west of Mussons Soak, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3.5 metres tall. Bark minniritchi. All parts waxy. Leaves dull, purple-grey-green. A dozen plants growing on edge of low granite outcrop but very high in larger-scale landscape. With some Eucalyptus loxophleba subsp. lissophloia (E. comitae-vallis and E. oleosa nearby). PERTH Photos

Location: Callion to Mussons Soak track, Western Australia.
Description: Robust tree-mallees to 7 metres tall. Branchlets variably glaucous. Growing on red loam with Eucalyptus comitae-vallis and E. rigidula. PERTH Seed Photos

Location: Callion to Mussons Soak track, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall.  Growing on red loam on plain in open woodland with Eucalyptus longissima and E. horistes (bark rough up to 0.8 metres from base). Photo specimen only.

Location: 200 metres north of below coordinates. West of Callion on track to Mussons Soak, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3.5 metres tall. Bark minniritchi. Flowers pale creamy yellow. All parts glaucous. More than 100 plants scattered in mulga scrub on low stony rise of red loam. AD PERTH

Location: 200 metres north of below coordinates. West of Callion on track to Mussons Soak, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3.5 metres tall. Bark minniritchi. Flowers pale creamy yellow. All parts glaucous. Quite variable in fruit size and ribbing (smooth to noticeably ribbed). More than 100 plants scattered in mulga scrub on low stony rise of red loam. AD PERTH Photos

Location: Davyhurst Road, Western Australia.
Description: On red gravelly sand on level country, growing with Eucalyptus concinna and Acacia shrubs. Photo specimen only.

Location: Pianto Road, Goongarrie National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark variable, smooth throughout or rough to 1.5 metres. Leaves glossy, light green.  First seen from west, growing on plain of red sand in Acacia shrubland with some Eucalyptus longissima. AD PERTH Seed

Location: Pianto Road, Goongarrie National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Coppice from stem at 1 metre. Coppice leaves narrow, grey-green, waxy. Growing on plain of red sand in Acacia shrubland with some Eucalyptus longissima. PERTH

Location: Pianto Road, Goongarrie National Park, Western Australia.
Description: Robust tree-mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, glossy, greenish-red. Branchlets waxy. A few plants, growing on red sand plain with Eucalyptus sp. Mulga Rock dominant, and some E. comitae-vallis and E. longissima. PERTH

Location: Yarri Road, north of Pianto Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark rough for 2 metres. Leaves maturing glossy green. A few large clumps growing in mulga scrub on edge of granite outcrops. PERTH

Location: Just north of Lords Bore, near Kirgella Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 5 metres tall. Bark rough for 1.2 metres, flaky-fibrous. Leaves glossy, mid-green. Growing on red loam on flat in mulga shrubland with Eucalyptus longissima, E. concinna and E. rigidula. PERTH

Location: Nippon Highway, east of Kirgella Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 8 metres tall. Bark rough for 1-2 metres, grey. Branchlets waxy. Leaves dull, blue-green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus platycorys on high, very broad rise of red sand. Eucalyptus youngiana, E. concinna and E. rigidula nearby on slightly lower sites. PERTH Photos

Location: Nippon Highway, east of Kirgella Rocks, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough for 1-2 metres. Leaves glossy, dark green, thick. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus hypolaena on high, very broad rise of red sand. Eucalyptus youngiana, E. concinna and E. rigidula nearby on slightly lower sites. PERTH Photos

Location: East side of Ponton Creek on new mining road, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, light green.  Scattered trees here, growing on low broad flat with some Eucalyptus gracilis and E. cylindrocarpa. PERTH

Location: New mining road, between Mulga Rockhole and Ponton Creek, Western Australia.
Description: Whipstick mallee to 2.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Fruit size variable, this among smallest. First seen of this species when coming from the west. Growing on red sand plain with Eucalyptus youngiana, E. rigidula, E. gongylocarpa (first seen from west) and E. sp. Queen Victoria Spring (first seen from west). PERTH

Location: New mining road, between Mulga Rockhole and Ponton Creek, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee, spreading, to 1.5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, blue-grey. Flowers yellow. First seen of this species when coming from the west. Common here, growing on slightly undulating plain of red sand over limestone, with Eucalyptus hypolaena, E. mannensis subsp. mannensis and E. platycorys. PERTH Photos

Location: New mining road, between Mulga Rockhole and Ponton Creek, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough for ca. 1 metre. Leaves very glossy, dark green. First seen of this species when coming from the west. Common here, growing on slightly undulating plain of red sand over limestone, with Eucalyptus hypolaena, E. pimpiniana and E. platycorys. PERTH Seed

Location: New mining road, just east of Mulga Rockhole track, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall (regrowth from fire). Leaves dull, blue-green. Buds and fruits glaucous.  Growing on red sand, undulating, with Eucalyptus ebbanoensis subsp. glauciramula, E. platycorys, E. sp. Mulga Rock, E. pimpiniana and E. hypolaena. PERTH Photos

Location: New mining road, north-east of Mulga Rockhole, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall (regrowth from fire). Leaves glossy, green. All fruits sessile.  Common here, growing on high, very broad rise, in pale orange sand with Eucalyptus gongylocarpa, E. youngiana, E. mannensis subsp. mannensis and E. sp. Mulga Rock. AD CANB PERTH Seed Photos

FieldDetermination: Eucalyptus sp. Great Victoria Desert - E. horistes intergrade?
Location: PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall, burnt. Bark looks like it would have been smooth. Juveniles from lignotuber, rounded to ovate, well spaced, glaucous. Growing on red sand between complex dunes with Eucalyptus gongylocarpa and E. youngiana. PERTH Photos

Location: PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3.5 metres tall. Bark smooth but ribbony, bronze-tan. Leaves glossy, green. Growing on red sand in undulating dunes with Eucalyptus gongylocarpa, E. youngiana and E. mannensis subsp. mannensis. PERTH Seed Photos

Location: PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 6 metres tall.  Growing on very slightly undulating pale orange sand with Eucalyptus mannensis subsp. mannensis, E. sp. Great Victoria Desert, E. youngiana, E. gongylocarpa and Callitris, with a Triodia understory. Photo specimen only

Location: PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Long-unburnt mallees to 4.5 metres tall. Bark mostly minniritchi, but thick and layered on lower stems. Leaves dull, blue-green, some glaucous. Fruit size variable. About 100 plants, growing  in dense mulga shrubland on a flat of hard red loam (shallow soil over outcropping stone). AD PERTH Seed Photos

Location: PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Whipstick mallee 2 metres tall. Bark minniritchi. Branchlets and fruits glaucous. Leaves dull, slightly blue-green. Growing on flat of red loam over some outcropping limestone, with Eucalyptus trivalva and E. concinna dominant (and some E. youngiana). PERTH Photos

Location: PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Burnt mallees 3 metres tall. Regrowth to 1 metre tall, dull, greyish, slightly waxy.  Growing in red sand on very slight rise with Eucalyptus platycorys and E. gongylocarpa. AD PERTH

Location: PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling mallee 1.5 metres tall. Leaves dull, blue-grey. Only one old plant seen here, growing on red sand plain with Eucalyptus platycorys, E. sp. Cable Haul Road and E. sp. Kitchener. PERTH

Location: Cable Haul Road, south of PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 metre, tightly held, grey, smooth above. Leaves glossy, green. Growing on red sand on slight rise in mallee with Eucalyptus sp. Cable Haul Road and E. platycorys. AD PERTH Seed Photos

Location: Cable Haul Road, south of PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Juveniles big, more or less rounded to ovate, dull, blue-green, not or slightly waxy. Growing on red sand on slight rise in mallee with Eucalyptus sp. Cable Haul Road and E. platycorys. AD PERTH

Location: Cable Haul Road, south of PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Robust mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark rough for 1-2 metres, tightly held, smooth cream over grey above. Leaves moderately glossy, dark green. No parts glaucous. Flowers cream. Growing on red sand on slight rise in mallee with Eucalyptus sp. Kitchener and E. platycorys. AD PERTH Seed

Location: Cable Haul Road, south of PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 2 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, pale green. Scattered in low area between rises in low shrubland on red loam with some Eucalyptus concinna, E. rigidula and E. youngiana. PERTH

Location: Cable Haul Road, south of PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall. Bark ribbony-rough on lower stems, smooth pale tan and cream and ribbony above. Leaves glossy, green, completely lacking oil glands. Growing on red sandy-loam plain over limestone in open mallee with Eucalyptus concinna and E. sp. Cable Haul Road. PERTH Seed Photos

Location: Cable Haul Road, south of PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Robust mallee to 8 metres tall. Bark rough for 1-2 metres, smooth above. Leaves glossy, green, no parts waxy.  Growing on red sandy-loam plain over limestone in open mallee with Eucalyptus concinna and E rigidula. (This always with green leaves, but dull to glossy.) AD CANB PERTH Seed Photos

Location: Cable Haul Road, south of PNC Baseline Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, coppery-grey. Leaves glossy green. Growing on plain of red sand with Eucalyptus concinna, E. gypsophila, E. sp. Kitchener and E. sp. Cable Haul Road (non-waxy green). PERTH

Location: Kitchener to Tjuntjunjarra road, west of Cable Haul Road, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark mostly smooth, some rough to 0.5 metres. Leaves very glossy, green.  Common here on slightly undulating red sand with Eucalyptus gongylocarpa, E. sp. Cable Haul Road, E. platycorys, E. youngiana and E. mannensis subsp. mannensis in mallee shrubland. AD CANB PERTH (proposed type) Photos of several plants

Location: Kitchener to Tjuntjunjarra road, west of Cable Haul Road, Western Australia.
Description: Coppice from same tree as D.Nicolle 6958. From stem at 1 metre. Leaves large, well spaced, elliptical to ovate, dull, grey-green, slightly waxy. Common here on slightly undulating red sand, growing with Eucalyptus gongylocarpa, E. sp. Cable Haul Road, E. platycorys, E. youngiana and E. mannensis subsp. mannensis in mallee shrubland. AD PERTH

Location: Kitchener to Tjuntjunjarra road, west of Cable Haul Road, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 9 metres tall. Bark more or less smooth throughout, dull tan/white. A small area of trees (and last seen going south) growing on slightly undulating red sand with Eucalyptus sp. Kitchener, E. sp. Cable Haul Road, E. platycorys, E. youngiana and E. mannensis subsp. mannensis in mallee shrubland. PERTH Photos

Location: Kitchener to Tjuntjunjarra road, west of Cable Haul Road, Western Australia.
Description: Erect-stemmed mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough for 1-2 metres, dark grey (like Eucalytpus hypolaena), smooth above. Leaves variable in gloss from plant to plant, dull to quite glossy, mostly green but some new growth lightly blue-green. No parts glaucous. Common here on slightly undulating red sand with Eucalyptus sp. Kitchener, E. gongylocarpa, E. platycorys, E. youngiana and E. mannensis subsp. mannensis in mallee shrubland. PERTH Photos of several plants.

Location: Kitchener to Tjuntjunjarra road, west of Cable Haul Road, Western Australia.
Description: Trees to 25 metres tall.  First seen of species when coming from the north, forming an open low forest on red clay-loam in more or less pure stand with Eucalyptus cylindrocarpa. Photo specimen only.

Location: East side of Lake Boonderoo, south-east of Kitchener, Western Australia.
Description: Large, old mallees and tree-like, to 9 metres tall. Bark rough for a few metres, then smooth. Leaves glossy, green. Pure stand growing on massive kopi escarpment, with Eucalyptus melanoxylon and E. gracilis nearby, also on kopi, but not the scarp. PERTH

Location: Emu Point Tank to Pioneer Tank track, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, shiny, orange-bronze. Leaves glossy, green. Lone tree, growing on pale red clay-loam in open Acacia papyrocarpa woodland with Maireana sedifolia. PERTH Photos

Location: Pioneer Tank to Newman Rock track, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 17 metres tall. Bark rough on lower to mid-trunk. Leaves glossy, green. Growing on very low hills of gravely (limestone) powdery pale brown loam in open woodland. Photo specimen only.

Location: 10.1 km from Pioneer Tank on track to Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Large mallee to 7 metres tall. Bark rough on lower stems, coarsly fissured, grey. Leaves slightly glossy, dark, slightly blue-green. First seen of this species when coming from the east. Growing on very slight rise of pale brown powdery loam with Eucalyptus gracilis, E. oleosa subsp. oleosa and E. salubris. PERTH

Location: 10.9 km from Pioneer Tank on track to Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Regrowth mallets from fire, 4 metres tall.  First seen of this species when coming from the east. Growing on pale grey limestoney gravel soil, mostly pure stand with Eucalyptus gracilis. PERTH

Location: Ca. 12 km from Pioneer Tank on track to Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Tree (mallet) to 16 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, white/tan. Leaves dull, dark blue-green. Branchlets, bud and fruits waxy. First seen of this species when coming from east. Growing on pale brown powdery loam with Eucalyptus oleosa subsp. oleosa. PERTH (Photos nearby)

Location: Ca. 12 km from Pioneer Tank on track to Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Robust mallees and tree-like, to 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, very ribbony. Leaves dull, blue-green maturing green. Branchlets slightly waxy. Growing on pale red powdery loam in Eucalyptus optima open woodland. PERTH Photos

Location: Ca. 15 km from Pioneer Tank on track to Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 metres tall (regrowth following fire). Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, maturing slightly glossy, blue-green. First seen of this species coming from the east. Growing with Eucalyptus oleosa subsp. oleosa on pale red loam. PERTH Photos

Location: Ca. 15 km from Pioneer Tank on track to Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves dull, blue-green, maturing slightly glossy. First seen of this species coming from the east. Growing on reddish loam on flat with Eucalyptus oleosa subsp. oleosa, E. flocktoniae subsp. hebes, E. eremophila and E. gracilis. PERTH

Location: Ca. 21 km from Pioneer Tank on track to Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallet 8 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey and orange. First seen of this species coming from the east. A few plants,grrowing on orange clay in open Eucalyptus salubris woodland. PERTH

Location: Eyre Highway, between Balladonia and Fraser Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout.  Common here, growing on high broad rise in mallee shrubland, on stony red loam with Eucalyptus effusa subsp. effusa, E. oleosa subsp. oleosa, E. spreta, E. sp. Kitchener, E. grossa, E. histophylla and E. terebra. PERTH

Location: Eyre Highway, between Balladonia and Fraser Range, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 5 metres tall. Bark rough for 0.8 metres. Leaves glossy, green, broader than D.Nicolle 6973. A few plants here (not common), growing on high broad rise in mallee shrubland, on stony red loam with Eucalyptus effusa subsp. effusa, E. oleosa subsp. oleosa, E. spreta, E. sp. Fraser Range, E. grossa, E. histophylla and E. terebra. PERTH Photos

Location: Eyre Highway, between Balladonia and Fraser Range, Western Australia.
Description: Juvenile leaves from suppressed seedling. Leaves well-spaced, dull, grey-green, slightly glaucous. Growing on high broad rise in mallee shrubland, on stony red loam with Eucalyptus effusa subsp. effusa, E. oleosa subsp. oleosa, E. spreta, E. sp. Fraser Range, E. grossa, E. histophylla and E. terebra. PERTH

Location: New mining access track in area north of Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout. Leaves glossy, green. Co-dominant with Eucalyptus websteriana here, growing on red loam on outcropping granite, with some E. gracilis and E. planipes. PERTH Photos

Location: New mining access track in area north of Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth thoughout. Leaves very glossy, light green. Growing on fringe of granite rocky low hill with Eucalyptus gracilis and E. sp. Fraser Range. PERTH

Location: New mining access track in area north of Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee, whipstick, to 3 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale brown and grey. Leaves glossy dark green. Dominant here, growing on high broad hill of shallow red clay-loam, with Eucalyptus effusa subsp. effusa, E. spreta, E. eremophila and E. planipes. (Eucalyptus prolixa nearby on lower ground in deeper soils.) PERTH Photos

Location: New mining access track in area north of Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Bushy mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark minniritchi. Leaves dull, blue-green. Waxiness variable here, mostly weakly or not glaucous like this. Locally very common, growing on broad rise of outcropping stone with red loam, with some Eucalyptus sp. Fraser Range. PERTH Photos

Location: New mining access track in area north of Newman Rock, Western Australia.
Description: Bushy mallee to 4 metres tall. Bark minniritchi. Leaves dull, blue-green. Waxiness variable here, this one with moderately waxy features. Locally very common, growing on broad rise of outcropping stone with red loam, with some Eucalyptus sp. Fraser Range. PERTH Seed

Location: Eyre Highway, between Norseman and Fraser Range, Western Australia.
Description: Trees and mallees to 8 metres tall. Bark rough for 1 to 2 metres. Leaves glossy, green. Growing on low rise in depression around salt lake with Eucalyptus eremophila and E. spreta. PERTH

Location: Eyre Highway, between Norseman and Fraser Range, Western Australia.
Description: Juveniles from seedling in road verge. Leaves rounded, greyish, waxy. Growing on low rise in depression around salt lake with Eucalyptus eremophila and E. spreta. PERTH

Location: Ca. 10 km north from Eyre Highway on Heartbreak Ridge track, Western Australia.
Description: Regrowth mallets 5 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, shiny, coppery-bronze. Leaves glossy, green. Growing in minor creek with Eucalyptus planipes, E. salmonophloia, E. loxophleba subsp. lissophloia and E. urna. PERTH

Location: Ca. 12 km north from Eyre Highway on Heartbreak Ridge track, Western Australia.
Description: Effuse mallee, to 2.5 metres tall. Leaves thick, glossy, dark green. First seen of this species coming from the south. Small patch growing on red clay-loam with Eucalyptus ravida (greyish-leaved form), E. celastroides subsp. celastroides and E. salmonophloia. PERTH

Location: Ca. 30 km north of Eyre Highway on Heartbreak Ridge track, south of Woodline Hills, Western Australia.
Description: Large mallees (some tree-like) to 14 metres tall. Bark rough for 1-3 metres, fibrous-flakey, grey, smooth pale tan above. Locally dominant in open mallee, growing on pale yellow sandhills with Callitris. PERTH Seed Photos

Location: Ca. 30 km north of Eyre Highway on Heartbreak Ridge track, south of Woodline Hills, Western Australia.
Description: Juveniles from lignotuber. Juvenile leaves rounded to ovate, smallish, grey, glaucous. Locally dominant in open mallee, growing on pale yellow sandhills with Callitris. PERTH

Location: Woodline Hills, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall. Bark variably rough at base, mostly smooth to up to 2 metres. Branchlets waxy. Locally common on rocky hills, growing with Eucalyptus salmonophloia, E. lesouefii, E. celastroides subsp. celastroides and E. loxophleba subsp. lissophloia. PERTH Photos

Location: North of Woodline Hills, Western Australia.
Description: Trees to 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, shiny, bronze-orange. Pure stand forming open woodland on red clay, with some Eucalyptus salmonophloia and E. celastroides subsp. celastroides . Photo specimen only.

Location: Southern bluff of 'Coffin Hill', Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 12 metres tall.
